					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><p>
This is a <a href="/wiki/Bibliography" title="Bibliography">bibliography</a> of works on the <a href="/wiki/Latter_Day_Saint_movement" title="Latter Day Saint movement">Latter Day Saint movement</a>.
</p>
<meta property="mw:PageProp/toc" />
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="General">General</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: General"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Overviews">Overviews</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Overviews"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<ul><li><style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r1215172403">.mw-parser-output cite.citation{font-style:inherit;word-wrap:break-word}.mw-parser-output .citation q{quotes:"\"""\"""'""'"}.mw-parser-output .citation:target{background-color:rgba(0,127,255,0.133)}.mw-parser-output .id-lock-free.id-lock-free a{background:url("//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/65/Lock-green.svg")right 0.1em center/9px no-repeat}body:not(.skin-timeless):not(.skin-minerva) .mw-parser-output .id-lock-free a{background-size:contain}.mw-parser-output .id-lock-limited.id-lock-limited a,.mw-parser-output .id-lock-registration.id-lock-registration a{background:url("//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d6/Lock-gray-alt-2.svg")right 0.1em center/9px no-repeat}body:not(.skin-timeless):not(.skin-minerva) .mw-parser-output .id-lock-limited a,body:not(.skin-timeless):not(.skin-minerva) .mw-parser-output .id-lock-registration a{background-size:contain}.mw-parser-output .id-lock-subscription.id-lock-subscription a{background:url("//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/aa/Lock-red-alt-2.svg")right 0.1em center/9px no-repeat}body:not(.skin-timeless):not(.skin-minerva) .mw-parser-output .id-lock-subscription a{background-size:contain}.mw-parser-output .cs1-ws-icon a{background:url("//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/4c/Wikisource-logo.svg")right 0.1em center/12px no-repeat}body:not(.skin-timeless):not(.skin-minerva) .mw-parser-output .cs1-ws-icon a{background-size:contain}.mw-parser-output .cs1-code{color:inherit;background:inherit;border:none;padding:inherit}.mw-parser-output .cs1-hidden-error{display:none;color:#d33}.mw-parser-output .cs1-visible-error{color:#d33}.mw-parser-output .cs1-maint{display:none;color:#2C882D;margin-left:0.3em}.mw-parser-output .cs1-format{font-size:95%}.mw-parser-output .cs1-kern-left{padding-left:0.2em}.mw-parser-output .cs1-kern-right{padding-right:0.2em}.mw-parser-output .citation .mw-selflink{font-weight:inherit}html.skin-theme-clientpref-night .mw-parser-output .cs1-maint{color:#18911F}html.skin-theme-clientpref-night .mw-parser-output .cs1-visible-error,html.skin-theme-clientpref-night .mw-parser-output .cs1-hidden-error{color:#f8a397}@media(prefers-color-scheme:dark){html.skin-theme-clientpref-os .mw-parser-output .cs1-visible-error,html.skin-theme-clientpref-os .mw-parser-output .cs1-hidden-error{color:#f8a397}html.skin-theme-clientpref-os .mw-parser-output .cs1-maint{color:#18911F}}</style><cite id="CITEREFHinckley1947" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Gordon_B._Hinckley" title="Gordon B. Hinckley">Hinckley, Gordon B.</a> (1947). <i><a href="/wiki/What_of_the_Mormons%3F" title="What of the Mormons?">What of the Mormons?</a>: A Brief Study of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints</i>. <a href="/wiki/Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints" class="mw-redirect" title="Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints">Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1494053462" title="Special:BookSources/1494053462"><bdi>1494053462</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=What+of+the+Mormons%3F%3A+A+Brief+Study+of+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.pub=Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.date=1947&amp;rft.isbn=1494053462&amp;rft.aulast=Hinckley&amp;rft.aufirst=Gordon+B.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>As part of the celebration of the 100th anniversary of the <a href="/wiki/Mormon_pioneers" title="Mormon pioneers">Mormon pioneers</a>' arrival in the <a href="/wiki/Salt_Lake_Valley" title="Salt Lake Valley">Salt Lake Valley</a>, LDS church president <a href="/wiki/George_Albert_Smith" title="George Albert Smith">George Albert Smith</a> tasked Hinckley (then employed as the Executive Secretary to the Church Radio, Publicity, and Mission Literature Committee) to write a book which would introduce the Church to non-members; it is divided into two sections— "The Mormons Today: A Contemporary Picture" and "The Mormons Yesterday: Their History"; beginning in 1969, the Church began publishing the historical part alone under the title <i>Truth Restored: A Short History of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints</i>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFLudlow1992" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Daniel_H._Ludlow" title="Daniel H. Ludlow">Ludlow, Daniel H.</a>, ed. (1992). <i><a href="/wiki/Encyclopedia_of_Mormonism" title="Encyclopedia of Mormonism">Encyclopedia of Mormonism</a>: The History, Scripture, Doctrine, and Procedure of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints</i>. New York: <a href="/wiki/Macmillan_Publishers_(United_States)" class="mw-redirect" title="Macmillan Publishers (United States)">Macmillan</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/002904040X" title="Special:BookSources/002904040X"><bdi>002904040X</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Encyclopedia+of+Mormonism%3A+The+History%2C+Scripture%2C+Doctrine%2C+and+Procedure+of+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Macmillan&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.isbn=002904040X&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://eom.byu.edu/">[1]</a>
<ul><li>A semiofficial encyclopedia for topics relevant to the LDS Church. Published in four volumes, with an optional fifth volume containing the "<a href="/wiki/Standard_Works" class="mw-redirect" title="Standard Works">Standard Works</a>."</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBushman2008" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Richard_Bushman" title="Richard Bushman">Bushman, Richard Lyman</a> (22 April 2008). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=BgkSDAAAQBAJ"><i>Mormonism: A Very Short Introduction</i></a>. <a href="/wiki/Oxford_University_Press,_USA" class="mw-redirect" title="Oxford University Press, USA">Oxford University Press, USA</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0195310306" title="Special:BookSources/978-0195310306"><bdi>978-0195310306</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormonism%3A+A+Very+Short+Introduction&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press%2C+USA&amp;rft.date=2008-04-22&amp;rft.isbn=978-0195310306&amp;rft.aulast=Bushman&amp;rft.aufirst=Richard+Lyman&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DBgkSDAAAQBAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A compact (144 pages) history of the LDS Church, and survey of contentious issues in contemporary Mormonism; an installment in the <i><a href="/wiki/Very_Short_Introductions" title="Very Short Introductions">Very Short Introductions</a></i> book series by an eminent historian and practicing Mormon.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFShipps1987" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Jan_Shipps" title="Jan Shipps">Shipps, Jan</a> (1987). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=mIr3eviKfE0C"><i>Mormonism: The Story of a New Religious Tradition</i></a>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0252014170" title="Special:BookSources/0252014170"><bdi>0252014170</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormonism%3A+The+Story+of+a+New+Religious+Tradition&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=1987&amp;rft.isbn=0252014170&amp;rft.aulast=Shipps&amp;rft.aufirst=Jan&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DmIr3eviKfE0C&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Scholarly analysis of the religion's origins and development; written by a <a href="/wiki/Cultural_historian" class="mw-redirect" title="Cultural historian">cultural historian</a>, who is a leading authority on Mormonism (yet not a member of the faith).</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFOstlingOstling2012" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Richard_Ostling" class="mw-redirect" title="Richard Ostling">Ostling, Richard</a>; <a href="/wiki/Joan_K._Ostling" class="mw-redirect" title="Joan K. Ostling">Ostling, Joan K.</a> (2012) [2001]. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=5h6paNzoIOIC"><i>Mormon America: The Power and the Promise</i></a> (revised and updated&#160;ed.). <a href="/wiki/HarperCollins" title="HarperCollins">HarperCollins</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0061432958" title="Special:BookSources/978-0061432958"><bdi>978-0061432958</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormon+America%3A+The+Power+and+the+Promise&amp;rft.edition=revised+and+updated&amp;rft.pub=HarperCollins&amp;rft.date=2012&amp;rft.isbn=978-0061432958&amp;rft.aulast=Ostling&amp;rft.aufirst=Richard&amp;rft.au=Ostling%2C+Joan+K.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D5h6paNzoIOIC&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>By journalists who sought to write "a candid but non-<a href="/wiki/Polemical" class="mw-redirect" title="Polemical">polemical</a>" overview of the Mormon world; investigates <a href="/wiki/Finances_of_The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints" class="mw-redirect" title="Finances of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints">the LDS Church's finances</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMauss1994" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Armand_Mauss" title="Armand Mauss">Mauss, Armand L.</a> (1994). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Angel_and_the_Beehive&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Angel and the Beehive (page does not exist)">The Angel and the Beehive</a>: The Mormon Struggle with Assimilation</i>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0252020715" title="Special:BookSources/0252020715"><bdi>0252020715</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Angel+and+the+Beehive%3A+The+Mormon+Struggle+with+Assimilation&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.isbn=0252020715&amp;rft.aulast=Mauss&amp;rft.aufirst=Armand+L.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=wTBUCGwdG8MC">[2]</a>
<ul><li>A sociological analysis of the previous forty years of Mormon history and a cultural "retrenchment" among Mormons— against <a href="/wiki/Cultural_assimilation" title="Cultural assimilation">assimilation</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBushman2006" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Claudia_Lauper_Bushman" title="Claudia Lauper Bushman">Bushman, Claudia L.</a> (30 January 2006). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Contemporary_Mormonism&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Contemporary Mormonism (page does not exist)">Contemporary Mormonism</a>: Latter-day Saints in Modern America</i>. <a href="/wiki/Greenwood_Publishing_Group" title="Greenwood Publishing Group">Greenwood Publishing Group</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/027598933X" title="Special:BookSources/027598933X"><bdi>027598933X</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Contemporary+Mormonism%3A+Latter-day+Saints+in+Modern+America&amp;rft.pub=Greenwood+Publishing+Group&amp;rft.date=2006-01-30&amp;rft.isbn=027598933X&amp;rft.aulast=Bushman&amp;rft.aufirst=Claudia+L.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=tGF7LdsbatoC">[3]</a>
<ul><li>A collection of the viewpoints of contemporary Mormons in America, on their beliefs, rituals, and practices; also their views on race, ethnicity, social class, gender, and sexual orientation.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFO&#39;Dea1957" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Thomas_F._O%27Dea&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Thomas F. O&#39;Dea (page does not exist)">O'Dea, Thomas F.</a> (1957). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Mormons_(book)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Mormons (book) (page does not exist)">The Mormons</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/The_University_of_Chicago_Press" class="mw-redirect" title="The University of Chicago Press">The University of Chicago Press</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Mormons&amp;rft.pub=The+University+of+Chicago+Press&amp;rft.date=1957&amp;rft.aulast=O%27Dea&amp;rft.aufirst=Thomas+F.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.olivercowdery.com/smithhome/1900s/Odea1957.htm">[4]</a>
<ul><li>A study of the Mormons and their religion by a non-member <a href="/wiki/Sociologist" class="mw-redirect" title="Sociologist">sociologist</a>; includes an account of LDS theology, with an analysis of the Book of Mormon.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="History">History</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: History"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFAllenLeonard1992" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/James_B._Allen_(historian)" title="James B. Allen (historian)">Allen, James B.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Glen_M._Leonard" title="Glen M. Leonard">Leonard, Glen M.</a> (1992) [1976]. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Story_of_the_Latter-day_Saints" title="The Story of the Latter-day Saints">The Story of the Latter-day Saints</a></i> (2nd, revised and enlarged&#160;ed.). Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Deseret_Book" class="mw-redirect" title="Deseret Book">Deseret Book</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/087579565X" title="Special:BookSources/087579565X"><bdi>087579565X</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Story+of+the+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.edition=2nd%2C+revised+and+enlarged&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Book&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.isbn=087579565X&amp;rft.aulast=Allen&amp;rft.aufirst=James+B.&amp;rft.au=Leonard%2C+Glen+M.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A single-volume history covering the LDS Church down to 1991. Commissioned by the Church Historical Department; it puts the history of the Church in the context of its times. First published on the one-hundredth anniversary of <a href="/wiki/Joseph_Fielding_Smith" title="Joseph Fielding Smith">Joseph Fielding Smith</a>'s birth; it was subject to some controversy within the Church, with some considering it not "spiritual enough."</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSmith1858" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Joseph_Smith" title="Joseph Smith">Smith, Joseph</a> (1858). <a href="/wiki/B._H._Roberts" title="B. H. Roberts">Roberts, B. H.</a> (ed.). <i><a href="/wiki/History_of_the_Church_(Joseph_Smith)" class="mw-redirect" title="History of the Church (Joseph Smith)">History of the Church</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Deseret_Book_Company" title="Deseret Book Company">Deseret Book Company</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0875794866" title="Special:BookSources/0875794866"><bdi>0875794866</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=History+of+the+Church&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Book+Company&amp;rft.date=1858&amp;rft.isbn=0875794866&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> Originally entitled <i>History of Joseph Smith</i>; a revised edition was published in seven volumes under the title <i>History of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints</i> from 1902 to 1932; it is currently published under the shortened title. <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://byustudies.byu.edu/history-of-the-church">[5]</a>
<ul><li>A semi-official history of the early Latter Day Saint movement during the lifetime of Joseph Smith. It is largely composed of Smith's writings with interpolations and editorial comments by Smith's secretaries and scribes; and, after Smith's death, historians of the LDS Church.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSmith1922" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Joseph_Fielding_Smith" title="Joseph Fielding Smith">Smith, Joseph Fielding</a> (1922). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Essentials_in_Church_History&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Essentials in Church History (page does not exist)">Essentials in Church History</a>: A History of the Church From the Birth of Joseph Smith to the Present Time (1922), With Introductory Chapters on the Antiquity of the Gospel and the "Falling Away,"</i>. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Deseret_News_Press" class="mw-redirect" title="Deseret News Press">Deseret News Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1290646546" title="Special:BookSources/1290646546"><bdi>1290646546</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Essentials+in+Church+History%3A+A+History+of+the+Church+From+the+Birth+of+Joseph+Smith+to+the+Present+Time+%281922%29%2C+With+Introductory+Chapters+on+the+Antiquity+of+the+Gospel+and+the+%22Falling+Away%2C%22&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+News+Press&amp;rft.date=1922&amp;rft.isbn=1290646546&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph+Fielding&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/EssentialsInChurchHistory">[6]</a>
<ul><li>Single volume history produced by the LDS Church; written by <a href="/wiki/Quorum_of_the_Twelve_Apostles_(LDS_Church)" title="Quorum of the Twelve Apostles (LDS Church)">an Apostle</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSmith2012" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Joseph_Smith" title="Joseph Smith">Smith, Joseph</a> (31 March 2012). <a href="/wiki/Karen_Lynn_Davidson" title="Karen Lynn Davidson">Davidson, Karen Lynn</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=David_J._Whittaker&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="David J. Whittaker (page does not exist)">Whittaker, David J.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Mark_R._Ashurst-McGee" class="mw-redirect" title="Mark R. Ashurst-McGee">Ashurst-McGee, Mark R.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Richard_L._Jensen" title="Richard L. Jensen">Jensen, Richard L.</a> (eds.). <i>Histories, Volume 1: Joseph Smith Histories, 1832–1844</i>. <a href="/wiki/The_Joseph_Smith_Papers" title="The Joseph Smith Papers">The Joseph Smith Papers</a>: Histories Series (Book 1 of 2). Salt Lake City: <a href="/wiki/The_Church_Historian%27s_Press" class="mw-redirect" title="The Church Historian&#39;s Press">The Church Historian's Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1606411964" title="Special:BookSources/978-1606411964"><bdi>978-1606411964</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Histories%2C+Volume+1%3A+Joseph+Smith+Histories%2C+1832%E2%80%931844&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.series=The+Joseph+Smith+Papers%3A+Histories+Series+%28Book+1+of+2%29&amp;rft.pub=The+Church+Historian%27s+Press&amp;rft.date=2012-03-31&amp;rft.isbn=978-1606411964&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.josephsmithpapers.org/articles/histories-volume-1-joseph-smith-histories-1832-1844">[7]</a>
<ul><li>Collection of six personal and church histories written, dictated, or closely supervised by Smith; including accounts of <a href="/wiki/First_Vision" title="First Vision">his first vision of Deity</a>, ministering of the <a href="/wiki/Angel_Moroni" title="Angel Moroni">angel Moroni</a>, discovery of the <a href="/wiki/Gold_plates" class="mw-redirect" title="Gold plates">gold plates</a> and translation of the <a href="/wiki/Book_of_Mormon" title="Book of Mormon">Book of Mormon</a>, <a href="/wiki/Priesthood_(Latter_Day_Saints)#History_of_the_priesthood_in_the_Latter_Day_Saint_tradition" title="Priesthood (Latter Day Saints)">bestowal of priesthood authority</a>, an account of the "<a href="/wiki/Missouri_Mormon_War" class="mw-redirect" title="Missouri Mormon War">Missouri Mormon War</a>", and Smith's original <a href="/wiki/Articles_of_Faith_(Latter_Day_Saints)" title="Articles of Faith (Latter Day Saints)">Articles of Faith</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMackayDirkmaatUnderwoodWoodford2013" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Michael_Hubbard_Mackay&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Michael Hubbard Mackay (page does not exist)">Mackay, Michael Hubbard</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Gerrit_J._Dirkmaat&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Gerrit J. Dirkmaat (page does not exist)">Dirkmaat, Gerrit J.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Grant_Underwood" title="Grant Underwood">Underwood, Grant</a>; <a href="/wiki/Robert_J._Woodford" title="Robert J. Woodford">Woodford, Robert J.</a>; <a href="/wiki/William_G._Hartley" title="William G. Hartley">Hartley, William G.</a>, eds. (8 November 2013). <i>Documents, Volume 1: July 1828-June 1831</i>. <a href="/wiki/The_Joseph_Smith_Papers" title="The Joseph Smith Papers">The Joseph Smith Papers</a>: Documents Series (Book 1 of 10). Salt Lake City: <a href="/wiki/The_Church_Historian%27s_Press" class="mw-redirect" title="The Church Historian&#39;s Press">The Church Historian's Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1609075774" title="Special:BookSources/978-1609075774"><bdi>978-1609075774</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Documents%2C+Volume+1%3A+July+1828-June+1831&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.series=The+Joseph+Smith+Papers%3A+Documents+Series+%28Book+1+of+10%29&amp;rft.pub=The+Church+Historian%27s+Press&amp;rft.date=2013-11-08&amp;rft.isbn=978-1609075774&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.josephsmithpapers.org/articles/documents-volume-1-july-1828-june-1831">[8]</a>
<ul><li>A collection including the first three years of what survives of Joseph Smith's papers, including letters sent and received, <a href="/wiki/Revelation_(Latter_Day_Saints)" class="mw-redirect" title="Revelation (Latter Day Saints)">revelations</a>, minutes of meetings, <a href="/wiki/Deed" title="Deed">deeds</a> and other financial papers, records of <a href="/wiki/Ecclesiastical" title="Ecclesiastical">ecclesiastical</a> administration; covering documentation of key events including the <a href="/wiki/Book_of_Mormon#Manuscripts" title="Book of Mormon">translation and publication of the Book of Mormon</a>, the <a href="/wiki/Church_of_Christ_(Latter_Day_Saints)" title="Church of Christ (Latter Day Saints)">establishment of a church</a>, and the <a href="/wiki/Missionary_(LDS_Church)" class="mw-redirect" title="Missionary (LDS Church)">mission</a> by <a href="/wiki/Oliver_Cowdery" title="Oliver Cowdery">Oliver Cowdery</a> and others to <a href="/wiki/Mormonism_in_the_19th_century#May" title="Mormonism in the 19th century">preach to American Indians on the western frontier of the United States</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFRoberts1930" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/B._H._Roberts" title="B. H. Roberts">Roberts, B. H.</a> (6 April 1930). <i><a href="/wiki/Comprehensive_History_of_The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints" title="Comprehensive History of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints">Comprehensive History of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints: Century I</a></i>. The <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a> and <a href="/wiki/Deseret_News_Press" class="mw-redirect" title="Deseret News Press">Deseret News Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0842504826" title="Special:BookSources/0842504826"><bdi>0842504826</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Comprehensive+History+of+The+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints%3A+Century+I&amp;rft.pub=The+LDS+Church+and+Deseret+News+Press&amp;rft.date=1930-04-06&amp;rft.isbn=0842504826&amp;rft.aulast=Roberts&amp;rft.aufirst=B.+H.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A six-volume history by a <a href="/wiki/General_authority" title="General authority">general authority</a> and <a href="/wiki/Assistant_Church_Historian" class="mw-redirect" title="Assistant Church Historian">Assistant Church Historian</a> of the <a href="/wiki/The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints" title="The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints">LDS Church</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFQuinn1994" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/D._Michael_Quinn" title="D. Michael Quinn">Quinn, D. Michael</a> (15 December 1994). <i>The Mormon Hierarchy: Origins of Power</i>. <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1560850566" title="Special:BookSources/1560850566"><bdi>1560850566</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Mormon+Hierarchy%3A+Origins+of+Power&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=1994-12-15&amp;rft.isbn=1560850566&amp;rft.aulast=Quinn&amp;rft.aufirst=D.+Michael&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>An examination of the first two decades of LDS history and the move from Joseph Smith's charismatic spontaneity, and the <a href="/wiki/Egalitarian" class="mw-redirect" title="Egalitarian">egalitarian</a> chaos of the early church, to Brigham Young's well-defined structure and the <a href="/wiki/Bureaucratization" class="mw-redirect" title="Bureaucratization">bureaucratization</a> of Mormonism.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFGrowSmith2017" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Matthew_Grow" title="Matthew Grow">Grow, Matthew J.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=R._Eric_Smith&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="R. Eric Smith (page does not exist)">Smith, R. Eric</a>, eds. (4 September 2017). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Council_of_Fifty:_What_the_Records_Reveal_about_Mormon_History&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Council of Fifty: What the Records Reveal about Mormon History (page does not exist)">The Council of Fifty: What the Records Reveal about Mormon History</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Religious_Studies_Center" title="Religious Studies Center">RSC BYU</a>, <a href="/wiki/Deseret_Book" class="mw-redirect" title="Deseret Book">Deseret Book</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1944394219" title="Special:BookSources/978-1944394219"><bdi>978-1944394219</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Council+of+Fifty%3A+What+the+Records+Reveal+about+Mormon+History&amp;rft.pub=RSC+BYU%2C+Deseret+Book&amp;rft.date=2017-09-04&amp;rft.isbn=978-1944394219&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A compilation of fifteen brief essays on new insights found in the previously unavailable minutes of the <a href="/wiki/Council_of_Fifty" title="Council of Fifty">Council of Fifty</a>; historians who analyze the records include <a href="/wiki/Richard_Lyman_Bushman" class="mw-redirect" title="Richard Lyman Bushman">Richard Lyman Bushman</a>, <a href="/wiki/Richard_E._Turley_Jr." title="Richard E. Turley Jr.">Richard E. Turley Jr.</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Spencer_W._McBride&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Spencer W. McBride (page does not exist)">Spencer W. McBride</a>, <a href="/wiki/Patrick_Q._Mason" title="Patrick Q. Mason">Patrick Q. Mason</a>, <a href="/wiki/Benjamin_E._Park" class="mw-redirect" title="Benjamin E. Park">Benjamin E. Park</a>, <a href="/wiki/Nathan_B._Oman" class="mw-redirect" title="Nathan B. Oman">Nathan B. Oman</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Gerrit_J._Dirkmaat&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Gerrit J. Dirkmaat (page does not exist)">Gerrit J. Dirkmaat</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=R._Eric_Smith&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="R. Eric Smith (page does not exist)">R. Eric Smith</a>, <a href="/wiki/Matthew_J._Grow" class="mw-redirect" title="Matthew J. Grow">Matthew J. Grow</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Marilyn_Bradford&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Marilyn Bradford (page does not exist)">Marilyn Bradford</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Jeffrey_D._Mahas&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Jeffrey D. Mahas (page does not exist)">Jeffrey D. Mahas</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Matthew_C._Godfrey&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Matthew C. Godfrey (page does not exist)">Matthew C. Godfrey</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Christopher_James_Blythe&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Christopher James Blythe (page does not exist)">Christopher James Blythe</a>, <a href="/wiki/Richard_E._Bennett" title="Richard E. Bennett">Richard E. Bennett</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Jedediah_S._Rogers&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Jedediah S. Rogers (page does not exist)">Jedediah S. Rogers</a>, and <a href="/wiki/W._Paul_Reeve" title="W. Paul Reeve">W. Paul Reeve</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFHunter2012" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=J._Michael_Hunter&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="J. Michael Hunter (page does not exist)">Hunter, J. Michael</a>, ed. (5 December 2012). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=ZD8vhVCx03wC"><i>Mormons and Popular Culture: The Global Influence of an American Phenomenon</i></a>. <a href="/wiki/ABC-CLIO" class="mw-redirect" title="ABC-CLIO">ABC-CLIO</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0313391675" title="Special:BookSources/978-0313391675"><bdi>978-0313391675</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormons+and+Popular+Culture%3A+The+Global+Influence+of+an+American+Phenomenon&amp;rft.pub=ABC-CLIO&amp;rft.date=2012-12-05&amp;rft.isbn=978-0313391675&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DZD8vhVCx03wC&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A collection of essays on influential Mormons in <a href="/wiki/American_popular_culture" class="mw-redirect" title="American popular culture">American popular culture</a>; in cinema, television, drama, theater, and music; with specific chapters on <a href="/wiki/Disney" class="mw-redirect" title="Disney">Disney</a>, <a href="/wiki/Philo_T._Farnsworth" class="mw-redirect" title="Philo T. Farnsworth">Philo T. Farnsworth</a>, the <a href="/wiki/Hill_Cumorah_Pageant" title="Hill Cumorah Pageant">Hill Cumorah Pageant</a>, the <a href="/wiki/Mormon_Tabernacle_Choir" class="mw-redirect" title="Mormon Tabernacle Choir">Mormon Tabernacle Choir</a>, <a href="/wiki/Rose_Marie_Reid" title="Rose Marie Reid">Rose Marie Reid</a>, and a selection of <a href="/wiki/List_of_Latter_Day_Saints#Media_and_Entertainment_Figures" title="List of Latter Day Saints">Mormon actors</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFNibley1987" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Hugh_Nibley" title="Hugh Nibley">Nibley, Hugh</a> (1 November 1987). <a href="/wiki/Todd_Compton" title="Todd Compton">Compton, Todd</a>; <a href="/wiki/Stephen_D._Ricks" title="Stephen D. Ricks">Ricks, Stephen D.</a> (eds.). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Mormonism_and_Early_Christianity&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Mormonism and Early Christianity (page does not exist)">Mormonism and Early Christianity</a></i>. The Collected Works of Hugh Nibley. Salt Lake City: <a href="/wiki/Deseret_Book" class="mw-redirect" title="Deseret Book">Deseret Book</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-87579-127-1" title="Special:BookSources/0-87579-127-1"><bdi>0-87579-127-1</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormonism+and+Early+Christianity&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.series=The+Collected+Works+of+Hugh+Nibley&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Book&amp;rft.date=1987-11-01&amp;rft.isbn=0-87579-127-1&amp;rft.aulast=Nibley&amp;rft.aufirst=Hugh&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://publications.mi.byu.edu/book/mormonism-and-early-christianity/">[9]</a>
<ul><li>A collection of essays about <a href="/wiki/Christian_primitivism" class="mw-redirect" title="Christian primitivism">primitive Christianity</a>, with particular focus on the connection between the practices and the doctrines of the early Church and the LDS Church.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBatesSmith2017" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Irene_M._Bates&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Irene M. Bates (page does not exist)">Bates, Irene M.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=E._Gary_Smith&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="E. Gary Smith (page does not exist)">Smith, E. Gary</a> (2017) [1996]. <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Lost_Legacy:_The_Mormon_Office_of_Presiding_Patriarch&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Lost Legacy: The Mormon Office of Presiding Patriarch (page does not exist)">Lost Legacy: The Mormon Office of Presiding Patriarch</a></i> (expanded&#160;ed.). <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0252083099" title="Special:BookSources/978-0252083099"><bdi>978-0252083099</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Lost+Legacy%3A+The+Mormon+Office+of+Presiding+Patriarch&amp;rft.edition=expanded&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=2017&amp;rft.isbn=978-0252083099&amp;rft.aulast=Bates&amp;rft.aufirst=Irene+M.&amp;rft.au=Smith%2C+E.+Gary&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A study of the office of <a href="/wiki/Presiding_Patriarch" title="Presiding Patriarch">Presiding Patriarch</a> in the LDS Church; chronicling its history.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Mormon_studies">Mormon studies</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Mormon studies"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r1033289096">.mw-parser-output .hatnote{font-style:italic}.mw-parser-output div.hatnote{padding-left:1.6em;margin-bottom:0.5em}.mw-parser-output .hatnote i{font-style:normal}.mw-parser-output .hatnote+link+.hatnote{margin-top:-0.5em}</style><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Further information: <a href="/wiki/Mormon_studies" title="Mormon studies">Mormon studies</a></div>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFQuinn1992" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/D._Michael_Quinn" title="D. Michael Quinn">Quinn, D. Michael</a>, ed. (15 January 1992). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_New_Mormon_History&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The New Mormon History (page does not exist)">The New Mormon History</a>: Revisionist Essays on the Mormon Past</i>. <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1560850116" title="Special:BookSources/1560850116"><bdi>1560850116</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+New+Mormon+History%3A+Revisionist+Essays+on+the+Mormon+Past&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=1992-01-15&amp;rft.isbn=1560850116&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://signaturebookslibrary.org/?p=745">[10]</a>
<ul><li>A collection of 15 essays taking a new look at events in Mormon history— such as the significance of the <a href="/wiki/First_Vision" title="First Vision">First Vision</a>, the <a href="/wiki/History_of_Nauvoo,_Illinois#Nauvoo_founded_by_the_Latter_Day_Saints" title="History of Nauvoo, Illinois">Nauvoo period</a>, the <a href="/wiki/Miracle_of_the_gulls" title="Miracle of the gulls">miracle of the gulls</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Mormon_polygamy" class="mw-redirect" title="Mormon polygamy">Mormon polygamy</a>; contributors include <a href="/wiki/Leonard_J._Arrington" title="Leonard J. Arrington">Leonard J. Arrington</a>, <a href="/wiki/Mario_S._De_Pillis" class="mw-redirect" title="Mario S. De Pillis">Mario S. De Pillis</a>, <a href="/wiki/James_B._Allen_(historian)" title="James B. Allen (historian)">James B. Allen</a>, <a href="/wiki/Jan_Shipps" title="Jan Shipps">Jan Shipps</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Robert_Bruce_Flanders&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Robert Bruce Flanders (page does not exist)">Robert Bruce Flanders</a>, <a href="/wiki/Linda_King_Newell" title="Linda King Newell">Linda King Newell</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Dean_May_(historian)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Dean May (historian) (page does not exist)">Dean May</a>, <a href="/wiki/William_G._Hartley" title="William G. Hartley">William G. Hartley</a>, <a href="/wiki/Maureen_Ursenbach_Beecher" class="mw-redirect" title="Maureen Ursenbach Beecher">Maureen Ursenbach Beecher</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Stanley_S._Ivins&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Stanley S. Ivins (page does not exist)">Stanley S. Ivins</a>, <a href="/wiki/Eugene_E._Campbell" title="Eugene E. Campbell">Eugene E. Campbell</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Bruce_L._Campbell&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Bruce L. Campbell (page does not exist)">Bruce L. Campbell</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Kenneth_L._Cannon_II&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Kenneth L. Cannon II (page does not exist)">Kenneth L. Cannon II</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Klaus_J._Hansen&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Klaus J. Hansen (page does not exist)">Klaus J. Hansen</a>, <a href="/wiki/Thomas_G._Alexander" title="Thomas G. Alexander">Thomas G. Alexander</a>, <a href="/wiki/Ronald_W._Walker" title="Ronald W. Walker">Ronald W. Walker</a>, and <a href="/wiki/B._H._Roberts" title="B. H. Roberts">B. H. Roberts</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFWalkerWhittakerAllen2001" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Ronald_W._Walker" title="Ronald W. Walker">Walker, Ronald W.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=David_J._Whittaker&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="David J. Whittaker (page does not exist)">Whittaker, David J.</a>; <a href="/wiki/James_B._Allen_(historian)" title="James B. Allen (historian)">Allen, James B.</a> (18 April 2001). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/mormonhistory0000walk"><i>Mormon History</i></a>. Urbana, IL: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0252026195" title="Special:BookSources/0252026195"><bdi>0252026195</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormon+History&amp;rft.place=Urbana%2C+IL&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=2001-04-18&amp;rft.isbn=0252026195&amp;rft.aulast=Walker&amp;rft.aufirst=Ronald+W.&amp;rft.au=Whittaker%2C+David+J.&amp;rft.au=Allen%2C+James+B.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fmormonhistory0000walk&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=-iSVA0KRs4MC">[11]</a>
<ul><li>A <a href="/wiki/Historiographical" class="mw-redirect" title="Historiographical">historiographical</a> survey of how the writing of Mormon history has evolved since the establishment of the church; a companion volume to the bibliography, <i>Studies in Mormon History, 1830–1997</i>; includes a contribution by <a href="/wiki/Armand_Mauss" title="Armand Mauss">Armand Mauss</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFAllenWalkerWhittaker2000" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/James_B._Allen_(historian)" title="James B. Allen (historian)">Allen, James B.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Ronald_W._Walker" title="Ronald W. Walker">Walker, Ronald W.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=David_J._Whittaker&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="David J. Whittaker (page does not exist)">Whittaker, David</a> (13 January 2000). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Studies_in_Mormon_History&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Studies in Mormon History (page does not exist)">Studies in Mormon History</a>, 1830–1997: An Indexed Bibliography</i>. Urbana: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0252025652" title="Special:BookSources/0252025652"><bdi>0252025652</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Studies+in+Mormon+History%2C+1830%E2%80%931997%3A+An+Indexed+Bibliography&amp;rft.place=Urbana&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=2000-01-13&amp;rft.isbn=0252025652&amp;rft.aulast=Allen&amp;rft.aufirst=James+B.&amp;rft.au=Walker%2C+Ronald+W.&amp;rft.au=Whittaker%2C+David&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A <a href="/wiki/Bibliography" title="Bibliography">bibliography</a> on historical literature about the Mormons; listing books, articles, theses, and dissertations on the history of the LDS Church.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFArrington2006" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Leonard_J._Arrington" title="Leonard J. Arrington">Arrington, Leonard J.</a> (15 November 2006). <a href="/wiki/Reid_L._Neilson" title="Reid L. Neilson">Neilson, Reid L.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Ronald_W._Walker" title="Ronald W. Walker">Walker, Ronald W.</a> (eds.). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Reflections_of_a_Mormon_Historian&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Reflections of a Mormon Historian (page does not exist)">Reflections of a Mormon Historian</a>: Leonard J. Arrington on the New Mormon History</i>. <a href="/wiki/Norman,_OK" class="mw-redirect" title="Norman, OK">Norman, OK</a>: <a href="/wiki/Arthur_H._Clark_Company" title="Arthur H. Clark Company">Arthur H. Clark Company</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0870623486" title="Special:BookSources/0870623486"><bdi>0870623486</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Reflections+of+a+Mormon+Historian%3A+Leonard+J.+Arrington+on+the+New+Mormon+History&amp;rft.place=Norman%2C+OK&amp;rft.pub=Arthur+H.+Clark+Company&amp;rft.date=2006-11-15&amp;rft.isbn=0870623486&amp;rft.aulast=Arrington&amp;rft.aufirst=Leonard+J.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Compilation of fourteen essays on history and the Mormons by Arrington, the first professional historian to serve as <a href="/wiki/Church_Historian" class="mw-redirect" title="Church Historian">Church Historian</a>, and a prominent founder of the <a href="/wiki/New_Mormon_history" title="New Mormon history">New Mormon history</a>; includes a biographical sketch by Walker, a bibliography of his works and speeches by Whitaker, and a personal tribute by his daughter, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Susan_Arrington_Madsen&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Susan Arrington Madsen (page does not exist)">Susan Arrington Madsen</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFVogel1988" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Dan_Vogel" title="Dan Vogel">Vogel, Dan</a> (1 February 1988). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Religious_Seekers_and_the_Advent_of_Mormonism&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Religious Seekers and the Advent of Mormonism (page does not exist)">Religious Seekers and the Advent of Mormonism</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0941214648" title="Special:BookSources/0941214648"><bdi>0941214648</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Religious+Seekers+and+the+Advent+of+Mormonism&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=1988-02-01&amp;rft.isbn=0941214648&amp;rft.aulast=Vogel&amp;rft.aufirst=Dan&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://signaturebookslibrary.org/religious-seekers/">[12]</a>
<ul><li>A study of the early history of the Church, introducing readers to groups and individuals who seem to have anticipated its kind of <a href="/wiki/Restorationism" title="Restorationism">religious primitivism</a>, especially the <a href="/wiki/Seekers" title="Seekers">Seekers</a> (who resembled Mormonism's concept of authority during its formative years).</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBowman2012" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Matthew_Bowman_(author)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Matthew Bowman (author) (page does not exist)">Bowman, Matthew</a> (28 August 2012). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Mormon_People&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Mormon People (page does not exist)">The Mormon People</a>: The Making of an American Faith</i>. <a href="/wiki/Random_House_Trade_Paperbacks" class="mw-redirect" title="Random House Trade Paperbacks">Random House Trade Paperbacks</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0812983364" title="Special:BookSources/978-0812983364"><bdi>978-0812983364</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Mormon+People%3A+The+Making+of+an+American+Faith&amp;rft.pub=Random+House+Trade+Paperbacks&amp;rft.date=2012-08-28&amp;rft.isbn=978-0812983364&amp;rft.aulast=Bowman&amp;rft.aufirst=Matthew&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/mormonpeoplemaki00bowm_0">[13]</a>
<ul><li>Survey of Mormon history and doctrine; recounting the church's origins, explaining the evolution of the Mormon vision, and its place in American public life.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFTaysom2011" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Stephen_C._Taysom&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Stephen C. Taysom (page does not exist)">Taysom, Stephen C.</a>, ed. (15 June 2011). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Dimensions_of_Faith&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Dimensions of Faith (page does not exist)">Dimensions of Faith</a>: A Mormon Studies Reader</i>. Salt Lake City: <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1560852124" title="Special:BookSources/978-1560852124"><bdi>978-1560852124</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Dimensions+of+Faith%3A+A+Mormon+Studies+Reader&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=2011-06-15&amp;rft.isbn=978-1560852124&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Seventeen articles on a range of topics including <a href="/wiki/David_O._McKay" title="David O. McKay">David O. McKay</a>'s personality, comparisons of <a href="/wiki/John_Humphrey_Noyes" title="John Humphrey Noyes">John Humphrey Noyes</a> with Joseph Smith, <a href="/wiki/Wilford_Woodruff" title="Wilford Woodruff">Wilford Woodruff</a>'s vision of the signers of the <a href="/wiki/United_States_Declaration_of_Independence" title="United States Declaration of Independence">Declaration of Independence</a>, a "<a href="/wiki/David_W._Patten#Story_of_meeting_Cain" title="David W. Patten">Mormon Bigfoot</a>", Mormon ritual healing, the campaign to suppress <a href="/w/index.php?title=Anti-Mormon_motion_pictures&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Anti-Mormon motion pictures (page does not exist)">anti-Mormon motion pictures</a>, Mormon representations of <a href="/wiki/Judaism" title="Judaism">Judaism</a>, Mormon women's fiction, <a href="/wiki/Edward_Tullidge" title="Edward Tullidge">Edward Tullidge</a> and the women of Mormondom; contributors include <a href="/wiki/Kathleen_Flake" title="Kathleen Flake">Kathleen Flake</a>, <a href="/wiki/Newell_Bringhurst" class="mw-redirect" title="Newell Bringhurst">Newell Bringhurst</a>, <a href="/wiki/Claudia_Bushman" class="mw-redirect" title="Claudia Bushman">Claudia Bushman</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Douglas_Davies" title="Douglas Davies">Douglas Davies</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFNewellMason2013" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Quincy_D._Newell" title="Quincy D. Newell">Newell, Quincy D.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Eric_F._Mason&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Eric F. Mason (page does not exist)">Mason, Eric Farrel</a>, eds. (14 March 2013). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=New_Perspectives_in_Mormon_Studies&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="New Perspectives in Mormon Studies (page does not exist)">New Perspectives in Mormon Studies</a>: Creating and Crossing Boundaries</i>. <a href="/wiki/Norman,_Oklahoma" title="Norman, Oklahoma">Norman, Oklahoma</a>: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Oklahoma_Press" title="University of Oklahoma Press">University of Oklahoma Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0806143132" title="Special:BookSources/978-0806143132"><bdi>978-0806143132</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=New+Perspectives+in+Mormon+Studies%3A+Creating+and+Crossing+Boundaries&amp;rft.place=Norman%2C+Oklahoma&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Oklahoma+Press&amp;rft.date=2013-03-14&amp;rft.isbn=978-0806143132&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=QtYLXM7Uhx4C">[14]</a>
<ul><li>A collection of essays with topics include Joseph Smith's <a href="/wiki/Political_economy" title="Political economy">political economy</a>, Jane James's place in LDS history, the young Joseph Smith and <a href="/wiki/Presbyterianism" title="Presbyterianism">Presbyterianism</a>, the relation of <a href="/wiki/Pentecostalism" title="Pentecostalism">Pentecostalism</a> to Mormonism in the case of <a href="/wiki/John_Alexander_Dowie" title="John Alexander Dowie">John Alexander Dowie</a>, some comparative observations of <a href="/wiki/Islam_and_Mormonism" title="Islam and Mormonism">Islam and Mormonism</a>, the <a href="/w/index.php?title=Ex-Mormons_For_Jesus&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Ex-Mormons For Jesus (page does not exist)">Ex-Mormons For Jesus</a>/<a href="/w/index.php?title=Saints_Alive_In_Jesus&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Saints Alive In Jesus (page does not exist)">Saints Alive In Jesus</a>, who <a href="/wiki/Elijah#Elijah_and_Elias_in_the_LDS_Church" title="Elijah">Elias</a> is, and LDS engagement with <a href="/wiki/Dead_Sea_Scrolls" title="Dead Sea Scrolls">Dead Sea Scrolls</a> scholarship; contributors include <a href="/w/index.php?title=David_Charles_Gore&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="David Charles Gore (page does not exist)">David Charles Gore</a>, <a href="/wiki/Quincy_D._Newell" title="Quincy D. Newell">Quincy D. Newell</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=John_Matzko&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="John Matzko (page does not exist)">John Matzko</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=D._William_Faupel&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="D. William Faupel (page does not exist)">D. William Faupel</a>, <a href="/wiki/Grant_Underwood" title="Grant Underwood">Grant Underwood</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Sara_M._Patterson&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Sara M. Patterson (page does not exist)">Sara M. Patterson</a>, <a href="/wiki/Stevan_Davies" title="Stevan Davies">Stevan Davies</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Eric_F._Mason&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Eric F. Mason (page does not exist)">Eric F. Mason</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Richard_Lyman_Bushman" class="mw-redirect" title="Richard Lyman Bushman">Richard Lyman Bushman</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFHill1989" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Marvin_S._Hill" title="Marvin S. Hill">Hill, Marvin S.</a> (1 June 1989). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Quest_for_Refuge&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Quest for Refuge (page does not exist)">Quest for Refuge</a>: The Mormon Flight from American Pluralism</i>. <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0941214702" title="Special:BookSources/0941214702"><bdi>0941214702</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Quest+for+Refuge%3A+The+Mormon+Flight+from+American+Pluralism&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=1989-06-01&amp;rft.isbn=0941214702&amp;rft.aulast=Hill&amp;rft.aufirst=Marvin+S.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://signaturebookslibrary.org/quest-for-refuge/">[15]</a>
<ul><li>A history of the development of Mormon doctrines and the attempt to develop a communal utopia under a theocratic government during the 1830s and early 1840s; an interpretation of the LDS movement as a reaction to the diminishing role of religion in an emerging democratic, competitive, and increasingly secular world.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Regional_studies">Regional studies</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Regional studies"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Britain">Britain</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: Britain"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFAllenEsplinWhittaker1992" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/James_B._Allen_(historian)" title="James B. Allen (historian)">Allen, James B.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Ron_Esplin" title="Ron Esplin">Esplin, Ronald K.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=David_J._Whittaker&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="David J. Whittaker (page does not exist)">Whittaker, David J.</a> (1992). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Men_with_a_Mission&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Men with a Mission (page does not exist)">Men with a Mission</a>: The Quorum of the Twelve Apostles in the British Isles, 1837–1841</i>. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Deseret_Book" class="mw-redirect" title="Deseret Book">Deseret Book</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1590389980" title="Special:BookSources/1590389980"><bdi>1590389980</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Men+with+a+Mission%3A+The+Quorum+of+the+Twelve+Apostles+in+the+British+Isles%2C+1837%E2%80%931841&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Book&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.isbn=1590389980&amp;rft.aulast=Allen&amp;rft.aufirst=James+B.&amp;rft.au=Esplin%2C+Ronald+K.&amp;rft.au=Whittaker%2C+David+J.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> Republished on 13 May 2009.
<ul><li>History of the <a href="/wiki/Quorum_of_the_Twelve" title="Quorum of the Twelve">Quorum of the Twelve</a>'s <a href="/wiki/The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints_in_England#1837-1841:_First_Mormon_missionaries_reach_England" title="The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints in England">mission to the United Kingdom</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFJensenThorp1989" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Richard_L._Jensen" title="Richard L. Jensen">Jensen, Richard L.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Malcolm_R._Thorp&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Malcolm R. Thorp (page does not exist)">Thorp, Malcolm R.</a>, eds. (1989). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Mormons_in_Early_Victorian_Britain&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Mormons in Early Victorian Britain (page does not exist)">Mormons in Early Victorian Britain</a></i>. Publications in Mormon Studies, Volume 4. Salt Lake City: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Utah_Press" title="University of Utah Press">University of Utah Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0874803225" title="Special:BookSources/0874803225"><bdi>0874803225</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormons+in+Early+Victorian+Britain&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.series=Publications+in+Mormon+Studies%2C+Volume+4&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Utah+Press&amp;rft.date=1989&amp;rft.isbn=0874803225&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A collection of 16 biographical, local, background, and general articles on <a href="/wiki/The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints_in_the_United_Kingdom" title="The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints in the United Kingdom">Mormonism in the British Isles</a>, emphasizing the period of 1840 to the late 1850s; written by a mix historians of British history, and of American history.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Denmark">Denmark</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Denmark"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFAllen2017" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Julie_K._Allen&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Julie K. Allen (page does not exist)">Allen, Julie K.</a> (30 May 2017). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Danish_But_Not_Lutheran&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Danish But Not Lutheran (page does not exist)">Danish But Not Lutheran</a>: The Impact of Mormonism on Danish Cultural Identity, 1850-1920</i>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_Utah_Press" title="University of Utah Press">University of Utah Press</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Danish+But+Not+Lutheran%3A+The+Impact+of+Mormonism+on+Danish+Cultural+Identity%2C+1850-1920&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Utah+Press&amp;rft.date=2017-05-30&amp;rft.aulast=Allen&amp;rft.aufirst=Julie+K.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Story of the social and cultural ramifications of <a href="/wiki/The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints_in_Denmark" title="The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints in Denmark">Danish conversions to Mormonism</a>; explores the range of Danish public reactions over a seventy-year period.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Italy">Italy</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Italy"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFTorontoDurstelerHomer2017" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/James_A._Toronto" title="James A. Toronto">Toronto, James A.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Eric_R._Dursteler" title="Eric R. Dursteler">Dursteler, Eric R.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Michael_W._Homer&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Michael W. Homer (page does not exist)">Homer, Michael W.</a> (2 January 2017). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Mormons_in_the_Piazza&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Mormons in the Piazza (page does not exist)">Mormons in the Piazza</a>: History of the Latter-Day Saints in Italy</i>. <a href="/wiki/BYU_Religious_Studies_Center" class="mw-redirect" title="BYU Religious Studies Center">BYU Religious Studies Center</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1944394103" title="Special:BookSources/978-1944394103"><bdi>978-1944394103</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormons+in+the+Piazza%3A+History+of+the+Latter-Day+Saints+in+Italy&amp;rft.pub=BYU+Religious+Studies+Center&amp;rft.date=2017-01-02&amp;rft.isbn=978-1944394103&amp;rft.aulast=Toronto&amp;rft.aufirst=James+A.&amp;rft.au=Dursteler%2C+Eric+R.&amp;rft.au=Homer%2C+Michael+W.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>An account and analysis of the people, events, and issues relevant to <a href="/wiki/The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints_in_Italy" title="The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints in Italy">LDS missionary efforts in Italy</a>.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Pacific_Islands">Pacific Islands</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Pacific Islands"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFUnderwood2000" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Grant_Underwood" title="Grant Underwood">Underwood, Grant</a>, ed. (1 December 2000). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Voyages_of_Faith&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Voyages of Faith (page does not exist)">Voyages of Faith</a>: Explorations in Mormon Pacific History</i>. Studies in Latter-day Saint History series (Book 2). Provo, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young_University" title="Brigham Young University">Brigham Young University</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0842524800" title="Special:BookSources/0842524800"><bdi>0842524800</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Voyages+of+Faith%3A+Explorations+in+Mormon+Pacific+History&amp;rft.place=Provo%2C+Utah&amp;rft.series=Studies+in+Latter-day+Saint+History+series+%28Book+2%29&amp;rft.pub=Brigham+Young+University&amp;rft.date=2000-12-01&amp;rft.isbn=0842524800&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A compilation of scholarly research, personal reminiscences, and faith stories of <a href="/wiki/Mormonism_and_Pacific_Islanders" class="mw-redirect" title="Mormonism and Pacific Islanders">LDS Church missionary work among the Pacific Islands</a> from 1843 onward; including articles on the <a href="/wiki/The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints" title="The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints">work in French Polynesia</a> and <a href="/wiki/The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints_in_Tonga" title="The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints in Tonga">Tonga</a>, <a href="/wiki/The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints_in_New_Zealand" title="The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints in New Zealand">influence on Maori religious identity</a>, the founding of <a href="/wiki/Iosepa" class="mw-redirect" title="Iosepa">Iosepa</a>, <a href="/wiki/The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints_in_Hawaii" title="The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints in Hawaii">a rich history in Hawaii</a>, the site selection of the <a href="/wiki/Church_College_of_Hawai%27i" class="mw-redirect" title="Church College of Hawai&#39;i">Church College of Hawai'i</a> campus, the art and architecture of the <a href="/wiki/Laie_Hawaii_Temple" title="Laie Hawaii Temple">Laie Hawaii Temple</a> (and a purported <a href="/wiki/Attack_on_Pearl_Harbor" title="Attack on Pearl Harbor">7 December 1941 attack</a> attempt), and reflections on the <a href="/wiki/Polynesian_Cultural_Center" title="Polynesian Cultural Center">Polynesian Cultural Center</a>).</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFUnderwood2005" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Grant_Underwood" title="Grant Underwood">Underwood, Grant</a>, ed. (2005). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Pioneers_in_the_Pacific&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Pioneers in the Pacific (page does not exist)">Pioneers in the Pacific</a>: Memory, History, and Cultural Identity Among the Latter-Day Saints</i>. Provo, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Religious_Studies_Center" title="Religious Studies Center">Religious Studies Center, BYU</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0842526161" title="Special:BookSources/0842526161"><bdi>0842526161</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Pioneers+in+the+Pacific%3A+Memory%2C+History%2C+and+Cultural+Identity+Among+the+Latter-Day+Saints&amp;rft.place=Provo%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Religious+Studies+Center%2C+BYU&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.isbn=0842526161&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://contentdm.lib.byu.edu/cdm/ref/collection/rsc/id/15344">[16]</a>
<ul><li>Collection of articles and remembrances on the history of <a href="/wiki/Mormonism_and_Pacific_Islanders" class="mw-redirect" title="Mormonism and Pacific Islanders">the LDS Church throughout the Pacific Islands</a> up to the year 2004; including an address by <a href="/wiki/Gordon_B._Hinckley" title="Gordon B. Hinckley">Gordon B. Hinckley</a>, an article on <a href="/wiki/Matthew_Cowley" title="Matthew Cowley">Matthew Cowley</a>, the cultural foundations of the <a href="/wiki/Polynesian_Cultural_Center" title="Polynesian Cultural Center">Polynesian Cultural Center</a>, <a href="/wiki/George_Q._Cannon" title="George Q. Cannon">George Q. Cannon</a>'s mission in Hawai'i, and <a href="/wiki/David_O._McKay" title="David O. McKay">David O. McKay</a>'s 1921 trip around the Pacific.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Japan">Japan</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Japan"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFNeilson2010" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Reid_L._Neilson" title="Reid L. Neilson">Neilson, Reid Larkin</a> (2010). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Early_Mormon_Missionary_Activities_in_Japan,_1901-1924&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Early Mormon Missionary Activities in Japan, 1901-1924 (page does not exist)">Early Mormon Missionary Activities in Japan, 1901-1924</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_Utah_Press" title="University of Utah Press">University of Utah Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780874809893" title="Special:BookSources/9780874809893"><bdi>9780874809893</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Early+Mormon+Missionary+Activities+in+Japan%2C+1901-1924&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Utah+Press&amp;rft.date=2010&amp;rft.isbn=9780874809893&amp;rft.aulast=Neilson&amp;rft.aufirst=Reid+Larkin&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Study of the early <a href="/wiki/The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints_in_Japan#History_LDS_Missionary_efforts_in_Japan" title="The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints in Japan">history LDS Missionary efforts in Japan</a>; the challenges of adapting their message to the cultures encountered in East Asia.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Korea">Korea</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Korea"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPalmerPalmer1995" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Spencer_J._Palmer" title="Spencer J. Palmer">Palmer, Spencer J.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Shirley_H._Palmer&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Shirley H. Palmer (page does not exist)">Palmer, Shirley H.</a>, eds. (1995). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Korean_Saints&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Korean Saints (page does not exist)">The Korean Saints</a>: Personal Stories of Trial and Triumph, 1950–1980</i>. <a href="/wiki/Provo,_Utah" title="Provo, Utah">Provo, Utah</a>: <a href="/wiki/BYU_Religious_Education" title="BYU Religious Education">Religious Education, Brigham Young University</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0875798888" title="Special:BookSources/0875798888"><bdi>0875798888</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Korean+Saints%3A+Personal+Stories+of+Trial+and+Triumph%2C+1950%E2%80%931980&amp;rft.place=Provo%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Religious+Education%2C+Brigham+Young+University&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.isbn=0875798888&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Collection of essays about <a href="/wiki/The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints_in_South_Korea" title="The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints in South Korea">the LDS Church in Korea</a>.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="American_South"><a href="/wiki/American_South" class="mw-redirect" title="American South">American South</a></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: American South"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMason2011" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Patrick_Q._Mason" title="Patrick Q. Mason">Mason, Patrick Q.</a> (16 February 2011). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Mormon_Menace&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Mormon Menace (page does not exist)">The Mormon Menace</a>: Violence and Anti-Mormonism in the Postbellum South</i>. <a href="/wiki/Oxford_University_Press" title="Oxford University Press">Oxford University Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0199740024" title="Special:BookSources/978-0199740024"><bdi>978-0199740024</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Mormon+Menace%3A+Violence+and+Anti-Mormonism+in+the+Postbellum+South&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2011-02-16&amp;rft.isbn=978-0199740024&amp;rft.aulast=Mason&amp;rft.aufirst=Patrick+Q.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=bPr_gAiM9tEC">[17]</a>
<ul><li>History of late nineteenth century <a href="/wiki/Anti-Mormonism" title="Anti-Mormonism">Anti-Mormonism</a> in the <a href="/wiki/American_South" class="mw-redirect" title="American South">American South</a>; which sometimes rose to the level of <a href="/wiki/Vigilantism" title="Vigilantism">vigilante violence</a>.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Sacred_works">Sacred works</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: Sacred works"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="The_Book_of_Mormon">The Book of Mormon</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: The Book of Mormon"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1033289096"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Further information: <a href="/wiki/Origin_of_the_Book_of_Mormon" title="Origin of the Book of Mormon">Origin of the Book of Mormon</a></div>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFHardy2005" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Grant_Hardy" title="Grant Hardy">Hardy, Grant</a>, ed. (10 August 2005). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Book_of_Mormon:_A_Reader%27s_Edition&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Book of Mormon: A Reader&#39;s Edition (page does not exist)">The Book of Mormon: A Reader's Edition</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/025207341X" title="Special:BookSources/025207341X"><bdi>025207341X</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Book+of+Mormon%3A+A+Reader%27s+Edition&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=2005-08-10&amp;rft.isbn=025207341X&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=wbSqttrggZIC">[18]</a>
<ul><li>A reader-friendly version reformating the complete, unchanged 1920 text in the manner of modern translations of the Bible, with paragraphs, quotations marks, poetic forms, topical headings, multichapter headings, indention of quoted documents, italicized reworkings of biblical prophecies, and minimized verse numbers; also featuring a hypothetical map based on internal references, an essay on Book of Mormon poetry, a full glossary of names, <a href="/wiki/Genealogical" class="mw-redirect" title="Genealogical">genealogical charts</a>, a basic bibliography of Mormon and non-Mormon scholarship, a chronology of the translation, eyewitness accounts of <a href="/wiki/Golden_plates" title="Golden plates">the gold plates</a>, and information regarding the <a href="/wiki/Lost_116_pages" title="Lost 116 pages">lost 116 pages</a> and significant changes in the text.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFHardy2010" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Grant_Hardy" title="Grant Hardy">Hardy, Grant</a> (7 April 2010). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Understanding_the_Book_of_Mormon&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Understanding the Book of Mormon (page does not exist)">Understanding the Book of Mormon</a>: A Reader's Guide</i>. <a href="/wiki/Oxford_University_Press" title="Oxford University Press">Oxford University Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0199731701" title="Special:BookSources/978-0199731701"><bdi>978-0199731701</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Understanding+the+Book+of+Mormon%3A+A+Reader%27s+Guide&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2010-04-07&amp;rft.isbn=978-0199731701&amp;rft.aulast=Hardy&amp;rft.aufirst=Grant&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=xa2NZBVldBEC">[19]</a>
<ul><li>An analysis of the work's narrative structure; takes readers through its characters, events, and ideas, as it explores the story and its messages; seeks to reconcile believing and nonbelieving readings by offering a literary approach.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFNyman1991" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Monte_S._Nyman" title="Monte S. Nyman">Nyman, Monte S.</a> (1 September 1991). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Most_Correct_Book&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Most Correct Book (page does not exist)">The Most Correct Book</a>: Why the Book of Mormon is the Keystone Scripture</i>. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Bookcraft" title="Bookcraft">Bookcraft</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/088494798X" title="Special:BookSources/088494798X"><bdi>088494798X</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Most+Correct+Book%3A+Why+the+Book+of+Mormon+is+the+Keystone+Scripture&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Bookcraft&amp;rft.date=1991-09-01&amp;rft.isbn=088494798X&amp;rft.aulast=Nyman&amp;rft.aufirst=Monte+S.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Mostly written with a beginner in mind; it makes a case for Joseph Smith's description of the Book of Mormon as "the most correct of any book on earth, and the keystone of our religion," and that "a man would get nearer to God by abiding by its precepts, than by any other book."<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Others">Others</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15" title="Edit section: Others"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFRosenvallRosenvall2017" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Lynn_A._Rosenvall&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Lynn A. Rosenvall (page does not exist)">Rosenvall, Lynn A.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=David_L._Rosenvall&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="David L. Rosenvall (page does not exist)">Rosenvall, David L.</a> (24 November 2017). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=A_New_Approach_to_Studying_the_Covenants_of_Our_Fathers&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="A New Approach to Studying the Covenants of Our Fathers (page does not exist)">A New Approach to Studying the Covenants of Our Fathers</a>: A Harmony of Genesis, Moses and Abraham</i>. <a href="/w/index.php?title=Olive_Leaf_Foundation&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Olive Leaf Foundation (page does not exist)">Olive Leaf Foundation</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0998717814" title="Special:BookSources/978-0998717814"><bdi>978-0998717814</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+New+Approach+to+Studying+the+Covenants+of+Our+Fathers%3A+A+Harmony+of+Genesis%2C+Moses+and+Abraham&amp;rft.pub=Olive+Leaf+Foundation&amp;rft.date=2017-11-24&amp;rft.isbn=978-0998717814&amp;rft.aulast=Rosenvall&amp;rft.aufirst=Lynn+A.&amp;rft.au=Rosenvall%2C+David+L.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Presents the text of the <a href="/wiki/Book_of_Genesis" title="Book of Genesis">Book of Genesis</a>, <a href="/wiki/Book_of_Moses" title="Book of Moses">Book of Moses</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Book_of_Abraham" title="Book of Abraham">Book of Abraham</a> into 186 events or episodes placed in chronological sequence; in an effort to present the <a href="/wiki/Primeval_history" title="Primeval history">primeval history</a> of the <a href="/wiki/Genesis_creation_narrative" title="Genesis creation narrative">Genesis creation narrative</a> in a comprehensive harmonized structure.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Criticism">Criticism</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: Criticism"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1033289096"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Further information: <a href="/wiki/Criticism_of_Mormon_sacred_texts" title="Criticism of Mormon sacred texts">Criticism of Mormon sacred texts</a></div>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPalmer2002" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Grant_H._Palmer" title="Grant H. Palmer">Palmer, Grant H.</a> (15 November 2002). <i><a href="/wiki/An_Insider%27s_View_of_Mormon_Origins" title="An Insider&#39;s View of Mormon Origins">An Insider's View of Mormon Origins</a></i>. Salt Lake City: <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1560851570" title="Special:BookSources/1560851570"><bdi>1560851570</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=An+Insider%27s+View+of+Mormon+Origins&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=2002-11-15&amp;rft.isbn=1560851570&amp;rft.aulast=Palmer&amp;rft.aufirst=Grant+H.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Examination of the contents of the Book of Mormon, challenging the claim of ancient origin; by a retired <a href="/wiki/Church_Educational_System" title="Church Educational System">CES</a> instructor and <a href="/wiki/Institutes_of_Religion" class="mw-redirect" title="Institutes of Religion">Institute</a> director.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPersuitte2000" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/David_Persuitte" class="mw-redirect" title="David Persuitte">Persuitte, David</a> (1 September 2000) [1985]. <i><a href="/wiki/Joseph_Smith_and_the_Origins_of_the_Book_of_Mormon" title="Joseph Smith and the Origins of the Book of Mormon">Joseph Smith and the Origins of the Book of Mormon</a></i> (second expanded&#160;ed.). <a href="/wiki/Jefferson,_NC" class="mw-redirect" title="Jefferson, NC">Jefferson, NC</a>: <a href="/wiki/McFarland_%26_Company" title="McFarland &amp; Company">McFarland</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/078640826X" title="Special:BookSources/078640826X"><bdi>078640826X</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Joseph+Smith+and+the+Origins+of+the+Book+of+Mormon&amp;rft.place=Jefferson%2C+NC&amp;rft.edition=second+expanded&amp;rft.pub=McFarland&amp;rft.date=2000-09-01&amp;rft.isbn=078640826X&amp;rft.aulast=Persuitte&amp;rft.aufirst=David&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=5Zx9qOay304C">[20]</a>
<ul><li>Biographical sketch of <a href="/wiki/Joseph_Smith" title="Joseph Smith">Joseph Smith</a> with background information about the origin of the Book of Mormon; posits the idea that Smith used the 1823 work <i><a href="/wiki/View_of_the_Hebrews" title="View of the Hebrews">View of the Hebrews</a></i> as a source of ideas in creating the Book.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFLarson1992" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Charles_M._Larson&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Charles M. Larson (page does not exist)">Larson, Charles M.</a> (1 March 1992). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=By_His_Own_Hand_Upon_Papyrus&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="By His Own Hand Upon Papyrus (page does not exist)">By His Own Hand Upon Papyrus</a>: A New Look at the Joseph Smith Papyri</i>. <a href="/wiki/Institute_for_Religious_Research" title="Institute for Religious Research">Institute for Religious Research</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0962096326" title="Special:BookSources/0962096326"><bdi>0962096326</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=By+His+Own+Hand+Upon+Papyrus%3A+A+New+Look+at+the+Joseph+Smith+Papyri&amp;rft.pub=Institute+for+Religious+Research&amp;rft.date=1992-03-01&amp;rft.isbn=0962096326&amp;rft.aulast=Larson&amp;rft.aufirst=Charles+M.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/ByHisOwnHandUponPapyrusByCharlesB.Larson">[21]</a>
<ul><li>Critical examination of the <a href="/wiki/Joseph_Smith_Papyri" title="Joseph Smith Papyri">Egyptian papyri from which Joseph Smith</a> purportedly translated the <a href="/wiki/Book_of_Abraham" title="Book of Abraham">Book of Abraham</a>.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Beliefs_and_practices">Beliefs and practices</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=17" title="Edit section: Beliefs and practices"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1033289096"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Further information: <a href="/wiki/Mormon_doctrine" class="mw-redirect" title="Mormon doctrine">Mormon doctrine</a></div>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMillet1998" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Robert_L._Millet" title="Robert L. Millet">Millet, Robert L.</a> (1 March 1998). <i>The Mormon Faith: A New Look at Christianity</i>. <a href="/wiki/Shadow_Mountain_Publishing" class="mw-redirect" title="Shadow Mountain Publishing">Shadow Mountain</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1573453595" title="Special:BookSources/1573453595"><bdi>1573453595</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Mormon+Faith%3A+A+New+Look+at+Christianity&amp;rft.pub=Shadow+Mountain&amp;rft.date=1998-03-01&amp;rft.isbn=1573453595&amp;rft.aulast=Millet&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert+L.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A series of essays examining the theology and doctrine of the LDS Church; written primarily as an introduction for non-members; an overview of the <a href="/wiki/God_in_Mormonism" title="God in Mormonism">LDS views of God</a>, <a href="/wiki/Standard_works" title="Standard works">scripture</a>, <a href="/wiki/Beliefs_and_practices_of_The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints#Jesus_Christ" class="mw-redirect" title="Beliefs and practices of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints">Jesus</a>, the <a href="/wiki/Mormon_cosmology#Temporal_creation_and_fall" title="Mormon cosmology">nature and destiny of man</a>, <a href="/wiki/Grace_in_Christianity#The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints_(Mormon)" title="Grace in Christianity">grace</a> and <a href="/wiki/Plan_of_salvation_(Latter_Day_Saints)" class="mw-redirect" title="Plan of salvation (Latter Day Saints)">salvation</a>, <a href="/wiki/Sacrament_(LDS_Church)" title="Sacrament (LDS Church)">the sacraments</a>, the <a href="/wiki/Priesthood_(Latter_Day_Saints)" title="Priesthood (Latter Day Saints)">priesthood</a>, the purpose of <a href="/wiki/Temple_(LDS_Church)" title="Temple (LDS Church)">the temples</a>, <a href="/wiki/Beliefs_and_practices_of_The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints#Revelation" class="mw-redirect" title="Beliefs and practices of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints">revelation</a> and <a href="/wiki/Second_Coming_(LDS_Church)" class="mw-redirect" title="Second Coming (LDS Church)">eschatology</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSmith1985" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Joseph_Smith" title="Joseph Smith">Smith, Joseph Jr.</a> (1985) [1835]. <i><a href="/wiki/Lectures_on_Faith" title="Lectures on Faith">Lectures on Faith</a></i>. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Deseret_Book" class="mw-redirect" title="Deseret Book">Deseret Book</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/087747897X" title="Special:BookSources/087747897X"><bdi>087747897X</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Lectures+on+Faith&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Book&amp;rft.date=1985&amp;rft.isbn=087747897X&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph+Jr.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.josephsmithpapers.org/paper-summary/doctrine-and-covenants-1844/7">[22]</a>
<ul><li>A set of seven lectures on the doctrine and theology of the <a href="/wiki/Church_of_Christ_(Latter_Day_Saints)" title="Church of Christ (Latter Day Saints)">Church of Jesus Christ of Latter Day Saints</a>, first published as the doctrine portion of the canonical <a href="/wiki/Doctrine_and_Covenants" title="Doctrine and Covenants">Doctrine and Covenants</a>, but later removed from that work; originally presented to a group of <a href="/wiki/Elder_(Latter_Day_Saints)" title="Elder (Latter Day Saints)">Elders</a> in a "<a href="/wiki/School_of_the_Prophets" title="School of the Prophets">School of the Prophets</a>" course in the early winter of 1834–35 in <a href="/wiki/Kirtland,_Ohio" title="Kirtland, Ohio">Kirtland, Ohio</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFYoung1954" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young" title="Brigham Young">Young, Brigham</a> (1 June 1954) [1925]. <a href="/wiki/John_Andreas_Widtsoe" class="mw-redirect" title="John Andreas Widtsoe">Widtsoe, John A.</a> (ed.). <span class="id-lock-registration" title="Free registration required"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/discoursesofbrig00youn"><i>Discourses of Brigham Young</i></a></span>. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Deseret_Book" class="mw-redirect" title="Deseret Book">Deseret Book</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0877470669" title="Special:BookSources/0877470669"><bdi>0877470669</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Discourses+of+Brigham+Young&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Book&amp;rft.date=1954-06-01&amp;rft.isbn=0877470669&amp;rft.aulast=Young&amp;rft.aufirst=Brigham&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fdiscoursesofbrig00youn&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/stream/discoursesofbrig028407mbp#page/n3/mode/2up">[23]</a>
<ul><li>Collection of pronouncements by the Second President of the LDS Church, primarily from the <i><a href="/wiki/Journal_of_Discourses" title="Journal of Discourses">Journal of Discourses</a></i>, arranged by topic.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSmith2015" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Joseph_F._Smith" title="Joseph F. Smith">Smith, Joseph F.</a> (2015) [1919]. <a href="/wiki/John_Andreas_Widtsoe" class="mw-redirect" title="John Andreas Widtsoe">Widtsoe, John Andreas</a> (ed.). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Gospel_Doctrine:_Selections_From_the_Sermons_and_Writings_of_Joseph_F._Smith&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Gospel Doctrine: Selections From the Sermons and Writings of Joseph F. Smith (page does not exist)">Gospel Doctrine: Selections From the Sermons and Writings of Joseph F. Smith</a></i>. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/The_Deseret_News" class="mw-redirect" title="The Deseret News">The Deseret News</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1333356347" title="Special:BookSources/978-1333356347"><bdi>978-1333356347</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Gospel+Doctrine%3A+Selections+From+the+Sermons+and+Writings+of+Joseph+F.+Smith&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=The+Deseret+News&amp;rft.date=2015&amp;rft.isbn=978-1333356347&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph+F.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/stream/gospeldoctrinese00smitrich#page/n7/mode/2up">[24]</a>
<ul><li>Collection of teachings from the 6th president of the LDS Church (from 1901 to 1918); first published as a course of study for <a href="/wiki/Melchizedek_priesthood_(Latter_Day_Saints)" title="Melchizedek priesthood (Latter Day Saints)">Melchizedek Priesthood</a> <a href="/wiki/Quorum_(Latter_Day_Saints)" title="Quorum (Latter Day Saints)">quorums</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFTalmage1915" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/James_E._Talmage" title="James E. Talmage">Talmage, James E.</a> (1915). <i><a href="/wiki/Jesus_the_Christ_(book)" title="Jesus the Christ (book)">Jesus the Christ</a>: A Study of the Messiah and His Mission According to the Holy Scriptures Both Ancient and Modern</i>. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Deseret_Book" class="mw-redirect" title="Deseret Book">Deseret Book</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1598111957" title="Special:BookSources/1598111957"><bdi>1598111957</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Jesus+the+Christ%3A+A+Study+of+the+Messiah+and+His+Mission+According+to+the+Holy+Scriptures+Both+Ancient+and+Modern&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Book&amp;rft.date=1915&amp;rft.isbn=1598111957&amp;rft.aulast=Talmage&amp;rft.aufirst=James+E.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/22542">[25]</a></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFTalmage1915" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/James_E._Talmage" title="James E. Talmage">Talmage, James Edward</a> (1915). <i><a href="/wiki/Jesus_the_Christ_(book)" title="Jesus the Christ (book)">Jesus the Christ</a>: A Study of the Messiah and His Mission According to Holy Scriptures Both Ancient and Modern</i>. <a href="/wiki/Deseret_News" title="Deseret News">Deseret News</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0877479038" title="Special:BookSources/0877479038"><bdi>0877479038</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Jesus+the+Christ%3A+A+Study+of+the+Messiah+and+His+Mission+According+to+Holy+Scriptures+Both+Ancient+and+Modern&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+News&amp;rft.date=1915&amp;rft.isbn=0877479038&amp;rft.aulast=Talmage&amp;rft.aufirst=James+Edward&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a class="external autonumber" href="https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Jesus_the_Christ">[26]</a>
<ul><li>Viewed by the LDS Church as a classic text on its <a href="/wiki/Beliefs_and_practices_of_The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints#Jesus_Christ" class="mw-redirect" title="Beliefs and practices of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints">teachings and beliefs concerning the life and ministry of Jesus</a>; by an Apostle.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSmith1999" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Joseph_Fielding_Smith" title="Joseph Fielding Smith">Smith, Joseph Fielding</a> (1999) [1954]. <a href="/wiki/Bruce_R._McConkie" title="Bruce R. McConkie">McConkie, Bruce R.</a> (ed.). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Doctrines_of_Salvation&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Doctrines of Salvation (page does not exist)">Doctrines of Salvation</a>: Sermons and Writings of Joseph Fielding Smith</i> (3-in-1&#160;ed.). Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Bookcraft" title="Bookcraft">Bookcraft</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/157008646X" title="Special:BookSources/157008646X"><bdi>157008646X</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Doctrines+of+Salvation%3A+Sermons+and+Writings+of+Joseph+Fielding+Smith&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.edition=3-in-1&amp;rft.pub=Bookcraft&amp;rft.date=1999&amp;rft.isbn=157008646X&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph+Fielding&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/Doctrines-of-Salvation-volume-2-joseph-fielding-smith">[27]</a><a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/Doctrines-of-Salvation-volume-3-joseph-fielding-smith">[28]</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/Doctrines-of-Salvation-volume-1-joseph-fielding-smith">[29]</a>
<ul><li>Three volume collection on an array of gospel topics by then <a href="/wiki/President_of_the_Quorum_of_the_Twelve_Apostles_(LDS_Church)" title="President of the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles (LDS Church)">President of the Quorum of Twelve</a>; the <a href="/wiki/Pre-existence#The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints" title="Pre-existence">nature of our life in the pre-existence</a>; the <a href="/wiki/Mormon_cosmology#Temporal_creation_and_fall" title="Mormon cosmology">true story of creation</a>; <a href="/wiki/Dating_creation" title="Dating creation">the age of the earth</a>; <a href="/wiki/Mormon_views_on_evolution" title="Mormon views on evolution">the theory of evolution and the Gospel</a>; <a href="/wiki/Adam%E2%80%93God_doctrine" title="Adam–God doctrine">the Adam-God theory</a>; distinguishing between <a href="/wiki/Revelation_(Latter_Day_Saints)" class="mw-redirect" title="Revelation (Latter Day Saints)">true and false revelation</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFRichards1857" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Franklin_D._Richards_(Mormon_apostle)" title="Franklin D. Richards (Mormon apostle)">Richards, Franklin Dewey</a> (1857). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=A_Compendium_of_the_Faith_and_Doctrines_of_the_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="A Compendium of the Faith and Doctrines of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints (page does not exist)">A Compendium of the Faith and Doctrines of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints</a>: Compiled from the Bible; and Also from the Book of Mormon, Doctrine and Covenants, and Other Publications of the Church</i>. <a href="/wiki/Orson_Pratt" title="Orson Pratt">Orson Pratt</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1331100658" title="Special:BookSources/1331100658"><bdi>1331100658</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+Compendium+of+the+Faith+and+Doctrines+of+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints%3A+Compiled+from+the+Bible%3B+and+Also+from+the+Book+of+Mormon%2C+Doctrine+and+Covenants%2C+and+Other+Publications+of+the+Church&amp;rft.pub=Orson+Pratt&amp;rft.date=1857&amp;rft.isbn=1331100658&amp;rft.aulast=Richards&amp;rft.aufirst=Franklin+Dewey&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/compendiumoffait00rich">[30]</a>
<ul><li>A lengthy reference work combining doctrine and history; each chapter summarizes a particular doctrine followed by scriptural references from the <a href="/wiki/Standard_works" title="Standard works">standard works</a>, and any relevant statements from Joseph Smith; a favorite of field missionaries at the time.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMcConkie1979" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Bruce_R._McConkie" title="Bruce R. McConkie">McConkie, Bruce R.</a> (1979) [1958]. <i><a href="/wiki/Mormon_Doctrine_(book)" title="Mormon Doctrine (book)">Mormon Doctrine</a></i> (revised second&#160;ed.). <a href="/wiki/Bookcraft" title="Bookcraft">Bookcraft</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0884944468" title="Special:BookSources/0884944468"><bdi>0884944468</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormon+Doctrine&amp;rft.edition=revised+second&amp;rft.pub=Bookcraft&amp;rft.date=1979&amp;rft.isbn=0884944468&amp;rft.aulast=McConkie&amp;rft.aufirst=Bruce+R.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> (Originally subtitled <i>A Compendium of the Gospel</i>). <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/MormonDoctrine">[31]</a>
<ul><li>An encyclopedic work written by a <a href="/wiki/General_authority" title="General authority">general authority</a> of the LDS Church; intended primarily for a LDS audience, it covered a wide array of gospel topics in much detail; very popular among average Church members.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFJaques1888" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/John_Jaques_(Mormon)" title="John Jaques (Mormon)">Jaques, John</a> (1888) [1854]. <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Catechism_for_Children&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Catechism for Children (page does not exist)">Catechism for Children</a>: Exhibiting the Prominent Doctrines of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints</i>. <a href="/wiki/Deseret_News" title="Deseret News">Deseret News</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1333042817" title="Special:BookSources/1333042817"><bdi>1333042817</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Catechism+for+Children%3A+Exhibiting+the+Prominent+Doctrines+of+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+News&amp;rft.date=1888&amp;rft.isbn=1333042817&amp;rft.aulast=Jaques&amp;rft.aufirst=John&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/bcatechismforchil00jaqu">[32]</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/mormoncatechism">[33]</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://contentdm.lib.byu.edu/digital/collection/NCMP1820-1846/id/17398/">[34]</a>
<ul><li>Originally serialized in the <i><a href="/wiki/LDS_Millennial_Star" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Millennial Star">LDS Millennial Star</a></i>, this basic instructional work was very popular among Latter-day Saints.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFRoberts1995" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/B._H._Roberts" title="B. H. Roberts">Roberts, B. H.</a> (1995). <a href="/wiki/Stan_Larson" title="Stan Larson">Larson, Stan</a> (ed.). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Truth,_the_Way,_the_Life&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Truth, the Way, the Life (page does not exist)">The Truth, the Way, the Life</a>: An Elementary Treatise on Theology: The Masterwork of B.H. Roberts</i>. <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1560850779" title="Special:BookSources/1560850779"><bdi>1560850779</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Truth%2C+the+Way%2C+the+Life%3A+An+Elementary+Treatise+on+Theology%3A+The+Masterwork+of+B.H.+Roberts&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.isbn=1560850779&amp;rft.aulast=Roberts&amp;rft.aufirst=B.+H.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>An attempt to consolidate the author's "theological thought into a unified whole and to reconcile science with scripture." Deemed too controversial by the <a href="/wiki/First_Presidency_(LDS_Church)" title="First Presidency (LDS Church)">LDS First Presidency</a> and <a href="/wiki/Quorum_of_the_Twelve_Apostles_(LDS_Church)" title="Quorum of the Twelve Apostles (LDS Church)">Quorum of the Twelve</a>, it went unpublished for over 60 years.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFUnderwood1999" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Grant_Underwood" title="Grant Underwood">Underwood, Grant</a> (1 March 1999) [1993]. <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Millenarian_World_of_Early_Mormonism&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Millenarian World of Early Mormonism (page does not exist)">The Millenarian World of Early Mormonism</a></i>. Urbana: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois" class="mw-redirect" title="University of Illinois">University of Illinois</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0252068262" title="Special:BookSources/0252068262"><bdi>0252068262</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Millenarian+World+of+Early+Mormonism&amp;rft.place=Urbana&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois&amp;rft.date=1999-03-01&amp;rft.isbn=0252068262&amp;rft.aulast=Underwood&amp;rft.aufirst=Grant&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A detailed study of early Mormon thought about the "<a href="/wiki/Eschatology" title="Eschatology">end times</a>"; exploring <a href="/wiki/Mormonism_and_Christianity#The_Book_of_Mormon" class="mw-redirect" title="Mormonism and Christianity">early LDS interpretation of the Bible and the Book of Mormon</a> affecting <a href="/wiki/Second_Coming_(LDS_Church)#The_Millennium" class="mw-redirect" title="Second Coming (LDS Church)">Mormon millennial doctrines</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFToscanoToscano1990" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Margaret_Toscano" title="Margaret Toscano">Toscano, Margaret Merrill</a>; <a href="/wiki/Paul_Toscano" class="mw-redirect" title="Paul Toscano">Toscano, Paul</a> (1990). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Strangers_in_Paradox&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Strangers in Paradox (page does not exist)">Strangers in Paradox</a>: Explorations in Mormon Theology</i>. <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0941214982" title="Special:BookSources/0941214982"><bdi>0941214982</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Strangers+in+Paradox%3A+Explorations+in+Mormon+Theology&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=1990&amp;rft.isbn=0941214982&amp;rft.aulast=Toscano&amp;rft.aufirst=Margaret+Merrill&amp;rft.au=Toscano%2C+Paul&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://signaturebookslibrary.org/strangers-in-paradox/">[35]</a>
<ul><li>A controversial book by one of the <a href="/wiki/September_Six" title="September Six">September Six</a> and his wife (who some view as a "seventh" member of the Six); explores a range of theological issues, such as the <a href="/wiki/Nature_of_God" class="mw-redirect" title="Nature of God">nature of God</a>, <a href="/wiki/Gender_roles" class="mw-redirect" title="Gender roles">gender roles</a>, religious authority, and <a href="/wiki/Religious_symbolism" class="mw-redirect" title="Religious symbolism">symbolism</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMcMurrin2000" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Sterling_M._McMurrin" title="Sterling M. McMurrin">McMurrin, Sterling M.</a> (2000) [1965]. <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Theological_Foundations_of_the_Mormon_Religion&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Theological Foundations of the Mormon Religion (page does not exist)">The Theological Foundations of the Mormon Religion</a>: And, the Philosophical Foundations of Mormon Theology</i>. <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/156085135X" title="Special:BookSources/156085135X"><bdi>156085135X</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Theological+Foundations+of+the+Mormon+Religion%3A+And%2C+the+Philosophical+Foundations+of+Mormon+Theology&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.isbn=156085135X&amp;rft.aulast=McMurrin&amp;rft.aufirst=Sterling+M.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Philosophical study of the similarities between Mormonism and <a href="/wiki/Christianity_and_Hellenistic_philosophy" class="mw-redirect" title="Christianity and Hellenistic philosophy">Hellenistic Christianity</a>; and Mormonism's contribution to the overall pursuit of life's fundamental, <a href="/wiki/Ontological" class="mw-redirect" title="Ontological">ontological</a> questions.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFKimball2006" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Edward_L._Kimball" title="Edward L. Kimball">Kimball, Edward L.</a> (2006) [1978]. <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Teachings_of_Spencer_W._Kimball&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Teachings of Spencer W. Kimball (page does not exist)">The Teachings of Spencer W. Kimball</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Deseret_Books" class="mw-redirect" title="Deseret Books">Deseret Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1570089388" title="Special:BookSources/1570089388"><bdi>1570089388</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Teachings+of+Spencer+W.+Kimball&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Books&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.isbn=1570089388&amp;rft.aulast=Kimball&amp;rft.aufirst=Edward+L.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Collection of sermons and writings by <a href="/wiki/Spencer_W._Kimball" title="Spencer W. Kimball">Spencer W. Kimball</a>, a <a href="/wiki/Apostle_(Latter_Day_Saints)" title="Apostle (Latter Day Saints)">LDS Apostle</a> (from 1943 to 1985) and Church President (from 1973 to 1985); quotations aiming to provide instruction and inspiration on a wide range of gospel topics.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSpencerCrowel1848" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Orson_Spencer" title="Orson Spencer">Spencer, Orson</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=William_Crowel&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="William Crowel (page does not exist)">Crowel, William</a> (1848). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Letters_Exhibiting_the_Most_Prominent_Doctrines_of_the_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Letters Exhibiting the Most Prominent Doctrines of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints (page does not exist)">Letters Exhibiting the Most Prominent Doctrines of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints: In Reply to Rev. William Crowel</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Deseret_News_Company" class="mw-redirect" title="Deseret News Company">Deseret News Company</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/137544607X" title="Special:BookSources/137544607X"><bdi>137544607X</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Letters+Exhibiting+the+Most+Prominent+Doctrines+of+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints%3A+In+Reply+to+Rev.+William+Crowel&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+News+Company&amp;rft.date=1848&amp;rft.isbn=137544607X&amp;rft.aulast=Spencer&amp;rft.aufirst=Orson&amp;rft.au=Crowel%2C+William&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=7VdNAAAAYAAJ">[36]</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/lettersexhibitin03spen">[37]</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/45846">[38]</a>
<ul><li>A series of letters from <a href="/wiki/Rev." class="mw-redirect" title="Rev.">Rev.</a> Crowell (a <a href="/wiki/Baptist" class="mw-redirect" title="Baptist">Baptist</a> former colleague) inquiring about Spencer's conversion to the Mormon faith, together Spencer's responses.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFTalmage1909" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/James_E._Talmage" title="James E. Talmage">Talmage, James Edward</a> (1909). <i><a href="/wiki/The_Great_Apostasy_(book)" title="The Great Apostasy (book)">The Great Apostasy</a>: Considered in the Light of Scriptural and Secular History</i>. <a href="/wiki/Deseret_News" title="Deseret News">Deseret News</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1628451181" title="Special:BookSources/1628451181"><bdi>1628451181</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Great+Apostasy%3A+Considered+in+the+Light+of+Scriptural+and+Secular+History&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+News&amp;rft.date=1909&amp;rft.isbn=1628451181&amp;rft.aulast=Talmage&amp;rft.aufirst=James+Edward&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/greatapostasyco00talmgoog">[39]</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/35514">[40]</a>
<ul><li>Summarizes the <a href="/wiki/Great_Apostasy#Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints" title="Great Apostasy">Great Apostasy from the viewpoint of the LDS Church</a>; was once one of the few non-scriptural books which full-time <a href="/wiki/LDS_missionaries" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS missionaries">LDS missionaries</a> were encouraged to study; it has gone through many editions and continues to be published.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFHinckley2000" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Gordon_B._Hinckley" title="Gordon B. Hinckley">Hinckley, Gordon B.</a> (22 February 2000). <i><a href="/wiki/Standing_for_Something" title="Standing for Something">Standing for Something</a>: Ten Neglected Virtues that Will Heal Our Hearts and Homes</i>. <a href="/wiki/Times_Books" title="Times Books">Times Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0812933176" title="Special:BookSources/0812933176"><bdi>0812933176</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Standing+for+Something%3A+Ten+Neglected+Virtues+that+Will+Heal+Our+Hearts+and+Homes&amp;rft.pub=Times+Books&amp;rft.date=2000-02-22&amp;rft.isbn=0812933176&amp;rft.aulast=Hinckley&amp;rft.aufirst=Gordon+B.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A <a href="/wiki/Self-improvement_book" class="mw-redirect" title="Self-improvement book">self-improvement book</a>, by then president of the LDS Church; foreword by <a href="/wiki/Mike_Wallace" title="Mike Wallace">Mike Wallace</a>.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Special_topics">Special topics</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=18" title="Edit section: Special topics"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Death">Death</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=19" title="Edit section: Death"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFNelson1995" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Russell_M._Nelson" title="Russell M. Nelson">Nelson, Russell M.</a> (1995). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Gateway_We_Call_Death&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Gateway We Call Death (page does not exist)">The Gateway We Call Death</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Deseret_Book_Company" title="Deseret Book Company">Deseret Book Company</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0875799531" title="Special:BookSources/0875799531"><bdi>0875799531</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Gateway+We+Call+Death&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Book+Company&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.isbn=0875799531&amp;rft.aulast=Nelson&amp;rft.aufirst=Russell+M.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>An approach to the subject of <a href="/wiki/Death" title="Death">death</a> from both a medical and a theological point of view by a (then) LDS Apostle; discussing topics such as the purpose of life and of death; the purpose of mourning; factors of choice, such as <a href="/wiki/Suicide" title="Suicide">suicide</a>, <a href="/wiki/Euthanasia" title="Euthanasia">euthanasia</a>, and use of mechanical means to extend life; and <a href="/wiki/Life_after_death" class="mw-redirect" title="Life after death">life after death</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBrown2011" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Samuel_Morris_Brown&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Samuel Morris Brown (page does not exist)">Brown, Samuel Morris</a> (1 December 2011). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=In_Heaven_as_It_Is_on_Earth&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="In Heaven as It Is on Earth (page does not exist)">In Heaven as It Is on Earth</a>: Joseph Smith and the Early Mormon Conquest of Death</i>. <a href="/wiki/Oxford_University_Press,_USA" class="mw-redirect" title="Oxford University Press, USA">Oxford University Press, USA</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0199793570" title="Special:BookSources/978-0199793570"><bdi>978-0199793570</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=In+Heaven+as+It+Is+on+Earth%3A+Joseph+Smith+and+the+Early+Mormon+Conquest+of+Death&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press%2C+USA&amp;rft.date=2011-12-01&amp;rft.isbn=978-0199793570&amp;rft.aulast=Brown&amp;rft.aufirst=Samuel+Morris&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Narrative history of the foundational beliefs of early Mormonism; interpreting them through the lens of Joseph Smith's preoccupation with <a href="/wiki/Death" title="Death">death</a>.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Evolution">Evolution</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=20" title="Edit section: Evolution"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1033289096"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Further information: <a href="/wiki/Mormon_views_on_evolution" title="Mormon views on evolution">Mormon views on evolution</a></div>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSmith1954" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Joseph_Fielding_Smith" title="Joseph Fielding Smith">Smith, Joseph Fielding</a> (1954). <i>Man, His Origin and Destiny</i>. Salt Lake City: <a href="/wiki/Deseret_Book" class="mw-redirect" title="Deseret Book">Deseret Book</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Man%2C+His+Origin+and+Destiny&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Book&amp;rft.date=1954&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph+Fielding&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.sainesburyproject.com/mormonstuff/Man%20His%20Origin%20and%20Destiny.pdf">[41]</a>
<ul><li>Challenge to the "hypothesis of organic evolution"; written by the then <a href="/wiki/President_of_the_Quorum_of_the_Twelve_Apostles_(LDS_Church)" title="President of the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles (LDS Church)">President of the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles</a> of the LDS Church.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFEvensonJeffery2006" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=William_E._Evenson&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="William E. Evenson (page does not exist)">Evenson, William E.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Duane_E._Jeffery&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Duane E. Jeffery (page does not exist)">Jeffery, Duane E.</a> (11 January 2006). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Mormonism_and_Evolution&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Mormonism and Evolution (page does not exist)">Mormonism and Evolution</a>: The Authoritative LDS Statements</i>. Salt Lake City: <a href="/w/index.php?title=Greg_Kofford_Books&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Greg Kofford Books (page does not exist)">Greg Kofford Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1589580931" title="Special:BookSources/1589580931"><bdi>1589580931</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormonism+and+Evolution%3A+The+Authoritative+LDS+Statements&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.pub=Greg+Kofford+Books&amp;rft.date=2006-01-11&amp;rft.isbn=1589580931&amp;rft.aulast=Evenson&amp;rft.aufirst=William+E.&amp;rft.au=Jeffery%2C+Duane+E.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Compilation of all known authoritative statements by LDS Church leaders on the topics of evolution and the origin of human beings; with historical context for the statements.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFStephensMeldrumPeterson2001" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Trent_D._Stephens&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Trent D. Stephens (page does not exist)">Stephens, Trent D.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Jeff_Meldrum" class="mw-redirect" title="Jeff Meldrum">Meldrum, D. Jeffrey</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Forrest_B._Peterson&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Forrest B. Peterson (page does not exist)">Peterson, Forrest B.</a> (15 February 2001). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Evolution_and_Mormonism&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Evolution and Mormonism (page does not exist)">Evolution and Mormonism</a>: A Quest for Understanding</i>. Salt Lake City: <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1560851422" title="Special:BookSources/1560851422"><bdi>1560851422</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Evolution+and+Mormonism%3A+A+Quest+for+Understanding&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=2001-02-15&amp;rft.isbn=1560851422&amp;rft.aulast=Stephens&amp;rft.aufirst=Trent+D.&amp;rft.au=Meldrum%2C+D.+Jeffrey&amp;rft.au=Peterson%2C+Forrest+B.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A review the scientific data about how life developed on Earth, written for a general LDS audience.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSessionsOberg1993" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Gene_A._Sessions&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Gene A. Sessions (page does not exist)">Sessions, Gene A.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Craig_J._Oberg&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Craig J. Oberg (page does not exist)">Oberg, Craig J.</a>, eds. (1 March 1993). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Search_for_Harmony&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Search for Harmony (page does not exist)">The Search for Harmony</a>: Essays on Science and Mormonism</i>. Salt Lake City: <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1560850205" title="Special:BookSources/1560850205"><bdi>1560850205</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Search+for+Harmony%3A+Essays+on+Science+and+Mormonism&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=1993-03-01&amp;rft.isbn=1560850205&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://signaturebookslibrary.org/the-search-for-harmony/">[42]</a>
<ul><li>Compilation of essays on the theological implications of science, by LDS scientists.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPaul1992" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Erich_Paul&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Erich Paul (page does not exist)">Paul, Erich Robert</a> (1 June 1992). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Science,_Religion,_and_Mormon_Cosmology&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Science, Religion, and Mormon Cosmology (page does not exist)">Science, Religion, and Mormon Cosmology</a></i>. Urbana: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0252018958" title="Special:BookSources/0252018958"><bdi>0252018958</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Science%2C+Religion%2C+and+Mormon+Cosmology&amp;rft.place=Urbana&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=1992-06-01&amp;rft.isbn=0252018958&amp;rft.aulast=Paul&amp;rft.aufirst=Erich+Robert&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=xAm4qGyN2OYC">[43]</a>
<ul><li>Historical survey of the LDS Church's varied relationship to science.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Occult_aspects">Occult aspects</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=21" title="Edit section: Occult aspects"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFQuinn1998" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/D._Michael_Quinn" title="D. Michael Quinn">Quinn, D. Michael</a> (15 December 1998) [1987]. <i><a href="/wiki/Early_Mormonism_and_the_Magic_World_View" class="mw-redirect" title="Early Mormonism and the Magic World View">Early Mormonism and the Magic World View</a></i> (Revised and enlarged&#160;ed.). Salt Lake City: <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1560850892" title="Special:BookSources/1560850892"><bdi>1560850892</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Early+Mormonism+and+the+Magic+World+View&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.edition=Revised+and+enlarged&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=1998-12-15&amp;rft.isbn=1560850892&amp;rft.aulast=Quinn&amp;rft.aufirst=D.+Michael&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Study of the role of 19th-century New England folk magic lore in <a href="/wiki/Joseph_Smith" title="Joseph Smith">Joseph Smith</a>'s early visions and in the development of the <a href="/wiki/Book_of_Mormon" title="Book of Mormon">Book of Mormon</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFReeveWagenen2011" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/W._Paul_Reeve" title="W. Paul Reeve">Reeve, W. Paul</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Michael_Scott_Van_Wagenen&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Michael Scott Van Wagenen (page does not exist)">Wagenen, Michael Scott Van</a>, eds. (23 May 2011). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Between_Pulpit_and_Pew&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Between Pulpit and Pew (page does not exist)">Between Pulpit and Pew</a>: The Supernatural World in Mormon History and Folklore</i>. <a href="/wiki/Utah_State_University_Press" class="mw-redirect" title="Utah State University Press">Utah State University Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0874218381" title="Special:BookSources/978-0874218381"><bdi>978-0874218381</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Between+Pulpit+and+Pew%3A+The+Supernatural+World+in+Mormon+History+and+Folklore&amp;rft.pub=Utah+State+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2011-05-23&amp;rft.isbn=978-0874218381&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>An exploration of Mormon cultural and religious history through a collection of folklore, <a href="/wiki/Supernatural" title="Supernatural">supernatural</a> legends and events; including stories of <a href="/wiki/David_W._Patten#Story_of_meeting_Cain" title="David W. Patten">Cain as a Bigfoot</a>, the <a href="/wiki/Gadianton_robbers" title="Gadianton robbers">Gadianton robbers</a>, <a href="/wiki/UFOs" class="mw-redirect" title="UFOs">UFOs</a>, the <a href="/wiki/Dream_Mine" title="Dream Mine">Dream Mine</a>, and an Utah version of <a href="/wiki/Nessie" class="mw-redirect" title="Nessie">Nessie</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBrooke1996" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/John_L._Brooke" title="John L. Brooke">Brooke, John L.</a> (31 May 1996). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Refiner%27s_Fire&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Refiner&#39;s Fire (page does not exist)">The Refiner's Fire</a>: The Making of Mormon Cosmology, 1644-1844</i>. <a href="/wiki/Cambridge_University_Press" title="Cambridge University Press">Cambridge University Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521565642" title="Special:BookSources/0521565642"><bdi>0521565642</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Refiner%27s+Fire%3A+The+Making+of+Mormon+Cosmology%2C+1644-1844&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.date=1996-05-31&amp;rft.isbn=0521565642&amp;rft.aulast=Brooke&amp;rft.aufirst=John+L.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=eyvftt-1F_kC">[44]</a>
<ul><li>A history of the roots of Mormon theology; contending that its origins lie in the <a href="/wiki/Hermetism_and_other_religions#Mormonism" title="Hermetism and other religions">fusion of radical religion with occult ideas</a>.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Politics">Politics</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=22" title="Edit section: Politics"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1033289096"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Further information: <a href="/wiki/The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints_and_politics_in_the_United_States" title="The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints and politics in the United States">The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints and politics in the United States</a></div>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFFlake2004" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Kathleen_Flake" title="Kathleen Flake">Flake, Kathleen</a> (22 March 2004). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Politics_of_American_Religious_Identity&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Politics of American Religious Identity (page does not exist)">The Politics of American Religious Identity</a>: The Seating of Senator Reed Smoot, Mormon Apostle</i>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_North_Carolina_Press" title="University of North Carolina Press">University of North Carolina Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0807855014" title="Special:BookSources/0807855014"><bdi>0807855014</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Politics+of+American+Religious+Identity%3A+The+Seating+of+Senator+Reed+Smoot%2C+Mormon+Apostle&amp;rft.pub=University+of+North+Carolina+Press&amp;rft.date=2004-03-22&amp;rft.isbn=0807855014&amp;rft.aulast=Flake&amp;rft.aufirst=Kathleen&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=GLLCAB5vmMQC">[45]</a>
<ul><li>Analysis of the <a href="/wiki/Reed_Smoot_hearings" title="Reed Smoot hearings">Reed Smoot hearings</a> and their impact on the "<a href="/w/index.php?title=Mormon_Problem&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Mormon Problem (page does not exist)">Mormon Problem</a>."</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBringhurstFoster2011" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Newell_G._Bringhurst" title="Newell G. Bringhurst">Bringhurst, Newell G.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Craig_L._Foster&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Craig L. Foster (page does not exist)">Foster, Craig L.</a> (11 September 2011) [2008]. <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Mormon_Quest_for_the_Presidency&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Mormon Quest for the Presidency (page does not exist)">The Mormon Quest for the Presidency</a>: From Joseph Smith to Mitt Romney and Jon Huntsman </i>(expanded and updated volume)<i><span></span></i>. <a href="/wiki/John_Whitmer_Books" class="mw-redirect" title="John Whitmer Books">John Whitmer Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1934901090" title="Special:BookSources/978-1934901090"><bdi>978-1934901090</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Mormon+Quest+for+the+Presidency%3A+From+Joseph+Smith+to+Mitt+Romney+and+Jon+Huntsman+%28expanded+and+updated+volume%29&amp;rft.pub=John+Whitmer+Books&amp;rft.date=2011-09-11&amp;rft.isbn=978-1934901090&amp;rft.aulast=Bringhurst&amp;rft.aufirst=Newell+G.&amp;rft.au=Foster%2C+Craig+L.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A detailed description of the campaigns of 11 Mormons (including <a href="/wiki/Ex-Mormons" class="mw-redirect" title="Ex-Mormons">ex-Mormons</a> and soon-to-be Mormons) who <a href="/wiki/United_States_presidential_election" title="United States presidential election">ran for the presidency of the United States</a>; it includes the <a href="/wiki/Third_party_(United_States)" class="mw-redirect" title="Third party (United States)">third-party</a> runs of <a href="/wiki/Joseph_Smith_presidential_campaign,_1844" class="mw-redirect" title="Joseph Smith presidential campaign, 1844">Joseph Smith (1844)</a>, <a href="/wiki/Parley_P._Christensen" title="Parley P. Christensen">Parley P. Christensen</a> (1920), <a href="/wiki/Ezra_Taft_Benson" title="Ezra Taft Benson">Ezra Taft Benson</a> (1968), <a href="/wiki/Eldridge_Cleaver" title="Eldridge Cleaver">Eldridge Cleaver</a> (1968), <a href="/wiki/Sonia_Johnson" title="Sonia Johnson">Sonia Johnson</a> (1984), and <a href="/wiki/Bo_Gritz" title="Bo Gritz">Bo Gritz</a> (1992); and the major-party runs of <a href="/wiki/George_Romney_presidential_campaign,_1968" class="mw-redirect" title="George Romney presidential campaign, 1968">George Romney (1968)</a>, <a href="/wiki/Mo_Udall" title="Mo Udall">Mo Udall</a> (1976), <a href="/wiki/Orrin_Hatch" title="Orrin Hatch">Orrin Hatch</a> (2000), <a href="/wiki/Mitt_Romney_presidential_campaign,_2008" class="mw-redirect" title="Mitt Romney presidential campaign, 2008">Mitt Romney (2008)</a> and <a href="/wiki/Mitt_Romney_presidential_campaign,_2012" class="mw-redirect" title="Mitt Romney presidential campaign, 2012">2012</a>) and <a href="/wiki/Jon_Huntsman_presidential_campaign,_2012" class="mw-redirect" title="Jon Huntsman presidential campaign, 2012">Jon Huntsman (2012)</a>.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Polygamy">Polygamy</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=23" title="Edit section: Polygamy"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1033289096"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Further information: <a href="/wiki/Mormonism_and_polygamy" title="Mormonism and polygamy">Mormonism and polygamy</a></div>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFCompton1997" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Todd_Compton" title="Todd Compton">Compton, Todd M.</a> (15 December 1997). <i><a href="/wiki/In_Sacred_Loneliness" class="mw-redirect" title="In Sacred Loneliness">In Sacred Loneliness</a>: The Plural Wives of Joseph Smith</i>. Salt Lake City: <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/156085085X" title="Special:BookSources/156085085X"><bdi>156085085X</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=In+Sacred+Loneliness%3A+The+Plural+Wives+of+Joseph+Smith&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=1997-12-15&amp;rft.isbn=156085085X&amp;rft.aulast=Compton&amp;rft.aufirst=Todd+M.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=ApztAAAAMAAJ">[46]</a>
<ul><li>Biographical look at each of <a href="/wiki/List_of_Joseph_Smith%27s_wives" title="List of Joseph Smith&#39;s wives">the 33 women who married Joseph Smith</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBringhurstFoster2010" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Newell_G._Bringhurst" title="Newell G. Bringhurst">Bringhurst, Newell G.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Craig_L._Foster&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Craig L. Foster (page does not exist)">Foster, Craig L.</a>, eds. (1 November 2010). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Persistence_of_Polygamy&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Persistence of Polygamy (page does not exist)">The Persistence of Polygamy</a>: Joseph Smith and the Origins of Mormon Polygamy</i>. <a href="/wiki/John_Whitmer_Books" class="mw-redirect" title="John Whitmer Books">John Whitmer Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1934901137" title="Special:BookSources/978-1934901137"><bdi>978-1934901137</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Persistence+of+Polygamy%3A+Joseph+Smith+and+the+Origins+of+Mormon+Polygamy&amp;rft.pub=John+Whitmer+Books&amp;rft.date=2010-11-01&amp;rft.isbn=978-1934901137&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>First of three volumes, collecting essays on the relationship of Joseph Smith to <a href="/wiki/Fanny_Alger" title="Fanny Alger">Fanny Alger</a>, analysis of Section 132 of the LDS <a href="/wiki/Doctrine_and_Covenants" title="Doctrine and Covenants">Doctrine and Covenants</a> (including the <a href="/wiki/RLDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="RLDS Church">RLDS Church</a>'s reaction), <a href="/wiki/Polyandry#Latter-Day_Saints" title="Polyandry">Joseph Smith and polyandry</a>; contributors include <a href="/wiki/Todd_M._Compton" class="mw-redirect" title="Todd M. Compton">Todd M. Compton</a>, <a href="/wiki/Ugo_A._Perego" title="Ugo A. Perego">Ugo A. Perego</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Linda_King_Newell" title="Linda King Newell">Linda King Newell</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBringhurstFoster2013" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Newell_G._Bringhurst" title="Newell G. Bringhurst">Bringhurst, Newell G.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Craig_L._Foster&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Craig L. Foster (page does not exist)">Foster, Craig L.</a>, eds. (13 September 2013). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Persistence_of_Polygamy&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Persistence of Polygamy (page does not exist)">The Persistence of Polygamy</a>: From Joseph Smith's Martyrdom to the First Manifesto, 1844-1890</i>. <a href="/wiki/John_Whitmer_Books" class="mw-redirect" title="John Whitmer Books">John Whitmer Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1934901144" title="Special:BookSources/978-1934901144"><bdi>978-1934901144</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Persistence+of+Polygamy%3A+From+Joseph+Smith%27s+Martyrdom+to+the+First+Manifesto%2C+1844-1890&amp;rft.pub=John+Whitmer+Books&amp;rft.date=2013-09-13&amp;rft.isbn=978-1934901144&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Second of three volumes, collecting essays on plural marriage as practiced by <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young" title="Brigham Young">Brigham Young</a>, the plural wives of Prophets from Young to <a href="/wiki/Heber_J._Grant" title="Heber J. Grant">Heber J. Grant</a>, <a href="/wiki/Strangites" class="mw-redirect" title="Strangites">Strangites</a>, <a href="/wiki/William_Smith_(Latter_Day_Saints)" title="William Smith (Latter Day Saints)">William Smith</a>, <a href="/wiki/Lyman_Wight" title="Lyman Wight">Lyman Wight</a>, <a href="/wiki/Alpheus_Cutler" title="Alpheus Cutler">Alpheus Cutler</a>, nineteenth-century Mormon female activism, the incarceration of Mormon plural wives, and the <a href="/wiki/RLDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="RLDS Church">RLDS Church</a>'s directive on baptism of <a href="/wiki/Saora" class="mw-redirect" title="Saora">Saora</a> tribal polygamists; contributors include <a href="/wiki/George_D._Smith" class="mw-redirect" title="George D. Smith">George D. Smith</a> and <a href="/wiki/Richard_P._Howard" title="Richard P. Howard">Richard P. Howard</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBringhurstFoster2015" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Newell_G._Bringhurst" title="Newell G. Bringhurst">Bringhurst, Newell G.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Craig_L._Foster&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Craig L. Foster (page does not exist)">Foster, Craig L.</a>, eds. (17 August 2015). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Persistence_of_Polygamy&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Persistence of Polygamy (page does not exist)">Persistence of Polygamy</a>: Fundamentalist Mormon Polygamy from 1890 to the Present</i>. <a href="/wiki/John_Whitmer_Books" class="mw-redirect" title="John Whitmer Books">John Whitmer Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1934901168" title="Special:BookSources/978-1934901168"><bdi>978-1934901168</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Persistence+of+Polygamy%3A+Fundamentalist+Mormon+Polygamy+from+1890+to+the+Present&amp;rft.pub=John+Whitmer+Books&amp;rft.date=2015-08-17&amp;rft.isbn=978-1934901168&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Third of three volumes,  collecting seventeen original essays on the history of plural marriage among <a href="/wiki/Fundamentalist_Mormons" class="mw-redirect" title="Fundamentalist Mormons">fundamentalist Mormons</a>—who persisted in the practice after LDS Church President <a href="/wiki/Wilford_Woodruff" title="Wilford Woodruff">Wilford Woodruff</a>'s <a href="/wiki/1890_Manifesto" title="1890 Manifesto">1890 Manifesto</a>; provides a history of mainstream <a href="/wiki/Mormon_colonies_in_Mexico" title="Mormon colonies in Mexico">LDS polygamy in Mexico</a>, <a href="/wiki/John_Taylor_(Mormon)" title="John Taylor (Mormon)">John Taylor</a>'s controversial <a href="/wiki/1886_Revelation" title="1886 Revelation">1886 Revelation</a>, portraits of fundamentalist Mormon leaders such as <a href="/wiki/Joseph_White_Musser" title="Joseph White Musser">Joseph White Musser</a>, <a href="/wiki/Rulon_C._Allred" title="Rulon C. Allred">Rulon C. Allred</a>, <a href="/wiki/Rulon_T._Jeffs" class="mw-redirect" title="Rulon T. Jeffs">Rulon T. Jeffs</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Warren_S._Jeffs" class="mw-redirect" title="Warren S. Jeffs">Warren S. Jeffs</a>, the 1980s schism between the <a href="/w/index.php?title=FLDS_church&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="FLDS church (page does not exist)">FLDS church</a> and <a href="/wiki/Centennial_Park_group" title="Centennial Park group">Centennial Park Community</a>, the <a href="/wiki/YFZ_Ranch#April_2008_raid" title="YFZ Ranch">2008 Texas raid on the FLDS YFZ Ranch</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Latter_Day_Saints_in_popular_culture" title="Latter Day Saints in popular culture">modern media stereotyping of Mormon polygamy</a>, the changing style of fundamentalist clothing and hair styles.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Race">Race</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=24" title="Edit section: Race"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1033289096"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Further information: <a href="/wiki/Black_people_and_Mormonism" title="Black people and Mormonism">Black people and Mormonism</a></div>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBringhurstSmith2004" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Newell_G._Bringhurst" title="Newell G. Bringhurst">Bringhurst, Newell G.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Darron_T._Smith&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Darron T. Smith (page does not exist)">Smith, Darron T.</a>, eds. (2004). <i><a href="/wiki/Black_and_Mormon" title="Black and Mormon">Black and Mormon</a></i>. Urbana: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-252-02947-X" title="Special:BookSources/0-252-02947-X"><bdi>0-252-02947-X</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Black+and+Mormon&amp;rft.place=Urbana&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.isbn=0-252-02947-X&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A collection of articles about <a href="/wiki/Black_people_and_Mormonism" title="Black people and Mormonism">Black people and Mormonism</a>, <a href="/wiki/Black_people_and_priesthood_(LDS)" class="mw-redirect" title="Black people and priesthood (LDS)">race and the LDS priesthood</a>, and the experience of <a href="/wiki/Black_Mormons" title="Black Mormons">Black Mormons</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFReeve2015" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/W._Paul_Reeve" title="W. Paul Reeve">Reeve, W. Paul</a> (27 February 2015). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Religion_of_a_Different_Color&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Religion of a Different Color (page does not exist)">Religion of a Different Color</a>: Race and the Mormon Struggle for Whiteness</i>. <a href="/wiki/Oxford_University_Press" title="Oxford University Press">Oxford University Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0199754076" title="Special:BookSources/978-0199754076"><bdi>978-0199754076</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Religion+of+a+Different+Color%3A+Race+and+the+Mormon+Struggle+for+Whiteness&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2015-02-27&amp;rft.isbn=978-0199754076&amp;rft.aulast=Reeve&amp;rft.aufirst=W.+Paul&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=mpYKBgAAQBAJ">[47]</a>
<ul><li>A study of Mormonism's struggle for status and recognition, in the context of how Protestants <a href="/wiki/Racialized" class="mw-redirect" title="Racialized">racialized</a> Mormons.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMueller2017" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Max_Perry_Mueller&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Max Perry Mueller (page does not exist)">Mueller, Max Perry</a> (11 September 2017). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Race_and_the_Making_of_the_Mormon_People&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Race and the Making of the Mormon People (page does not exist)">Race and the Making of the Mormon People</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Chapel_Hill,_NC" class="mw-redirect" title="Chapel Hill, NC">Chapel Hill, NC</a>: <a href="/wiki/The_University_of_North_Carolina_Press" class="mw-redirect" title="The University of North Carolina Press">The University of North Carolina Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1469636160" title="Special:BookSources/978-1469636160"><bdi>978-1469636160</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Race+and+the+Making+of+the+Mormon+People&amp;rft.place=Chapel+Hill%2C+NC&amp;rft.pub=The+University+of+North+Carolina+Press&amp;rft.date=2017-09-11&amp;rft.isbn=978-1469636160&amp;rft.aulast=Mueller&amp;rft.aufirst=Max+Perry&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=hB8wDwAAQBAJ">[48]</a>
<ul><li>A study of the history of evolving Mormon concepts of race.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFCarter1965" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Kate_B._Carter" title="Kate B. Carter">Carter, Kate B.</a> (1965). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Story_of_the_Negro_Pioneer&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Story of the Negro Pioneer (page does not exist)">The Story of the Negro Pioneer</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Daughters_of_Utah_Pioneers" title="Daughters of Utah Pioneers">Daughters of Utah Pioneers</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Story+of+the+Negro+Pioneer&amp;rft.pub=Daughters+of+Utah+Pioneers&amp;rft.date=1965&amp;rft.aulast=Carter&amp;rft.aufirst=Kate+B.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>The stories of <a href="/wiki/Black_Mormons" title="Black Mormons">Black Mormons</a> who <a href="/wiki/Mormon_pioneers" title="Mormon pioneers">emigrated to Utah</a>; such as <a href="/wiki/Jane_Manning_James" title="Jane Manning James">Jane Manning James</a>, <a href="/wiki/Elijah_Abel" title="Elijah Abel">Elijah Abel</a>, and <a href="/w/index.php?title=Liz_Flake_Rowan&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Liz Flake Rowan (page does not exist)">Liz Flake Rowan</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFGarrett2016" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Matthew_Garrett_(historian)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Matthew Garrett (historian) (page does not exist)">Garrett, Matthew</a> (31 December 2016). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Making_Lamanites&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Making Lamanites (page does not exist)">Making Lamanites</a>: Mormons, Native Americans, and the Indian Student Placement Program, 1947-2000</i>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_Utah_Press" title="University of Utah Press">University of Utah Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1607815693" title="Special:BookSources/978-1607815693"><bdi>978-1607815693</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Making+Lamanites%3A+Mormons%2C+Native+Americans%2C+and+the+Indian+Student+Placement+Program%2C+1947-2000&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Utah+Press&amp;rft.date=2016-12-31&amp;rft.isbn=978-1607815693&amp;rft.aulast=Garrett&amp;rft.aufirst=Matthew&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Study of the <a href="/wiki/Lamanite_Placement_Program" class="mw-redirect" title="Lamanite Placement Program">Lamanite Placement Program</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFHarrisBringhurst2015" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Matthew_L._Harris&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Matthew L. Harris (page does not exist)">Harris, Matthew L.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Newell_G._Bringhurst" title="Newell G. Bringhurst">Bringhurst, Newell G.</a>, eds. (15 November 2015). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Mormon_Church_and_Blacks&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Mormon Church and Blacks (page does not exist)">The Mormon Church and Blacks</a>: A Documentary History</i>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0252097843" title="Special:BookSources/978-0252097843"><bdi>978-0252097843</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Mormon+Church+and+Blacks%3A+A+Documentary+History&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=2015-11-15&amp;rft.isbn=978-0252097843&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=Pn20CgAAQBAJ">[49]</a>
<ul><li>A collection of thirty official or authoritative Church statements on the status of <a href="/wiki/African_Americans" title="African Americans">African Americans</a> in the LDS Church; with editorial comments and analysis, contextualizing each within the history of race and religion in the US.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBushMauss1984" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Lester_E._Bush" class="mw-redirect" title="Lester E. Bush">Bush, Lester E.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Armand_Mauss" title="Armand Mauss">Mauss, Armand L.</a>, eds. (1984). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Neither_White_Nor_Black&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Neither White Nor Black (page does not exist)">Neither White Nor Black</a>: Mormon Scholars Confront the Race Issue in a Universal Church</i>. <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0941214222" title="Special:BookSources/0941214222"><bdi>0941214222</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Neither+White+Nor+Black%3A+Mormon+Scholars+Confront+the+Race+Issue+in+a+Universal+Church&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=1984&amp;rft.isbn=0941214222&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://signaturebookslibrary.org/neither-white-nor-black/">[50]</a>
<ul><li>Collection of essays by the editors, and <a href="/wiki/Newell_G._Bringhurst" title="Newell G. Bringhurst">Newell G. Bringhurst</a>, most of which originally appeared in <i><a href="/wiki/Dialogue:_A_Journal_of_Mormon_Thought" title="Dialogue: A Journal of Mormon Thought">Dialogue</a></i>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMauss2003" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Armand_Mauss" title="Armand Mauss">Mauss, Armand L.</a> (2003). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=All_Abraham%27s_Children&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="All Abraham&#39;s Children (page does not exist)">All Abraham's Children</a>: Changing Mormon Conceptions of Race and Lineage</i>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0252028031" title="Special:BookSources/0252028031"><bdi>0252028031</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=All+Abraham%27s+Children%3A+Changing+Mormon+Conceptions+of+Race+and+Lineage&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.isbn=0252028031&amp;rft.aulast=Mauss&amp;rft.aufirst=Armand+L.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=7lXq9JfR_EYC">[51]</a>
<ul><li>Study of the evolution of traditional Mormon beliefs and practices concerning minorities; examining how members of the LDS Church have defined themselves and others in terms of racial lineages.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSoutherton2004" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Simon_G._Southerton" class="mw-redirect" title="Simon G. Southerton">Southerton, Simon G.</a> (2004). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Losing_a_Lost_Tribe&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Losing a Lost Tribe (page does not exist)">Losing a Lost Tribe</a>: Native Americans, DNA, and the Mormon Church</i>. <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Losing+a+Lost+Tribe%3A+Native+Americans%2C+DNA%2C+and+the+Mormon+Church&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.aulast=Southerton&amp;rft.aufirst=Simon+G.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A molecular biologist's explanation of DNA research on Native Americans and Polynesians origins, conflicting with standard LDS Church teachings.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Sexuality">Sexuality</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=25" title="Edit section: Sexuality"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1033289096"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Further information: <a href="/wiki/Sexuality_and_Mormonism" class="mw-redirect" title="Sexuality and Mormonism">Sexuality and Mormonism</a></div>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFChristofferson2017" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Tom_Christofferson&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Tom Christofferson (page does not exist)">Christofferson, Tom</a> (25 October 2017). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=That_We_May_Be_One&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="That We May Be One (page does not exist)">That We May Be One</a>: A Gay Mormon's Perspective on Faith and Family</i>. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Deseret_Book" class="mw-redirect" title="Deseret Book">Deseret Book</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1629723914" title="Special:BookSources/978-1629723914"><bdi>978-1629723914</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=That+We+May+Be+One%3A+A+Gay+Mormon%27s+Perspective+on+Faith+and+Family&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Book&amp;rft.date=2017-10-25&amp;rft.isbn=978-1629723914&amp;rft.aulast=Christofferson&amp;rft.aufirst=Tom&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Perspectives of a self-described "happy <a href="/wiki/Mormonism_and_homosexuality" class="mw-redirect" title="Mormonism and homosexuality">gay Mormon</a>"; a brother of LDS Apostle <a href="/wiki/D._Todd_Christofferson" title="D. Todd Christofferson">D. Todd Christofferson</a>, who left the Church, and then returned to it.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFQuinn2001" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/D._Michael_Quinn" title="D. Michael Quinn">Quinn, D. Michael</a> (20 June 2001) [1996]. <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Same-Sex_Dynamics_Among_Nineteenth-Century_Americans&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Same-Sex Dynamics Among Nineteenth-Century Americans (page does not exist)">Same-Sex Dynamics Among Nineteenth-Century Americans: A Mormon Example</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0252069587" title="Special:BookSources/0252069587"><bdi>0252069587</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Same-Sex+Dynamics+Among+Nineteenth-Century+Americans%3A+A+Mormon+Example&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=2001-06-20&amp;rft.isbn=0252069587&amp;rft.aulast=Quinn&amp;rft.aufirst=D.+Michael&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=UXVj398JvnsC">[52]</a>
<ul><li>Historical survey the tolerance of <a href="/wiki/Same-sex_relationships" class="mw-redirect" title="Same-sex relationships">same-sex relationships</a> by the LDS Church, before the onset of <a href="/wiki/Homophobia" title="Homophobia">homophobia</a> in the late 1950s.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFCorcoran1994" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Brent_Corcoran&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Brent Corcoran (page does not exist)">Corcoran, Brent</a>, ed. (1994). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Multiply_and_Replenish&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Multiply and Replenish (page does not exist)">Multiply and Replenish</a>: Mormon Essays on Sex and Family</i>. <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1560850507" title="Special:BookSources/1560850507"><bdi>1560850507</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Multiply+and+Replenish%3A+Mormon+Essays+on+Sex+and+Family&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.isbn=1560850507&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://signaturebookslibrary.org/6580/">[53]</a>
<ul><li>Collection of 13 essays on the evolution of Mormon attitudes about sexual practices (including <a href="/wiki/Homosexuality" title="Homosexuality">homosexuality</a>), <a href="/wiki/Polygamy" title="Polygamy">polygamy</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Celestial_marriage" title="Celestial marriage">celestial marriage</a>; authors include <a href="/wiki/Eugene_England" title="Eugene England">Eugene England</a> and <a href="/wiki/Levi_S._Peterson" title="Levi S. Peterson">Levi S. Peterson</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFKimball2002" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Spencer_W._Kimball" title="Spencer W. Kimball">Kimball, Spencer W.</a> (2002) [1969]. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Miracle_of_Forgiveness" title="The Miracle of Forgiveness">The Miracle of Forgiveness</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Deseret_Book_Company" title="Deseret Book Company">Deseret Book Company</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0884941922" title="Special:BookSources/0884941922"><bdi>0884941922</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Miracle+of+Forgiveness&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Book+Company&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.isbn=0884941922&amp;rft.aulast=Kimball&amp;rft.aufirst=Spencer+W.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/topics/disability/materials/braille">[54]</a>
<ul><li>Once popular work about the <a href="/wiki/Atonement_in_Christianity#The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints" class="mw-redirect" title="Atonement in Christianity">atonement</a>, <a href="/wiki/Repentance" title="Repentance">repentance</a>, and the <a href="/wiki/Plan_of_salvation_(Latter_Day_Saints)" class="mw-redirect" title="Plan of salvation (Latter Day Saints)">plan of salvation</a> by a, then, Apostle of the LDS Church; controversial for its treatment of masturbation, homosexuality, premarital sex, and rape.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Temples">Temples</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=26" title="Edit section: Temples"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFTalmage1912" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/James_E._Talmage" title="James E. Talmage">Talmage, James Edward</a> (1912). <i><a href="/wiki/The_House_of_the_Lord" title="The House of the Lord">The House of the Lord</a>: A Study of Holy Sanctuaries, Ancient and Modern</i>. <a href="/wiki/Deseret_News" title="Deseret News">Deseret News</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1499640358" title="Special:BookSources/1499640358"><bdi>1499640358</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+House+of+the+Lord%3A+A+Study+of+Holy+Sanctuaries%2C+Ancient+and+Modern&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+News&amp;rft.date=1912&amp;rft.isbn=1499640358&amp;rft.aulast=Talmage&amp;rft.aufirst=James+Edward&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/houseoflordstudy00talm">[55]</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/45149">[56]</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/stream/houseoflordstudy00talm#page/n7/mode/2up">[57]</a>
<ul><li>Published by the LDS Church, it discusses the doctrine, purpose, and importance of <a href="/wiki/Temple_(LDS_Church)" title="Temple (LDS Church)">temples</a>; the first book to contain photographs of the interiors of Mormon temples (including those in <a href="/wiki/Kirtland_Temple" title="Kirtland Temple">Kirtland</a>, <a href="/wiki/Nauvoo_Temple" title="Nauvoo Temple">Nauvoo</a>, <a href="/wiki/Salt_Lake_Temple" title="Salt Lake Temple">Salt Lake</a>, <a href="/wiki/St._George_Utah_Temple" title="St. George Utah Temple">St. George</a>, <a href="/wiki/Logan_Utah_Temple" title="Logan Utah Temple">Logan</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Manti_Utah_Temple" title="Manti Utah Temple">Manti</a>).</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPacker2007" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Boyd_K._Packer" title="Boyd K. Packer">Packer, Boyd K.</a> (1 October 2007) [1980]. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Holy_Temple" title="The Holy Temple">The Holy Temple</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Bookcraft" title="Bookcraft">Bookcraft</a>/<a href="/wiki/Deseret_Book_Company" title="Deseret Book Company">Deseret Book Company</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0884944119" title="Special:BookSources/978-0884944119"><bdi>978-0884944119</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Holy+Temple&amp;rft.pub=Bookcraft%2FDeseret+Book+Company&amp;rft.date=2007-10-01&amp;rft.isbn=978-0884944119&amp;rft.aulast=Packer&amp;rft.aufirst=Boyd+K.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>LDS Apostle discusses the doctrine and purpose of the temples, including an explanation of <a href="/wiki/Temple_(LDS_Church)#Entrance_requirements" title="Temple (LDS Church)">the entrance requirements</a>; also explains why Church teachings focus on <a href="/wiki/Baptism_for_the_dead#Genealogy_and_baptism" title="Baptism for the dead">family history and genealogy</a>; Deseret Book published an extended, illustrated version of the book in 2007.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Violence">Violence</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=27" title="Edit section: Violence"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1033289096"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Further information: <a href="/wiki/Mormonism_and_violence" title="Mormonism and violence">Mormonism and violence</a></div>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFDenton2003" class="citation book cs1">Denton, Sally (17 June 2003). <i><a href="/wiki/American_Massacre" title="American Massacre">American Massacre</a>: The Tragedy at Mountain Meadows, September 1857</i> (First&#160;ed.). New York: <a href="/wiki/Alfred_A._Knopf" title="Alfred A. Knopf">Alfred A. Knopf</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-375-41208-5" title="Special:BookSources/0-375-41208-5"><bdi>0-375-41208-5</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=American+Massacre%3A+The+Tragedy+at+Mountain+Meadows%2C+September+1857&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.edition=First&amp;rft.pub=Alfred+A.+Knopf&amp;rft.date=2003-06-17&amp;rft.isbn=0-375-41208-5&amp;rft.aulast=Denton&amp;rft.aufirst=Sally&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=YPyDmKq0t34C">[58]</a>
<ul><li>History of the <a href="/wiki/Mountain_Meadows_Massacre" title="Mountain Meadows Massacre">Mountain Meadows Massacre</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBagley2002" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Will_Bagley" title="Will Bagley">Bagley, Will</a> (2002). <i><a href="/wiki/Blood_of_the_Prophets" title="Blood of the Prophets">Blood of the Prophets</a>: Brigham Young and the Massacre at Mountain Meadows</i>. <a href="/wiki/Norman,_OK" class="mw-redirect" title="Norman, OK">Norman, OK</a>: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Oklahoma_Press" title="University of Oklahoma Press">University of Oklahoma Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-8061-3426-7" title="Special:BookSources/0-8061-3426-7"><bdi>0-8061-3426-7</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Blood+of+the+Prophets%3A+Brigham+Young+and+the+Massacre+at+Mountain+Meadows&amp;rft.place=Norman%2C+OK&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Oklahoma+Press&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.isbn=0-8061-3426-7&amp;rft.aulast=Bagley&amp;rft.aufirst=Will&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=eakce2R_mdkC">[59]</a>
<ul><li>History of the <a href="/wiki/Mountain_Meadows_Massacre" title="Mountain Meadows Massacre">Mountain Meadows Massacre</a>; the author posits that <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young" title="Brigham Young">Brigham Young</a> ordered the massacre.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFWalkerTurleyLeonard2011" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Ronald_W._Walker" title="Ronald W. Walker">Walker, Ronald W.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Richard_E._Turley_Jr." title="Richard E. Turley Jr.">Turley, Richard E.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Glen_M._Leonard" title="Glen M. Leonard">Leonard, Glen M.</a> (9 February 2011). <i><a href="/wiki/Massacre_at_Mountain_Meadows" title="Massacre at Mountain Meadows">Massacre at Mountain Meadows</a></i>. New York: <a href="/wiki/Oxford_University_Press" title="Oxford University Press">Oxford University Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0199747566" title="Special:BookSources/978-0199747566"><bdi>978-0199747566</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Massacre+at+Mountain+Meadows&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2011-02-09&amp;rft.isbn=978-0199747566&amp;rft.aulast=Walker&amp;rft.aufirst=Ronald+W.&amp;rft.au=Turley%2C+Richard+E.&amp;rft.au=Leonard%2C+Glen+M.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=nGEL80DBnccC">[60]</a>
<ul><li>Account of the <a href="/wiki/Mountain_Meadows_Massacre" title="Mountain Meadows Massacre">Mountain Meadows Massacre</a>; written drawing from LDS Church documents previously not available to scholars.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFTurleyWalker2009" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Richard_E._Turley_Jr." title="Richard E. Turley Jr.">Turley, Richard E. Jr.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Ronald_W._Walker" title="Ronald W. Walker">Walker, Ronald W.</a>, eds. (30 September 2009). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Mountain_Meadows_Massacre:_The_Andrew_Jenson_and_David_H._Morris_Collections&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Mountain Meadows Massacre: The Andrew Jenson and David H. Morris Collections (page does not exist)">Mountain Meadows Massacre: The Andrew Jenson and David H. Morris Collections</a></i>. Provo, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young_University_Press" title="Brigham Young University Press">Brigham Young University Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0842527231" title="Special:BookSources/978-0842527231"><bdi>978-0842527231</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mountain+Meadows+Massacre%3A+The+Andrew+Jenson+and+David+H.+Morris+Collections&amp;rft.place=Provo%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Brigham+Young+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2009-09-30&amp;rft.isbn=978-0842527231&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A reproduction of two of the collections uncovered during research for <i><a href="/wiki/Massacre_at_Mountain_Meadows" title="Massacre at Mountain Meadows">Massacre at Mountain Meadows</a></i>; one compiled in the 1890s by <a href="/wiki/Andrew_Jenson" title="Andrew Jenson">Andrew Jenson</a>, the second a decade later by <a href="/w/index.php?title=David_H._Morris&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="David H. Morris (page does not exist)">David H. Morris</a> (1858–1937), an attorney and judge in <a href="/wiki/St._George,_Utah" title="St. George, Utah">St. George, Utah</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFKrakauer2004" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Jon_Krakauer" title="Jon Krakauer">Krakauer, Jon</a> (2004). <i><a href="/wiki/Under_the_Banner_of_Heaven" title="Under the Banner of Heaven">Under the Banner of Heaven</a>: A Story of Violent Faith</i>. <a href="/wiki/Knopf_Doubleday_Publishing_Group" class="mw-redirect" title="Knopf Doubleday Publishing Group">Knopf Doubleday Publishing Group</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781400078998" title="Special:BookSources/9781400078998"><bdi>9781400078998</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Under+the+Banner+of+Heaven%3A+A+Story+of+Violent+Faith&amp;rft.pub=Knopf+Doubleday+Publishing+Group&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.isbn=9781400078998&amp;rft.aulast=Krakauer&amp;rft.aufirst=Jon&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/isbn_9780965778404">[61]</a>
<ul><li>Investigation of the histories of the LDS Church, and the crimes of a small splinter group called <a href="/wiki/List_of_Mormon_fundamentalist_leaders#School_of_the_Prophets" title="List of Mormon fundamentalist leaders">the School of Prophets</a>; also examines the ideologies of both the LDS Church and the <a href="/wiki/Fundamentalist_Mormon" class="mw-redirect" title="Fundamentalist Mormon">fundamentalist Mormon</a> polygamous groups, such as the <a href="/wiki/FLDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="FLDS Church">FLDS Church</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFTurley1992" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Richard_E._Turley_Jr." title="Richard E. Turley Jr.">Turley, Richard E. Jr.</a> (1992). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Victims:_The_LDS_Church_and_the_Mark_Hofmann_Case&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Victims: The LDS Church and the Mark Hofmann Case (page does not exist)">Victims: The LDS Church and the Mark Hofmann Case</a></i>. Urbana: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0252018850" title="Special:BookSources/0252018850"><bdi>0252018850</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Victims%3A+The+LDS+Church+and+the+Mark+Hofmann+Case&amp;rft.place=Urbana&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.isbn=0252018850&amp;rft.aulast=Turley&amp;rft.aufirst=Richard+E.+Jr.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=IqrDDrWR_X4C">[62]</a>
<ul><li>The story of the <a href="/wiki/Mark_Hofmann" title="Mark Hofmann">Mark Hofmann</a> case, told from the perspectives of the murder victims and the LDS Church; written by an <a href="/wiki/Assistant_Church_Historian" class="mw-redirect" title="Assistant Church Historian">Assistant Church Historian</a> with church leaders' support and access to interviews, diaries, journals, memoranda, and other records.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Women">Women</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=28" title="Edit section: Women"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1033289096"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Further information: <a href="/wiki/Mormonism_and_women" title="Mormonism and women">Mormonism and women</a></div>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation book cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/manual/daughters-in-my-kingdom-the-history-and-work-of-relief-society"><i>Daughters in My Kingdom: The History and Work of Relief Society</i></a>. <a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Christopher_Publishing_House&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Christopher Publishing House (page does not exist)">The Christopher Publishing House</a>. 2011<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">8 January</span> 2018</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Daughters+in+My+Kingdom%3A+The+History+and+Work+of+Relief+Society&amp;rft.pub=The+Christopher+Publishing+House&amp;rft.date=2011&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Fstudy%2Fmanual%2Fdaughters-in-my-kingdom-the-history-and-work-of-relief-society&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Comprehensive history of the <a href="/wiki/Relief_Society" title="Relief Society">Relief Society</a>, produced by the <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a>; written by <a href="/wiki/Susan_W._Tanner" title="Susan W. Tanner">Susan W. Tanner</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFHanks1992" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Maxine_Hanks" class="mw-redirect" title="Maxine Hanks">Hanks, Maxine</a>, ed. (1992). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Women_and_Authority&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Women and Authority (page does not exist)">Women and Authority</a>: Re-emerging Mormon Feminism</i>. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1560850140" title="Special:BookSources/1560850140"><bdi>1560850140</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Women+and+Authority%3A+Re-emerging+Mormon+Feminism&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.isbn=1560850140&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://signaturebookslibrary.org/840/">[63]</a>
<ul><li>Collection of essays compiled by a <a href="/wiki/Mormon_feminist" class="mw-redirect" title="Mormon feminist">Mormon feminist</a> <a href="/wiki/Feminist_theologian" class="mw-redirect" title="Feminist theologian">theologian</a>, exploring issues of <a href="/wiki/Feminist_spirituality" class="mw-redirect" title="Feminist spirituality">women's spirituality</a> and authority within the Mormon church; the Mormon concept of a <a href="/wiki/Heavenly_Mother_(Mormonism)" title="Heavenly Mother (Mormonism)">mother in heaven</a>; and the relationship of <a href="/wiki/Mormonism_and_women#Laying_on_of_hands_and_Priesthood" title="Mormonism and women">Mormon women and priesthood</a>. Contributors include <a href="/wiki/Linda_King_Newell" title="Linda King Newell">Linda King Newell</a>, <a href="/wiki/Meg_Wheatley" title="Meg Wheatley">Meg Wheatley</a>, <a href="/wiki/Todd_Compton" title="Todd Compton">Todd Compton</a>, <a href="/wiki/Lavina_Fielding_Anderson" title="Lavina Fielding Anderson">Lavina Fielding Anderson</a>, <a href="/wiki/Carol_Lynn_Pearson" title="Carol Lynn Pearson">Carol Lynn Pearson</a>, <a href="/wiki/D._Michael_Quinn" title="D. Michael Quinn">D. Michael Quinn</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Margaret_Merrill_Toscano" class="mw-redirect" title="Margaret Merrill Toscano">Margaret Merrill Toscano</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBrooksSteenblikWheelwright2015" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Joanna_Brooks" title="Joanna Brooks">Brooks, Joanna</a>; <a href="/wiki/Rachel_Hunt_Steenblik" title="Rachel Hunt Steenblik">Steenblik, Rachel Hunt</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Hannah_Wheelwright&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Hannah Wheelwright (page does not exist)">Wheelwright, Hannah</a>, eds. (2 November 2015). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Mormon_Feminism:_Essential_Writings&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Mormon Feminism: Essential Writings (page does not exist)">Mormon Feminism: Essential Writings</a></i>. New York, NY: <a href="/wiki/Oxford_University_Press" title="Oxford University Press">Oxford University Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0190248031" title="Special:BookSources/978-0190248031"><bdi>978-0190248031</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormon+Feminism%3A+Essential+Writings&amp;rft.place=New+York%2C+NY&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2015-11-02&amp;rft.isbn=978-0190248031&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=zohmCgAAQBAJ">[64]</a>
<ul><li>A collection of writings and speeches from four decades of the modern <a href="/wiki/Mormon_feminist" class="mw-redirect" title="Mormon feminist">Mormon feminist</a> movement; a guide to understand the history of gender in Mormonism. Contributors include <a href="/wiki/Claudia_Lauper_Bushman" title="Claudia Lauper Bushman">Claudia Lauper Bushman</a>, <a href="/wiki/Sonia_Johnson" title="Sonia Johnson">Sonia Johnson</a>, <a href="/wiki/Linda_King_Newell" title="Linda King Newell">Linda King Newell</a>, <a href="/wiki/Carol_Cornwall_Madsen" title="Carol Cornwall Madsen">Carol Cornwall Madsen</a>, <a href="/wiki/Laurel_Thatcher_Ulrich" title="Laurel Thatcher Ulrich">Laurel Thatcher Ulrich</a>, <a href="/wiki/Mary_Lythgoe_Bradford" title="Mary Lythgoe Bradford">Mary Lythgoe Bradford</a>, <a href="/wiki/Margaret_Merrill_Toscano" class="mw-redirect" title="Margaret Merrill Toscano">Margaret Merrill Toscano</a>, <a href="/wiki/Linda_Sillitoe" title="Linda Sillitoe">Linda Sillitoe</a>, <a href="/wiki/Carol_Lynn_Pearson" title="Carol Lynn Pearson">Carol Lynn Pearson</a>, <a href="/wiki/Janice_Merrill_Allred" title="Janice Merrill Allred">Janice Merrill Allred</a>, <a href="/wiki/Chieko_Nishimura_Okazaki" class="mw-redirect" title="Chieko Nishimura Okazaki">Chieko Nishimura Okazaki</a>, <a href="/wiki/Lisa_Butterworth" class="mw-redirect" title="Lisa Butterworth">Lisa Butterworth</a>, <a href="/wiki/Valerie_Hudson_Cassler" class="mw-redirect" title="Valerie Hudson Cassler">Valerie Hudson Cassler</a>, <a href="/wiki/Neylan_McBaine" title="Neylan McBaine">Neylan McBaine</a>, <a href="/wiki/Kate_Kelly_(feminist)" title="Kate Kelly (feminist)">Kate Kelly</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Lani_Wendt_Young" title="Lani Wendt Young">Lani Wendt Young</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFShepherdAndersonShepherd2015" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Gordon_Shepherd_(author)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Gordon Shepherd (author) (page does not exist)">Shepherd, Gordon</a>; <a href="/wiki/Lavina_Fielding_Anderson" title="Lavina Fielding Anderson">Anderson, Lavina Fielding</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Gary_Shepherd_(author)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Gary Shepherd (author) (page does not exist)">Shepherd, Gary</a>, eds. (29 July 2015). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Voices_for_Equality&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Voices for Equality (page does not exist)">Voices for Equality</a>: Ordain Women and Resurgent Mormon Feminism</i>. Salt Lake City: <a href="/w/index.php?title=Greg_Kofford_Books&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Greg Kofford Books (page does not exist)">Greg Kofford Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1589587588" title="Special:BookSources/978-1589587588"><bdi>978-1589587588</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Voices+for+Equality%3A+Ordain+Women+and+Resurgent+Mormon+Feminism&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.pub=Greg+Kofford+Books&amp;rft.date=2015-07-29&amp;rft.isbn=978-1589587588&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A collection of articles by twenty-five scholars and activists on the issue of <a href="/wiki/Gender_equality" title="Gender equality">gender equality</a> in the LDS Church; examines the high public visibility of the <a href="/wiki/Ordain_Women" title="Ordain Women">Ordain Women</a> movement, and details the theological debates about gender and priesthood authority.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFDavidsonDerr2013" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Karen_Lynn_Davidson" title="Karen Lynn Davidson">Davidson, Karen Lynn</a>; <a href="/wiki/Jill_Mulvay_Derr" title="Jill Mulvay Derr">Derr, Jill Mulvay</a> (2013). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Eliza:_The_Life_and_Faith_of_Eliza_R._Snow&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Eliza: The Life and Faith of Eliza R. Snow (page does not exist)">Eliza: The Life and Faith of Eliza R. Snow</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Deseret_Book" class="mw-redirect" title="Deseret Book">Deseret Book</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1609089023" title="Special:BookSources/978-1609089023"><bdi>978-1609089023</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Eliza%3A+The+Life+and+Faith+of+Eliza+R.+Snow&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Book&amp;rft.date=2013&amp;rft.isbn=978-1609089023&amp;rft.aulast=Davidson&amp;rft.aufirst=Karen+Lynn&amp;rft.au=Derr%2C+Jill+Mulvay&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Biography of <a href="/wiki/Eliza_R._Snow" title="Eliza R. Snow">Eliza R. Snow</a>, 2nd President of the <a href="/wiki/Relief_Society" title="Relief Society">Relief Society</a> (from 1866 to 1887).</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBradley2005" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Martha_S._Bradley-Evans" class="mw-redirect" title="Martha S. Bradley-Evans">Bradley, Martha Sonntag</a> (18 October 2005). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Pedestals_and_Podiums&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Pedestals and Podiums (page does not exist)">Pedestals and Podiums</a>: Utah Women, Religious Authority, and Equal Rights</i>. <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1560851899" title="Special:BookSources/1560851899"><bdi>1560851899</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Pedestals+and+Podiums%3A+Utah+Women%2C+Religious+Authority%2C+and+Equal+Rights&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=2005-10-18&amp;rft.isbn=1560851899&amp;rft.aulast=Bradley&amp;rft.aufirst=Martha+Sonntag&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A survey of the involvement of Mormons in the <a href="/wiki/Women%27s_movement" class="mw-redirect" title="Women&#39;s movement">women's movement</a>  (including early Utah leaders such as <a href="/wiki/Emmeline_B._Wells" title="Emmeline B. Wells">Emmeline B. Wells</a>) and the shift to championing a more conservative view of women's roles; culminating in the concerted effort to defeat the <a href="/wiki/Equal_Rights_Amendment" title="Equal Rights Amendment">Equal Rights Amendment</a> (ERA).</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFUlrich2017" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Laurel_Thatcher_Ulrich" title="Laurel Thatcher Ulrich">Ulrich, Laurel Thatcher</a> (10 January 2017). <i><a href="/wiki/A_House_Full_of_Females" title="A House Full of Females">A House Full of Females</a>: Plural Marriage and Women's Rights in Early Mormonism, 1835-1870</i>. <a href="/wiki/Knopf_Doubleday_Publishing_Group" class="mw-redirect" title="Knopf Doubleday Publishing Group">Knopf Doubleday Publishing Group</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0307594907" title="Special:BookSources/978-0307594907"><bdi>978-0307594907</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+House+Full+of+Females%3A+Plural+Marriage+and+Women%27s+Rights+in+Early+Mormonism%2C+1835-1870&amp;rft.pub=Knopf+Doubleday+Publishing+Group&amp;rft.date=2017-01-10&amp;rft.isbn=978-0307594907&amp;rft.aulast=Ulrich&amp;rft.aufirst=Laurel+Thatcher&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=drRKDwAAQBAJ">[65]</a>
<ul><li>A history of marriage and family life among first-generation Latter-day Saints; focused on the world of early Mormon women— pieced together through diaries, letters, albums, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Minute-books&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Minute-books (page does not exist)">minute-books</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Quilts" class="mw-redirect" title="Quilts">quilts</a>— their practice of "plural marriage," and their attainment of <a href="/wiki/Female_suffrage" class="mw-redirect" title="Female suffrage">female suffrage</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFHolbrookBowman2016" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Kate_Holbrook" title="Kate Holbrook">Holbrook, Kate</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Matthew_Bowman_(author)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Matthew Bowman (author) (page does not exist)">Bowman, Matthew Burton</a> (30 May 2016). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Women_and_Mormonism:_Historical_and_Contemporary_Perspectives&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Women and Mormonism: Historical and Contemporary Perspectives (page does not exist)">Women and Mormonism: Historical and Contemporary Perspectives</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_Utah_Press" title="University of Utah Press">University of Utah Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1607814771" title="Special:BookSources/978-1607814771"><bdi>978-1607814771</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Women+and+Mormonism%3A+Historical+and+Contemporary+Perspectives&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Utah+Press&amp;rft.date=2016-05-30&amp;rft.isbn=978-1607814771&amp;rft.aulast=Holbrook&amp;rft.aufirst=Kate&amp;rft.au=Bowman%2C+Matthew+Burton&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A collection of essays on the experience of LDS women in a predominantly male-led church; topics include <a href="/wiki/Jane_Manning_James" title="Jane Manning James">Jane Manning James</a>, <a href="/wiki/Mother_in_Heaven" class="mw-redirect" title="Mother in Heaven">Mother in Heaven</a>, and the intersecting paths of <a href="/wiki/Mormon_feminism" title="Mormon feminism">Mormon</a> and <a href="/wiki/Christian_feminism" title="Christian feminism">Roman Catholic feminists</a>; contributors include lay members and scholars, including both LDS and non-LDS viewpoints: <a href="/wiki/Catherine_Brekus" title="Catherine Brekus">Catherine Brekus</a>, <a href="/wiki/Laurel_Thatcher_Ulrich" title="Laurel Thatcher Ulrich">Laurel Thatcher Ulrich</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Rachel_Cope&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Rachel Cope (page does not exist)">Rachel Cope</a>, <a href="/wiki/Jennifer_Reeder" title="Jennifer Reeder">Jennifer Reeder</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Kristine_Wright&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Kristine Wright (page does not exist)">Kristine Wright</a>, <a href="/wiki/Jonathan_Stapley" class="mw-redirect" title="Jonathan Stapley">Jonathan Stapley</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Susanna_Morrill&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Susanna Morrill (page does not exist)">Susanna Morrill</a>, <a href="/wiki/Quincy_D._Newell" title="Quincy D. Newell">Quincy D. Newell</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Amanda_Hendrix-Komoto&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Amanda Hendrix-Komoto (page does not exist)">Amanda Hendrix-Komoto</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Rebekah_Ryan_Clark&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Rebekah Ryan Clark (page does not exist)">Rebekah Ryan Clark</a>, <a href="/wiki/David_E._Campbell_(academic)" class="mw-redirect" title="David E. Campbell (academic)">David E. Campbell</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Carine_Decoo-Vanwelkenhuysen&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Carine Decoo-Vanwelkenhuysen (page does not exist)">Carine Decoo-Vanwelkenhuysen</a>, <a href="/wiki/Melissa_Wei-Tsing_Inouye" title="Melissa Wei-Tsing Inouye">Melissa Wei-Tsing Inouye</a>, <a href="/wiki/Jennifer_Finlayson-Fife" title="Jennifer Finlayson-Fife">Jennifer Finlayson-Fife</a>, <a href="/wiki/Claudia_Bushman" class="mw-redirect" title="Claudia Bushman">Claudia Bushman</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=P._Jane_Hafen&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="P. Jane Hafen (page does not exist)">P. Jane Hafen</a>, <a href="/wiki/Neylan_McBaine" title="Neylan McBaine">Neylan McBaine</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Aimee_Evans_Hickman&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Aimee Evans Hickman (page does not exist)">Aimee Evans Hickman</a>, and <a href="/w/index.php?title=Mary_Farrell_Bednarowski&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Mary Farrell Bednarowski (page does not exist)">Mary Farrell Bednarowski</a>.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Criticisms">Criticisms</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=29" title="Edit section: Criticisms"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1033289096"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Further information: <a href="/wiki/Anti-Mormonism" title="Anti-Mormonism">Anti-Mormonism</a> and <a href="/wiki/Criticism_of_the_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints" title="Criticism of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints">Criticism of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints</a></div>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFHowe1834" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Eber_D._Howe" title="Eber D. Howe">Howe, Eber D.</a> (1834). <i><a href="/wiki/Mormonism_Unvailed" title="Mormonism Unvailed">Mormonism Unvailed</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Painesville" class="mw-redirect" title="Painesville">Painesville</a>: <a href="/wiki/Self-published" class="mw-redirect" title="Self-published">self-published</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormonism+Unvailed&amp;rft.place=Painesville&amp;rft.pub=self-published&amp;rft.date=1834&amp;rft.aulast=Howe&amp;rft.aufirst=Eber+D.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/mormonismunvaile00howe">[66]</a>
<ul><li>Contemporary <a href="/wiki/Expos%C3%A9_(journalism)" class="mw-redirect" title="Exposé (journalism)">exposé</a> of early Mormonism; considered to be the first <a href="/wiki/Anti-Mormon" class="mw-redirect" title="Anti-Mormon">anti-Mormon</a> book; republished as <i>History of the Mormons</i> in 1840.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBeckwithMosserOwen2010" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Francis_Beckwith" class="mw-redirect" title="Francis Beckwith">Beckwith, Francis</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Carl_Mosser&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Carl Mosser (page does not exist)">Mosser, Carl</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Paul_Owen_(author)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Paul Owen (author) (page does not exist)">Owen, Paul</a>, eds. (2010) [2002]. <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_New_Mormon_Challenge&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The New Mormon Challenge (page does not exist)">The New Mormon Challenge</a>: Responding to the Latest Defenses of a Fast-Growing Movement</i>. <a href="/wiki/Zondervan" title="Zondervan">Zondervan</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0310231943" title="Special:BookSources/978-0310231943"><bdi>978-0310231943</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+New+Mormon+Challenge%3A+Responding+to+the+Latest+Defenses+of+a+Fast-Growing+Movement&amp;rft.pub=Zondervan&amp;rft.date=2010&amp;rft.isbn=978-0310231943&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=MLrugt3clU4C">[67]</a>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Evangelical_Christian" class="mw-redirect" title="Evangelical Christian">Evangelical Christian</a> response to the challenge of <a href="/wiki/Mormon_apologetics" class="mw-redirect" title="Mormon apologetics">Mormon apologetics</a>; scholarly effort to rebut Mormon truth claims.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPaulson2000" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Matthew_A._Paulson&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Matthew A. Paulson (page does not exist)">Paulson, Matthew A.</a> (5 September 2000). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Breaking_the_Mormon_Code&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Breaking the Mormon Code (page does not exist)">Breaking the Mormon Code</a></i>. <a href="/w/index.php?title=WingSpan_Press&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="WingSpan Press (page does not exist)">WingSpan Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1595940677" title="Special:BookSources/1595940677"><bdi>1595940677</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Breaking+the+Mormon+Code&amp;rft.pub=WingSpan+Press&amp;rft.date=2000-09-05&amp;rft.isbn=1595940677&amp;rft.aulast=Paulson&amp;rft.aufirst=Matthew+A.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=Pbi_OfkPhzwC">[68]</a>
<ul><li>Critique of <a href="/wiki/FARMS" class="mw-redirect" title="FARMS">FARMS</a> scholarship; by a <a href="/wiki/CARM" class="mw-redirect" title="CARM">CARM</a> researcher.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFGivens2013" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Terryl_Givens" title="Terryl Givens">Givens, Terryl</a> (31 January 2013) [1997]. <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Viper_on_the_Hearth&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Viper on the Hearth (page does not exist)">The Viper on the Hearth</a>: Mormons, Myths, and the Construction of Heresy</i> (Updated&#160;ed.). <a href="/wiki/Oxford_University_Press_USA" class="mw-redirect" title="Oxford University Press USA">Oxford University Press USA</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0199933808" title="Special:BookSources/978-0199933808"><bdi>978-0199933808</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Viper+on+the+Hearth%3A+Mormons%2C+Myths%2C+and+the+Construction+of+Heresy&amp;rft.edition=Updated&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press+USA&amp;rft.date=2013-01-31&amp;rft.isbn=978-0199933808&amp;rft.aulast=Givens&amp;rft.aufirst=Terryl&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=CjnTa-oisL4C">[69]</a>
<ul><li>Examination of the presence and reception of the <a href="/wiki/Latter_Day_Saints_in_popular_culture" title="Latter Day Saints in popular culture">Mormon image in contemporary culture</a>; how nineteenth- and twentieth-century American writers frequently cast the Mormon as a stock villains in fiction; the updated edition has an expanded final chapter, on the Mormon presence in contemporary American culture, discussing the musical, <i><a href="/wiki/The_Book_of_Mormon_(musical)" title="The Book of Mormon (musical)">The Book of Mormon</a></i>, and the political campaigns of <a href="/wiki/Public_image_of_Mitt_Romney#Religion" title="Public image of Mitt Romney">Mitt Romney</a> and <a href="/wiki/Jon_Huntsman_presidential_campaign,_2012" class="mw-redirect" title="Jon Huntsman presidential campaign, 2012">Jon Huntsman</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFLauniusThatcher1998" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Roger_D._Launius" title="Roger D. Launius">Launius, Roger D.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Linda_Thatcher&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Linda Thatcher (page does not exist)">Thatcher, Linda</a>, eds. (1 April 1998). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Differing_Visions&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Differing Visions (page does not exist)">Differing Visions</a>: Dissenters in Mormon History</i>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0252067312" title="Special:BookSources/0252067312"><bdi>0252067312</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Differing+Visions%3A+Dissenters+in+Mormon+History&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=1998-04-01&amp;rft.isbn=0252067312&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=Gbdr5dF6eo4C">[70]</a>
<ul><li>An analysis of the careers of 18 converts who later left the LDS church— <a href="/wiki/David_Whitmer" title="David Whitmer">David Whitmer</a>, <a href="/wiki/John_Corrill" title="John Corrill">John Corrill</a>, <a href="/wiki/William_E._McLellin" title="William E. McLellin">William E. McLellin</a>, <a href="/wiki/Francis_Gladden_Bishop" class="mw-redirect" title="Francis Gladden Bishop">Francis Gladden Bishop</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=James_Colin_Brewster&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="James Colin Brewster (page does not exist)">James Colin Brewster</a>, <a href="/wiki/William_B._Smith" class="mw-redirect" title="William B. Smith">William B. Smith</a>, <a href="/wiki/Alpheus_Cutler" title="Alpheus Cutler">Alpheus Cutler</a>, <a href="/wiki/Stephen_Post" title="Stephen Post">Stephen Post</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=James_Dove&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="James Dove (page does not exist)">James</a> and <a href="/w/index.php?title=George_Dove_(Morrisite)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="George Dove (Morrisite) (page does not exist)">George Dove</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Henry_W._Lawrence&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Henry W. Lawrence (page does not exist)">Henry W. Lawrence</a>, <a href="/wiki/Frank_J._Cannon" title="Frank J. Cannon">Frank J. Cannon</a>, <a href="/wiki/Joseph_W._Musser" class="mw-redirect" title="Joseph W. Musser">Joseph W. Musser</a>, <a href="/wiki/Fawn_McKay_Brodie" class="mw-redirect" title="Fawn McKay Brodie">Fawn McKay Brodie</a>, <a href="/wiki/Maurine_Whipple" title="Maurine Whipple">Maurine Whipple</a>, <a href="/wiki/Richard_Price" title="Richard Price">Richard Price</a>, <a href="/wiki/Jerald_and_Sandra_Tanner" title="Jerald and Sandra Tanner">Jerald and Sandra Tanner</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Sonia_Johnson" title="Sonia Johnson">Sonia Johnson</a>; contributors include <a href="/wiki/Richard_N._Holzapfel" title="Richard N. Holzapfel">Richard N. Holzapfel</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=John_S._McCormick&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="John S. McCormick (page does not exist)">John S. McCormick</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Kenneth_M._Godfrey&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Kenneth M. Godfrey (page does not exist)">Kenneth M. Godfrey</a>, <a href="/wiki/William_D._Russell_(historian)" title="William D. Russell (historian)">William D. Russell</a>, <a href="/wiki/Dan_Vogel" title="Dan Vogel">Dan Vogel</a>, and <a href="/w/index.php?title=Jessie_L._Embry&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Jessie L. Embry (page does not exist)">Jessie L. Embry</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBurningham2011" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Kay_Burningham&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Kay Burningham (page does not exist)">Burningham, Kay</a> (2011). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=An_American_Fraud&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="An American Fraud (page does not exist)">An American Fraud</a>: One Lawyer's Case Against Mormonism</i>. <a href="/w/index.php?title=AmicaVeritatis&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="AmicaVeritatis (page does not exist)">AmicaVeritatis</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0615465890" title="Special:BookSources/978-0615465890"><bdi>978-0615465890</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=An+American+Fraud%3A+One+Lawyer%27s+Case+Against+Mormonism&amp;rft.pub=AmicaVeritatis&amp;rft.date=2011&amp;rft.isbn=978-0615465890&amp;rft.aulast=Burningham&amp;rft.aufirst=Kay&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A chronicle of the author's journey out of the LSD faith; and an exposé by a civil trial attorney, alleging fraud committed by generations of Mormon Leaders— misrepresentations resulting in damages (political, environmental, and psycho-social) to believers; presents The Book of Mormon as a 19th-century work of fiction</li></ul></li></ul>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Relations_to_other_faiths">Relations to other faiths</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=30" title="Edit section: Relations to other faiths"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1033289096"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Further information: <a href="/wiki/Mormonism#Relations_to_other_faiths" title="Mormonism">Mormonism §&#160;Relations_to_other_faiths</a></div>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPalmerKeller1997" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Spencer_J._Palmer" title="Spencer J. Palmer">Palmer, Spencer J.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Roger_R._Keller" title="Roger R. Keller">Keller, Roger R.</a> (1997) [1988]. <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Religions_of_the_World&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Religions of the World (page does not exist)">Religions of the World</a>: A Latter-day Saint View</i> (2nd general revised and enlarged&#160;ed.). Provo, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young_University" title="Brigham Young University">Brigham Young University</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0842523502" title="Special:BookSources/0842523502"><bdi>0842523502</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Religions+of+the+World%3A+A+Latter-day+Saint+View&amp;rft.place=Provo%2C+Utah&amp;rft.edition=2nd+general+revised+and+enlarged&amp;rft.pub=Brigham+Young+University&amp;rft.date=1997&amp;rft.isbn=0842523502&amp;rft.aulast=Palmer&amp;rft.aufirst=Spencer+J.&amp;rft.au=Keller%2C+Roger+R.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Overviews a variety of the world's religions with commentary following each one; offering <a href="/wiki/Mormonism#Relationship_with_other_faiths" title="Mormonism">a LDS perspective</a>, noting beliefs held in common, and divergences.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPalmer2002" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Spencer_J._Palmer" title="Spencer J. Palmer">Palmer, Spencer J.</a>, ed. (2002) [1983]. <i>Mormons and Muslims: Spiritual Foundations and Modern Manifestations</i> (updated and revised&#160;ed.). <a href="/wiki/Religious_Studies_Center" title="Religious Studies Center">Religious Studies Center</a>, <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young_University" title="Brigham Young University">Brigham Young University</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1591560233" title="Special:BookSources/1591560233"><bdi>1591560233</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormons+and+Muslims%3A+Spiritual+Foundations+and+Modern+Manifestations&amp;rft.edition=updated+and+revised&amp;rft.pub=Religious+Studies+Center%2C+Brigham+Young+University&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.isbn=1591560233&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Collection of papers from a BYU <a href="/wiki/Symposium" title="Symposium">symposium</a> in October 1981; focuses on parallels, similarities, and contrasts with <a href="/wiki/Islam" title="Islam">Islam</a> and the LDS. Revised edition includes new material by <a href="/wiki/Arnold_H._Green" title="Arnold H. Green">Arnold H. Green</a> and <a href="/wiki/Daniel_C._Peterson" title="Daniel C. Peterson">Daniel C. Peterson</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFThomas2016" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/John_Christopher_Thomas" title="John Christopher Thomas">Thomas, John Christopher</a> (31 March 2016). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=A_Pentecostal_Reads_the_Book_of_Mormon&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="A Pentecostal Reads the Book of Mormon (page does not exist)">A Pentecostal Reads the Book of Mormon</a>: A Literary and Theological Introduction</i>. <a href="/w/index.php?title=CPT_Press&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="CPT Press (page does not exist)">CPT Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1935931553" title="Special:BookSources/978-1935931553"><bdi>978-1935931553</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+Pentecostal+Reads+the+Book+of+Mormon%3A+A+Literary+and+Theological+Introduction&amp;rft.pub=CPT+Press&amp;rft.date=2016-03-31&amp;rft.isbn=978-1935931553&amp;rft.aulast=Thomas&amp;rft.aufirst=John+Christopher&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A monograph by a <a href="/wiki/Pentecostal" class="mw-redirect" title="Pentecostal">Pentecostal</a> <a href="/wiki/New_Testament" title="New Testament">New Testament</a> scholar offering an irenic, critical reading of the Book of Mormon; utilizing <a href="/wiki/Narrative_analysis" class="mw-redirect" title="Narrative analysis">narrative analysis</a>, it investigates of the book's overall structure; presents an extended reading focused on its literary and theological dimensions; and traces the book's reception amongst followers and opponents alike.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Missionary_work">Missionary work</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=31" title="Edit section: Missionary work"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1033289096"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Further information: <a href="/wiki/LDS_missionaries" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS missionaries">LDS missionaries</a></div>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFNeilsonWoods2012" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Reid_L._Neilson" title="Reid L. Neilson">Neilson, Reid L.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Fred_E._Woods" class="mw-redirect" title="Fred E. Woods">Woods, Fred E.</a>, eds. (2012). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Go_Ye_Into_All_the_World&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Go Ye Into All the World (page does not exist)">Go Ye Into All the World</a>: The Growth &amp; Development of Mormon Missionary Work</i>. <a href="/wiki/Religious_Studies_Center" title="Religious Studies Center">Religious Studies Center</a>, <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young_University" title="Brigham Young University">Brigham Young University</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0842528214" title="Special:BookSources/978-0842528214"><bdi>978-0842528214</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Go+Ye+Into+All+the+World%3A+The+Growth+%26+Development+of+Mormon+Missionary+Work&amp;rft.pub=Religious+Studies+Center%2C+Brigham+Young+University&amp;rft.date=2012&amp;rft.isbn=978-0842528214&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A collection of essays bringing some of the stories of <a href="/wiki/LDS_missionaries" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS missionaries">missionaries of the LDS Church</a> to the study of Mormon <a href="/wiki/Missiology" title="Missiology">missiology</a>; the result of a BYU Church History Symposium.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Branches_and_sects">Branches and sects</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=32" title="Edit section: Branches and sects"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1033289096"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Further information: <a href="/wiki/List_of_denominations_in_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement" title="List of denominations in the Latter Day Saint movement">List of denominations in the Latter Day Saint movement</a></div>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFShields1990" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Steven_L._Shields&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Steven L. Shields (page does not exist)">Shields, Steven L.</a> (1990) [1975]. <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Divergent_Paths_of_the_Restoration&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Divergent Paths of the Restoration (page does not exist)">Divergent Paths of the Restoration</a>: A History of the Latter Day Saint Movement</i> (fourth, revised and enlarged&#160;ed.). <a href="/wiki/Bountiful,_Utah" title="Bountiful, Utah">Bountiful, Utah</a>: <a href="/w/index.php?title=Restoration_Research&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Restoration Research (page does not exist)">Restoration Research</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0830905693" title="Special:BookSources/0830905693"><bdi>0830905693</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Divergent+Paths+of+the+Restoration%3A+A+History+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+Movement&amp;rft.place=Bountiful%2C+Utah&amp;rft.edition=fourth%2C+revised+and+enlarged&amp;rft.pub=Restoration+Research&amp;rft.date=1990&amp;rft.isbn=0830905693&amp;rft.aulast=Shields&amp;rft.aufirst=Steven+L.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Discusses the histories and theologies of more than a hundred different churches, organizations, and individuals in the <a href="/wiki/Latter_Day_Saint_movement" title="Latter Day Saint movement">Latter Day Saint movement</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBringhurstHamer2007" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Newell_G._Bringhurst" title="Newell G. Bringhurst">Bringhurst, Newell G.</a>; <a href="/wiki/John_C._Hamer" title="John C. Hamer">Hamer, John C.</a>, eds. (2007). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Scattering_Of_The_Saints&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Scattering Of The Saints (page does not exist)">Scattering Of The Saints</a>: Schism Within Mormonism</i>. <a href="/wiki/Independence,_MO" class="mw-redirect" title="Independence, MO">Independence, MO</a>: <a href="/wiki/John_Whitmer_Books" class="mw-redirect" title="John Whitmer Books">John Whitmer Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1934901021" title="Special:BookSources/978-1934901021"><bdi>978-1934901021</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Scattering+Of+The+Saints%3A+Schism+Within+Mormonism&amp;rft.place=Independence%2C+MO&amp;rft.pub=John+Whitmer+Books&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.isbn=978-1934901021&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A collection of sixteen original essays on <a href="/wiki/List_of_denominations_in_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement" title="List of denominations in the Latter Day Saint movement">different expressions of the Latter Day Saint movement</a>; including groups which trace their path through <a href="/wiki/Sidney_Rigdon" title="Sidney Rigdon">Sidney Rigdon</a>, <a href="/wiki/Lyman_Wight" title="Lyman Wight">Lyman Wight</a>, <a href="/wiki/James_J._Strang" class="mw-redirect" title="James J. Strang">James J. Strang</a>, <a href="/wiki/Alpheus_Cutler" title="Alpheus Cutler">Alpheus Cutler</a>, <a href="/wiki/Granville_Hedrick" title="Granville Hedrick">Granville Hedrick</a>, <a href="/wiki/David_Whitmer" title="David Whitmer">David Whitmer</a>, <a href="/wiki/William_Smith_(Latter_Day_Saints)" title="William Smith (Latter Day Saints)">William Smith</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Amasa_Lyman" title="Amasa Lyman">Amasa Lyman</a>; outlines the history of <a href="/wiki/Fundamentalist_Mormonism" class="mw-redirect" title="Fundamentalist Mormonism">fundamentalist Mormonism</a>, and recent schisms within the <a href="/wiki/Category:Josephite_denominations_in_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement" title="Category:Josephite denominations in the Latter Day Saint movement">Reorganized Latter Day Saint tradition</a>. Includes contributions from <a href="/wiki/Danny_L._Jorgensen" class="mw-redirect" title="Danny L. Jorgensen">Danny L. Jorgensen</a>, <a href="/wiki/Anne_Wilde" title="Anne Wilde">Anne Wilde</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Roger_D._Launius" title="Roger D. Launius">Roger D. Launius</a>.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h3><span id="Community_of_Christ_.28RLDS_Church.29"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Community_of_Christ_(RLDS_Church)">Community of Christ (RLDS Church)</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=33" title="Edit section: Community of Christ (RLDS Church)"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1033289096"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Further information: <a href="/wiki/Community_of_Christ" title="Community of Christ">Community of Christ</a></div>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFDavis1998" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Inez_Smith_Davis&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Inez Smith Davis (page does not exist)">Davis, Inez Smith</a> (1998) [1934]. <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Story_of_the_Church&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Story of the Church (page does not exist)">The Story of the Church</a>: A History of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter Day Saints and of Its Legal Successor, the Reorganized Church of Jesus Christ of Latter Day Saints</i> (thirteenth, updated&#160;ed.). <a href="/wiki/Independence,_MO" class="mw-redirect" title="Independence, MO">Independence, MO</a>: <a href="/wiki/Herald_Publishing_House" class="mw-redirect" title="Herald Publishing House">Herald Publishing House</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0830901884" title="Special:BookSources/0830901884"><bdi>0830901884</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Story+of+the+Church%3A+A+History+of+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter+Day+Saints+and+of+Its+Legal+Successor%2C+the+Reorganized+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter+Day+Saints&amp;rft.place=Independence%2C+MO&amp;rft.edition=thirteenth%2C+updated&amp;rft.pub=Herald+Publishing+House&amp;rft.date=1998&amp;rft.isbn=0830901884&amp;rft.aulast=Davis&amp;rft.aufirst=Inez+Smith&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>A history, by the daughter of <a href="/wiki/RLDS" class="mw-redirect" title="RLDS">RLDS</a> Apostle and Church Historian <a href="/wiki/Heman_C._Smith" title="Heman C. Smith">Heman C. Smith</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFEdwards1991" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Paul_M._Edwards&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Paul M. Edwards (page does not exist)">Edwards, Paul M.</a> (1991). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Our_Legacy_of_Faith&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Our Legacy of Faith (page does not exist)">Our Legacy of Faith</a>: A Brief History of the Reorganized Church of Jesus Christ of Latter Day Saints</i>. <a href="/wiki/Independence,_MO" class="mw-redirect" title="Independence, MO">Independence, MO</a>: <a href="/wiki/Herald_Publishing_House" class="mw-redirect" title="Herald Publishing House">Herald Publishing House</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0830905944" title="Special:BookSources/0830905944"><bdi>0830905944</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Our+Legacy+of+Faith%3A+A+Brief+History+of+the+Reorganized+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter+Day+Saints&amp;rft.place=Independence%2C+MO&amp;rft.pub=Herald+Publishing+House&amp;rft.date=1991&amp;rft.isbn=0830905944&amp;rft.aulast=Edwards&amp;rft.aufirst=Paul+M.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/History_of_the_Community_of_Christ" title="History of the Community of Christ">History of the RLDS Church</a>, published by the Church.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Others_2">Others</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=34" title="Edit section: Others"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFWalker1998" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Ronald_W._Walker" title="Ronald W. Walker">Walker, Ronald W.</a> (1 January 1998). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wayward_Saints&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Wayward Saints (page does not exist)">Wayward Saints</a>: The Godbeites and Brigham Young</i>. Urbana: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0252067053" title="Special:BookSources/0252067053"><bdi>0252067053</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Wayward+Saints%3A+The+Godbeites+and+Brigham+Young&amp;rft.place=Urbana&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=1998-01-01&amp;rft.isbn=0252067053&amp;rft.aulast=Walker&amp;rft.aufirst=Ronald+W.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> Foreword by <a href="/wiki/Jan_Shipps" title="Jan Shipps">Jan Shipps</a>. Republished by the <a href="/wiki/University_of_Utah" title="University of Utah">University of Utah</a> in 2009. <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=gBDKrHzY1OQC">[71]</a>
<ul><li>Chronicle of the <a href="/wiki/Godbeites" title="Godbeites">Godbeites</a> and their 1870s challenge to <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young" title="Brigham Young">Brigham Young</a>'s leadership and authority; a collective biography of <a href="/wiki/William_S._Godbe" title="William S. Godbe">William S. Godbe</a>, <a href="/wiki/Elias_L._T._Harrison" title="Elias L. T. Harrison">Elias L. T. Harrison</a>, <a href="/wiki/Edward_W._Tullidge" class="mw-redirect" title="Edward W. Tullidge">Edward W. Tullidge</a>, <a href="/wiki/Fanny_Stenhouse" title="Fanny Stenhouse">Fanny</a> and <a href="/wiki/Thomas_Stenhouse" class="mw-redirect" title="Thomas Stenhouse">Thomas Stenhouse</a>, <a href="/wiki/Amasa_M._Lyman" class="mw-redirect" title="Amasa M. Lyman">Amasa M. Lyman</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Henry_W._Lawrence&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Henry W. Lawrence (page does not exist)">Henry W. Lawrence</a>, and <a href="/w/index.php?title=Eli_B._Kelsey&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Eli B. Kelsey (page does not exist)">Eli B. Kelsey</a>.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Biographies">Biographies</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=35" title="Edit section: Biographies"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFJenson1901–1936" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Andrew_Jenson" title="Andrew Jenson">Jenson, Andrew</a> (1901–1936). <i><a href="/wiki/Latter-Day_Saint_Biographical_Encyclopedia" class="mw-redirect" title="Latter-Day Saint Biographical Encyclopedia">Latter-Day Saint Biographical Encyclopedia</a>: A Compilation of Biographical Sketches of Prominent Men and Women in the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-Day Saints</i>. <a href="/wiki/Deseret_News" title="Deseret News">Deseret News</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1589580273" title="Special:BookSources/1589580273"><bdi>1589580273</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Latter-Day+Saint+Biographical+Encyclopedia%3A+A+Compilation+of+Biographical+Sketches+of+Prominent+Men+and+Women+in+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-Day+Saints&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+News&amp;rft.date=1901%2F1936&amp;rft.isbn=1589580273&amp;rft.aulast=Jenson&amp;rft.aufirst=Andrew&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://contentdm.lib.byu.edu/digital/collection/BYUIBooks/id/3527/">[72]</a>
<ul><li>A four-volume <a href="/wiki/Biographical_dictionary" title="Biographical dictionary">biographical dictionary</a> by an Assistant Church Historian; includes a church chronology and biographical information about leaders and other prominent members of the LDS Church from its founding in 1830 until 1930.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Joseph_Smith">Joseph Smith</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=36" title="Edit section: Joseph Smith"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1033289096"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Further information: <a href="/wiki/Works_relating_to_Joseph_Smith" title="Works relating to Joseph Smith">Works relating to Joseph Smith</a></div>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSmith2008" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Joseph_Smith" title="Joseph Smith">Smith, Joseph</a> (26 November 2008). <a href="/wiki/Dean_Jessee" class="mw-redirect" title="Dean Jessee">Jessee, Dean</a>; <a href="/wiki/Ronald_Esplin" class="mw-redirect" title="Ronald Esplin">Esplin, Ronald</a>; <a href="/wiki/Richard_Lyman_Bushman" class="mw-redirect" title="Richard Lyman Bushman">Bushman, Richard Lyman</a> (eds.). <i><a href="/wiki/The_Joseph_Smith_Papers" title="The Joseph Smith Papers">The Joseph Smith Papers</a>: Journals, Vol. 1: 1832-1839</i>. Joseph Smith Papers: Journals Series (Book 1 of 3). Salt Lake City: <a href="/wiki/Church_Historian%27s_Press" title="Church Historian&#39;s Press">Church Historian's Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1570088490" title="Special:BookSources/978-1570088490"><bdi>978-1570088490</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Joseph+Smith+Papers%3A+Journals%2C+Vol.+1%3A+1832-1839&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.series=Joseph+Smith+Papers%3A+Journals+Series+%28Book+1+of+3%29&amp;rft.pub=Church+Historian%27s+Press&amp;rft.date=2008-11-26&amp;rft.isbn=978-1570088490&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.josephsmithpapers.org/articles/journals-volume-1-1832-1839">[73]</a>
<ul><li>Collection featuring Joseph Smith's first five journals; providing Smith's perspective on the <a href="/wiki/Kirtland_Temple" title="Kirtland Temple">Kirtland Temple</a>, the origins of the "<a href="/wiki/Missouri_Mormon_War" class="mw-redirect" title="Missouri Mormon War">Missouri Mormon War</a>", and the <a href="/wiki/History_of_Nauvoo,_Illinois#Nauvoo_founded_by_the_Latter_Day_Saints" title="History of Nauvoo, Illinois">founding of what would become Nauvoo, Illinois</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSmith2011" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Joseph_Smith" title="Joseph Smith">Smith, Joseph</a> (15 November 2011). <a href="/wiki/Andrew_H._Hedges" title="Andrew H. Hedges">Hedges, Andrew H.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Alex_D._Smith_(historian)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Alex D. Smith (historian) (page does not exist)">Smith, Alex D.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Richard_Lloyd_Anderson" title="Richard Lloyd Anderson">Anderson, Richard Lloyd</a> (eds.). <i><a href="/wiki/The_Joseph_Smith_Papers" title="The Joseph Smith Papers">The Joseph Smith Papers</a>: Journals, Vol. 2, December 1841–April 1843</i>. Joseph Smith Papers: Journals Series (Book 2 of 3). Salt Lake City: Church Historian's Press. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1609087371" title="Special:BookSources/978-1609087371"><bdi>978-1609087371</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Joseph+Smith+Papers%3A+Journals%2C+Vol.+2%2C+December+1841%E2%80%93April+1843&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.series=Joseph+Smith+Papers%3A+Journals+Series+%28Book+2+of+3%29&amp;rft.pub=Church+Historian%27s+Press&amp;rft.date=2011-11-15&amp;rft.isbn=978-1609087371&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.josephsmithpapers.org/articles/journals-volume-2-december-1841-april-1843">[74]</a>
<ul><li>Collection featuring Smith's first <a href="/wiki/Nauvoo,_Illinois" title="Nauvoo, Illinois">Nauvoo, Illinois</a> journal, as well as part of the second; chronicling the organization of the <a href="/wiki/Female_Relief_Society_of_Nauvoo" class="mw-redirect" title="Female Relief Society of Nauvoo">Female Relief Society of Nauvoo</a>, <a href="/wiki/Proxy_baptism" class="mw-redirect" title="Proxy baptism">proxy baptism</a> for the dead, publication of the <a href="/wiki/Book_of_Abraham" title="Book of Abraham">Book of Abraham</a>, construction of the <a href="/wiki/Nauvoo_Temple" title="Nauvoo Temple">Nauvoo Temple</a>, agitation from dissenters such as <a href="/wiki/John_C._Bennett" title="John C. Bennett">John C. Bennett</a>, and an attempts to have <a href="/wiki/Joseph_Smith_and_the_criminal_justice_system#In_Illinois_(1839–44)" title="Joseph Smith and the criminal justice system">Smith extradited to Missouri for trial</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSmith2015" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Joseph_Smith" title="Joseph Smith">Smith, Joseph</a> (30 November 2015). <a href="/wiki/Andrew_H._Hedges" title="Andrew H. Hedges">Hedges, Andrew H.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Alex_D._Smith_(historian)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Alex D. Smith (historian) (page does not exist)">Smith, Alex D.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Brent_M._Rogers&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Brent M. Rogers (page does not exist)">Rogers, Brent M.</a> (eds.). <i><a href="/wiki/The_Joseph_Smith_Papers" title="The Joseph Smith Papers">The Joseph Smith Papers</a>: Journals, Volume 3: May 1843-June 1844</i>. Joseph Smith Papers: Journals Series (Book 3 of 3). Salt Lake City: Church Historian's Press. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1629721477" title="Special:BookSources/978-1629721477"><bdi>978-1629721477</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Joseph+Smith+Papers%3A+Journals%2C+Volume+3%3A+May+1843-June+1844&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.series=Joseph+Smith+Papers%3A+Journals+Series+%28Book+3+of+3%29&amp;rft.pub=Church+Historian%27s+Press&amp;rft.date=2015-11-30&amp;rft.isbn=978-1629721477&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.josephsmithpapers.org/articles/journals-volume-3-may-1843-june-1844">[75]</a>
<ul><li>Collection featuring journal entries from the last year of Smith's life; discussing topics including <a href="/wiki/Apotheosis#The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints" title="Apotheosis">humanity's potential to become like God</a>, establishment of the <a href="/wiki/Council_of_Fifty" title="Council of Fifty">Council of Fifty</a>, <a href="/wiki/Joseph_Smith_presidential_campaign,_1844" class="mw-redirect" title="Joseph Smith presidential campaign, 1844">Smith's candidacy for United States president</a>, and escalating <a href="/wiki/Mormonism_and_violence#History_of_religious_violence_against_Mormons" title="Mormonism and violence">conflict against Smith and the church</a>. Includes appendixes with accounts from <a href="/wiki/Willard_Richards" title="Willard Richards">Willard Richards</a> and <a href="/wiki/William_Clayton_(Mormon)" class="mw-redirect" title="William Clayton (Mormon)">William Clayton</a> of the <a href="/wiki/Death_of_Joseph_Smith" class="mw-redirect" title="Death of Joseph Smith">murder of Joseph and Hyrum Smith</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSmith1853" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Lucy_Mack_Smith" title="Lucy Mack Smith">Smith, Lucy Mack</a> (1853). <i><a href="/wiki/Biographical_Sketches_Of_Joseph_Smith,_The_Prophet,_And_His_Progenitors_For_Many_Generations" class="mw-redirect" title="Biographical Sketches Of Joseph Smith, The Prophet, And His Progenitors For Many Generations">Biographical Sketches Of Joseph Smith, The Prophet, And His Progenitors For Many Generations</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Liverpool" title="Liverpool">Liverpool</a>: <a href="/wiki/Orson_Pratt" title="Orson Pratt">Orson Pratt</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1425483836" title="Special:BookSources/1425483836"><bdi>1425483836</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Biographical+Sketches+Of+Joseph+Smith%2C+The+Prophet%2C+And+His+Progenitors+For+Many+Generations&amp;rft.place=Liverpool&amp;rft.pub=Orson+Pratt&amp;rft.date=1853&amp;rft.isbn=1425483836&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Lucy+Mack&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/BiographicalSketchesOfJosephSmithTheProphet">[76]</a>
<ul><li>Republished under several titles, including <i>History of Joseph Smith by His Mother</i></li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBrodie1995" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Fawn_M._Brodie" title="Fawn M. Brodie">Brodie, Fawn M.</a> (1 August 1995) [1945]. <i><a href="/wiki/No_Man_Knows_My_History" title="No Man Knows My History">No Man Knows My History</a>: The Life of Joseph Smith, the Mormon Prophet</i> (2nd revised &amp; enlarged&#160;ed.). <a href="/wiki/Vintage_Books" title="Vintage Books">Vintage Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0679730540" title="Special:BookSources/0679730540"><bdi>0679730540</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=No+Man+Knows+My+History%3A+The+Life+of+Joseph+Smith%2C+the+Mormon+Prophet&amp;rft.edition=2nd+revised+%26+enlarged&amp;rft.pub=Vintage+Books&amp;rft.date=1995-08-01&amp;rft.isbn=0679730540&amp;rft.aulast=Brodie&amp;rft.aufirst=Fawn+M.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/NoManKnowsMyHistory">[77]</a>
<ul><li>Known as the first important non-<a href="/wiki/Hagiographic" class="mw-redirect" title="Hagiographic">hagiographic</a> biography of Joseph Smith; continually <a href="/wiki/Out-of-print_book" class="mw-redirect" title="Out-of-print book">in print</a> for over seven decades.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFRemini2002" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Robert_V._Remini" title="Robert V. Remini">Remini, Robert Vincent</a> (2002). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Joseph_Smith_(book)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Joseph Smith (book) (page does not exist)">Joseph Smith</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Penguin_Group" title="Penguin Group">Penguin</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/067003083X" title="Special:BookSources/067003083X"><bdi>067003083X</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Joseph+Smith&amp;rft.pub=Penguin&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.isbn=067003083X&amp;rft.aulast=Remini&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert+Vincent&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=u3nzkbb2ha8C">[78]</a>
<ul><li>A scholarly attempt at an objective portrayal of Joseph Smith by a historian of the <a href="/wiki/Jacksonian_democracy" title="Jacksonian democracy">Jacksonian era</a>; part of the <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Penguin_Lives&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Penguin Lives (page does not exist)">Penguin Lives</a></i> book series.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFVogel2004" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Dan_Vogel" title="Dan Vogel">Vogel, Dan</a> (2004). <i><a href="/wiki/Joseph_Smith:_The_Making_of_a_Prophet" title="Joseph Smith: The Making of a Prophet">Joseph Smith: The Making of a Prophet</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1560851791" title="Special:BookSources/1560851791"><bdi>1560851791</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Joseph+Smith%3A+The+Making+of+a+Prophet&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.isbn=1560851791&amp;rft.aulast=Vogel&amp;rft.aufirst=Dan&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://signaturebookslibrary.org/joseph-smith-the-making-of-a-prophet/">[79]</a>
<ul><li>A biography of the formative years, covering the period of Smith's life up until 1831; argues that Smith was a <a href="/wiki/Pious_fraud" title="Pious fraud">pious fraud</a>, interpreting the <a href="/wiki/Book_of_Mormon" title="Book of Mormon">Book of Mormon</a> as springing from his psychology and experiences.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFCaswall1843" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Henry_Caswall&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Henry Caswall (page does not exist)">Caswall, Henry</a> (1843). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Prophet_of_the_Nineteenth_Century&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Prophet of the Nineteenth Century (page does not exist)">The Prophet of the Nineteenth Century</a>: Or, The Rise, Progress, and Present State of the Mormons, Or Latter-day Saints: to which is Appended, an Analysis of the Book of Mormon</i>. <a href="/wiki/J._G._F._%26_J._Rivington" class="mw-redirect" title="J. G. F. &amp; J. Rivington">J. G. F. &amp; J. Rivington</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1435751701" title="Special:BookSources/1435751701"><bdi>1435751701</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Prophet+of+the+Nineteenth+Century%3A+Or%2C+The+Rise%2C+Progress%2C+and+Present+State+of+the+Mormons%2C+Or+Latter-day+Saints%3A+to+which+is+Appended%2C+an+Analysis+of+the+Book+of+Mormon&amp;rft.pub=J.+G.+F.+%26+J.+Rivington&amp;rft.date=1843&amp;rft.isbn=1435751701&amp;rft.aulast=Caswall&amp;rft.aufirst=Henry&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/prophetnineteen00caswgoog">[80]</a>
<ul><li>The first biography ever written on Joseph Smith; a hostile account.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFEvans1989" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/John_Henry_Evans" title="John Henry Evans">Evans, John Henry</a> (1 December 1989) [1933]. <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Joseph_Smith:_An_American_Prophet&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Joseph Smith: An American Prophet (page does not exist)">Joseph Smith: An American Prophet</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Deseret_Book_Company" title="Deseret Book Company">Deseret Book Company</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0875792154" title="Special:BookSources/0875792154"><bdi>0875792154</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Joseph+Smith%3A+An+American+Prophet&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Book+Company&amp;rft.date=1989-12-01&amp;rft.isbn=0875792154&amp;rft.aulast=Evans&amp;rft.aufirst=John+Henry&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Faithful biography presenting Smith "as a greater leader than <a href="/wiki/Moses" title="Moses">Moses</a> and a greater prophet than <a href="/wiki/Isaiah" title="Isaiah">Isaiah</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFHill1999" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Donna_Hill_(historian)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Donna Hill (historian) (page does not exist)">Hill, Donna</a> (15 March 1999) [1977]. <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Joseph_Smith:_The_First_Mormon&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Joseph Smith: The First Mormon (page does not exist)">Joseph Smith: The First Mormon</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/156085118X" title="Special:BookSources/156085118X"><bdi>156085118X</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Joseph+Smith%3A+The+First+Mormon&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=1999-03-15&amp;rft.isbn=156085118X&amp;rft.aulast=Hill&amp;rft.aufirst=Donna&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=roAOAAAACAAJ">[81]</a>
<ul><li>Comprehensive biography by a Mormon historian; described as having a temperate, balanced, middle-of-the-road approach— in the spectrum of pro and con biographies.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Brigham_Young">Brigham Young</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=37" title="Edit section: Brigham Young"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFArrington1985" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Leonard_J._Arrington" title="Leonard J. Arrington">Arrington, Leonard J.</a> (1985). <i><a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young:_American_Moses" title="Brigham Young: American Moses">Brigham Young: American Moses</a></i>. New York: <a href="/wiki/Alfred_A._Knopf" title="Alfred A. Knopf">Alfred A. Knopf</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-394-51022-4" title="Special:BookSources/0-394-51022-4"><bdi>0-394-51022-4</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Brigham+Young%3A+American+Moses&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Alfred+A.+Knopf&amp;rft.date=1985&amp;rft.isbn=0-394-51022-4&amp;rft.aulast=Arrington&amp;rft.aufirst=Leonard+J.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/brighamyoungamer00arri">[82]</a>
<ul><li>Admiring biography of <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young" title="Brigham Young">Brigham Young</a>, the 2nd President of the LDS Church (from 1847–1877); nicknamed the "American <a href="/wiki/Moses" title="Moses">Moses</a>" because he led his followers in an exodus through a desert, to what they saw as a promised land.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBringhurst1986" class="citation book cs1">Bringhurst, Newell G. (1986). <a href="/wiki/Oscar_Handlin" title="Oscar Handlin">Handlin, Oscar</a> (ed.). <span class="id-lock-registration" title="Free registration required"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/isbn_0316108227"><i>Brigham Young And The Expanding American Frontier</i></a></span>. <a href="/wiki/Boston" title="Boston">Boston</a>: <a href="/wiki/Little,_Brown" class="mw-redirect" title="Little, Brown">Little, Brown</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0316108227" title="Special:BookSources/0316108227"><bdi>0316108227</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Brigham+Young+And+The+Expanding+American+Frontier&amp;rft.place=Boston&amp;rft.pub=Little%2C+Brown&amp;rft.date=1986&amp;rft.isbn=0316108227&amp;rft.aulast=Bringhurst&amp;rft.aufirst=Newell+G.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fisbn_0316108227&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>.
<ul><li>Part of the Library of American Biography Series. Republished on 24 January 1997 by <a href="/wiki/Longman" title="Longman">Longman</a> (<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-673-39322-4" title="Special:BookSources/0-673-39322-4">0-673-39322-4</a>).</li></ul></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Others_3">Others</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=38" title="Edit section: Others"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFNewellAvery1994" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Linda_King_Newell" title="Linda King Newell">Newell, Linda King</a>; <a href="/wiki/Valeen_Tippetts_Avery" title="Valeen Tippetts Avery">Avery, Valeen Tippetts</a> (1994) [1984]. <i><a href="/wiki/Mormon_Enigma" title="Mormon Enigma">Mormon Enigma</a>: Emma Hale Smith, Prophet's Wife, "Elect Lady," Polygamy's Foe</i> (second&#160;ed.). Urbana, IL: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0252062914" title="Special:BookSources/0252062914"><bdi>0252062914</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormon+Enigma%3A+Emma+Hale+Smith%2C+Prophet%27s+Wife%2C+%22Elect+Lady%2C%22+Polygamy%27s+Foe&amp;rft.place=Urbana%2C+IL&amp;rft.edition=second&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.isbn=0252062914&amp;rft.aulast=Newell&amp;rft.aufirst=Linda+King&amp;rft.au=Avery%2C+Valeen+Tippetts&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=UjHEhhqVu1UC">[83]</a>
<ul><li>Award-winning biography of <a href="/wiki/Emma_Smith" title="Emma Smith">Emma Smith</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFWhitney2017" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Orson_F._Whitney" title="Orson F. Whitney">Whitney, Orson F.</a> (14 January 2017) [1888]. <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Life_of_Heber_C._Kimball&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Life of Heber C. Kimball (page does not exist)">Life of Heber C. Kimball</a>: An Apostle, The Father and Founder of the British Mission</i>. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Bookcraft" title="Bookcraft">Bookcraft</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1540792716" title="Special:BookSources/978-1540792716"><bdi>978-1540792716</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Life+of+Heber+C.+Kimball%3A+An+Apostle%2C+The+Father+and+Founder+of+the+British+Mission&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Bookcraft&amp;rft.date=2017-01-14&amp;rft.isbn=978-1540792716&amp;rft.aulast=Whitney&amp;rft.aufirst=Orson+F.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/LifeOfHeberC.Kimball">[84]</a>
<ul><li>Faithful biography of <a href="/wiki/Heber_C._Kimball" title="Heber C. Kimball">Heber C. Kimball</a>, by his grandson.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFWalker2004" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Ronald_W._Walker" title="Ronald W. Walker">Walker, Ronald W.</a> (1 August 2004). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Qualities_That_Count&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Qualities That Count (page does not exist)">Qualities That Count</a>: Heber J. Grant as Businessman, Missionary and Apostle</i>. Provo, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young_University" title="Brigham Young University">Brigham Young University</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0842525505" title="Special:BookSources/0842525505"><bdi>0842525505</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Qualities+That+Count%3A+Heber+J.+Grant+as+Businessman%2C+Missionary+and+Apostle&amp;rft.place=Provo%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Brigham+Young+University&amp;rft.date=2004-08-01&amp;rft.isbn=0842525505&amp;rft.aulast=Walker&amp;rft.aufirst=Ronald+W.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://contentdm.lib.byu.edu/cdm/ref/collection/byustudies/id/4510">[85]</a>
<ul><li>Essay collection discussing <a href="/wiki/Heber_J._Grant" title="Heber J. Grant">Heber J. Grant</a>'s life and service; from his birth to middle age, prior to becoming the 7th President of the LDS Church (from 1918 to 1945).</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPrinceWright2005" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Gregory_Prince" title="Gregory Prince">Prince, Gregory A.</a>; <a href="/wiki/William_Robert_Wright" class="mw-redirect" title="William Robert Wright">Wright, Wm. Robert</a> (9 March 2005). <i><a href="/wiki/David_O._McKay_and_the_Rise_of_Modern_Mormonism" title="David O. McKay and the Rise of Modern Mormonism">David O. McKay and the Rise of Modern Mormonism</a></i>. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Utah_Press" title="University of Utah Press">University of Utah Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-87480-822-7" title="Special:BookSources/0-87480-822-7"><bdi>0-87480-822-7</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=David+O.+McKay+and+the+Rise+of+Modern+Mormonism&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Utah+Press&amp;rft.date=2005-03-09&amp;rft.isbn=0-87480-822-7&amp;rft.aulast=Prince&amp;rft.aufirst=Gregory+A.&amp;rft.au=Wright%2C+Wm.+Robert&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=3UBXLIkLEQwC">[86]</a>
<ul><li>Biography of <a href="/wiki/David_O._McKay" title="David O. McKay">David O. McKay</a>, the ninth president of the LDS Church (from 1951 to 1970).</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFAvery1998" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Valeen_Tippetts_Avery" title="Valeen Tippetts Avery">Avery, Valeen Tippetts</a> (1 September 1998). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=From_Mission_to_Madness&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="From Mission to Madness (page does not exist)">From Mission to Madness</a>: Last Son of the Mormon Prophet</i>. Urbana, IL: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0252023994" title="Special:BookSources/0252023994"><bdi>0252023994</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=From+Mission+to+Madness%3A+Last+Son+of+the+Mormon+Prophet&amp;rft.place=Urbana%2C+IL&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=1998-09-01&amp;rft.isbn=0252023994&amp;rft.aulast=Avery&amp;rft.aufirst=Valeen+Tippetts&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://archive.org/details/frommissiontomad00aver_0">[87]</a>
<ul><li>Biography of the life of the youngest son of Joseph and Emma Smith, <a href="/wiki/David_Hyrum_Smith" title="David Hyrum Smith">David Hyrum Smith</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFLaunius1995" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Roger_D._Launius" title="Roger D. Launius">Launius, Roger D.</a> (1 September 1995) [1988]. <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Joseph_Smith_III:_Pragmatic_Prophet&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Joseph Smith III: Pragmatic Prophet (page does not exist)">Joseph Smith III: Pragmatic Prophet</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Urbana,_IL" class="mw-redirect" title="Urbana, IL">Urbana, IL</a>: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0252065158" title="Special:BookSources/0252065158"><bdi>0252065158</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Joseph+Smith+III%3A+Pragmatic+Prophet&amp;rft.place=Urbana%2C+IL&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=1995-09-01&amp;rft.isbn=0252065158&amp;rft.aulast=Launius&amp;rft.aufirst=Roger+D.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=K_xeJWwRouEC">[88]</a>
<ul><li>Biography of the founder of the <a href="/wiki/RLDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="RLDS Church">RLDS Church</a>, <a href="/wiki/Joseph_Smith_III" title="Joseph Smith III">Joseph Smith III</a>, which he led from 1860 until his death in 1914.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFKimball2005" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Edward_L._Kimball" title="Edward L. Kimball">Kimball, Edward L.</a> (2005). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Lengthen_Your_Stride&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Lengthen Your Stride (page does not exist)">Lengthen Your Stride</a>: The Presidency of Spencer W. Kimball</i>. <a href="/wiki/Deseret_Book" class="mw-redirect" title="Deseret Book">Deseret Book</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1590384571" title="Special:BookSources/1590384571"><bdi>1590384571</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Lengthen+Your+Stride%3A+The+Presidency+of+Spencer+W.+Kimball&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Book&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.isbn=1590384571&amp;rft.aulast=Kimball&amp;rft.aufirst=Edward+L.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=TKHtAAAAMAAJ">[89]</a>
<ul><li>Biography of <a href="/wiki/Spencer_W._Kimball" title="Spencer W. Kimball">Spencer W. Kimball</a>, the 12th President of the LDS Church (from 1973 to 1985), written by his son; focused exclusively on Kimball's ministry at Church President.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFFox1980" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Frank_W._Fox&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Frank W. Fox (page does not exist)">Fox, Frank W.</a> (1980). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=J._Reuben_Clark:_The_Public_Years&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="J. Reuben Clark: The Public Years (page does not exist)">J. Reuben Clark: The Public Years</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young_University_Press" title="Brigham Young University Press">Brigham Young University Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0842518320" title="Special:BookSources/0842518320"><bdi>0842518320</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=J.+Reuben+Clark%3A+The+Public+Years&amp;rft.pub=Brigham+Young+University+Press&amp;rft.date=1980&amp;rft.isbn=0842518320&amp;rft.aulast=Fox&amp;rft.aufirst=Frank+W.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Biography of <a href="/wiki/J._Reuben_Clark" title="J. Reuben Clark">J. Reuben Clark</a>; focused on his time as an attorney and government servant, prior to being called as a Counselor in the <a href="/wiki/First_Presidency_(LDS_Church)" title="First Presidency (LDS Church)">First Presidency</a> (from 1933 to 1961).</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMadsenJonesThornton2018" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Susan_Arrington_Madsen&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Susan Arrington Madsen (page does not exist)">Madsen, Susan Arrington</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Emily_Madsen_Jones&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Emily Madsen Jones (page does not exist)">Jones, Emily Madsen</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Rebecca_Madsen_Thornton&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Rebecca Madsen Thornton (page does not exist)">Thornton, Rebecca Madsen</a> (2018). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Fathers_of_the_Prophets&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Fathers of the Prophets (page does not exist)">Fathers of the Prophets</a>: From Joseph Smith to Russell M. Nelson</i>. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Deseret_Book" class="mw-redirect" title="Deseret Book">Deseret Book</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1629724485" title="Special:BookSources/978-1629724485"><bdi>978-1629724485</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Fathers+of+the+Prophets%3A+From+Joseph+Smith+to+Russell+M.+Nelson&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Book&amp;rft.date=2018&amp;rft.isbn=978-1629724485&amp;rft.aulast=Madsen&amp;rft.aufirst=Susan+Arrington&amp;rft.au=Jones%2C+Emily+Madsen&amp;rft.au=Thornton%2C+Rebecca+Madsen&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Collective biography of fathers of the leaders of the LDS Church; including <a href="/wiki/Joseph_Smith_Sr." title="Joseph Smith Sr.">Joseph Smith Sr.</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=John_Young_(father_of_Brigham)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="John Young (father of Brigham) (page does not exist)">John Young</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=James_Taylor_(father_of_John_Taylor)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="James Taylor (father of John Taylor) (page does not exist)">James Taylor</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Aphek_Woodruff&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Aphek Woodruff (page does not exist)">Aphek Woodruff</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Oliver_Snow_III&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Oliver Snow III (page does not exist)">Oliver Snow III</a>, <a href="/wiki/Hyrum_Smith" title="Hyrum Smith">Hyrum Smith</a>, <a href="/wiki/Jedediah_Morgan_Grant" class="mw-redirect" title="Jedediah Morgan Grant">Jedediah Morgan Grant</a>, <a href="/wiki/John_Henry_Smith" title="John Henry Smith">John Henry Smith</a>, <a href="/wiki/David_McKay_(politician)" title="David McKay (politician)">David McKay</a>, <a href="/wiki/Joseph_F._Smith" title="Joseph F. Smith">Joseph F. Smith</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Samuel_Marion_Lee_Jr.&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Samuel Marion Lee Jr. (page does not exist)">Samuel Marion Lee Jr.</a>, <a href="/wiki/Andrew_Kimball" title="Andrew Kimball">Andrew Kimball</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=George_Taft_Benson_Jr.&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="George Taft Benson Jr. (page does not exist)">George Taft Benson Jr.</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=John_William_%22Will%22_Hunter&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="John William &quot;Will&quot; Hunter (page does not exist)">John William "Will" Hunter</a>, <a href="/wiki/Bryant_S._Hinckley" title="Bryant S. Hinckley">Bryant S. Hinckley</a>, and <a href="/w/index.php?title=George_Spencer_Monson&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="George Spencer Monson (page does not exist)">George Spencer Monson</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFQuinn2002" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/D._Michael_Quinn" title="D. Michael Quinn">Quinn, D. Michael</a> (2002). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Elder_Statesman&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Elder Statesman (page does not exist)">Elder Statesman</a>: A Biography of J. Reuben Clark</i>. <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1560851554" title="Special:BookSources/1560851554"><bdi>1560851554</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Elder+Statesman%3A+A+Biography+of+J.+Reuben+Clark&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.isbn=1560851554&amp;rft.aulast=Quinn&amp;rft.aufirst=D.+Michael&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/J._Reuben_Clark" title="J. Reuben Clark">J. Reuben Clark</a>'s life and impact (intellectual and administrative) as counselor to three LDS Church presidents.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFGibbons2018" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Francis_M._Gibbons" title="Francis M. Gibbons">Gibbons, Francis M.</a> (14 January 2018). <a href="/w/index.php?title=Daniel_Bay_Gibbons&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Daniel Bay Gibbons (page does not exist)">Daniel Bay, Gibbons</a> (ed.). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Russell_M._Nelson_(book)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Russell M. Nelson (book) (page does not exist)">Russell M. Nelson</a></i>. <a href="/w/index.php?title=Sixteen_Stones_Press&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Sixteen Stones Press (page does not exist)">Sixteen Stones Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1942640257" title="Special:BookSources/978-1942640257"><bdi>978-1942640257</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Russell+M.+Nelson&amp;rft.pub=Sixteen+Stones+Press&amp;rft.date=2018-01-14&amp;rft.isbn=978-1942640257&amp;rft.aulast=Gibbons&amp;rft.aufirst=Francis+M.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Biography of <a href="/wiki/Russell_M._Nelson" title="Russell M. Nelson">Russell M. Nelson</a>, the seventeenth President of the LDS Church; a collection of personal reminiscences, written by a former secretary to the First Presidency, drawing on more than sixty years of association with President Nelson; the eighth and final part of the series entitled <i>Remembering the Prophets of God</i>.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Personal_accounts">Personal accounts</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bibliography_of_the_Latter_Day_Saint_movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=39" title="Edit section: Personal accounts"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFJones1890" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Daniel_Webster_Jones_(Mormon)" title="Daniel Webster Jones (Mormon)">Jones, Daniel W.</a> (1890). <i><a href="/wiki/Forty_Years_Among_the_Indians" class="mw-redirect" title="Forty Years Among the Indians">Forty Years Among the Indians</a>: A True yet Thrilling Narrative of the Author's Experiences among the Natives</i>. <a href="/wiki/Juvenile_Instructor_Press" class="mw-redirect" title="Juvenile Instructor Press">Juvenile Instructor Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1331575311" title="Special:BookSources/1331575311"><bdi>1331575311</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Forty+Years+Among+the+Indians%3A+A+True+yet+Thrilling+Narrative+of+the+Author%27s+Experiences+among+the+Natives&amp;rft.pub=Juvenile+Instructor+Press&amp;rft.date=1890&amp;rft.isbn=1331575311&amp;rft.aulast=Jones&amp;rft.aufirst=Daniel+W.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/46521">[90]</a>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Autobiography" title="Autobiography">Autobiography</a> of a convert to the LDS Church, who participated in the <a href="/wiki/Mormon_handcart_pioneers#1856:_Willie_and_Martin_handcart_companies" title="Mormon handcart pioneers">rescue of handcart companies during the winter of 1856</a>, worked with the <a href="/wiki/Indigenous_peoples_of_North_America" class="mw-redirect" title="Indigenous peoples of North America">Native American</a> and <a href="/wiki/Mexican_people" class="mw-redirect" title="Mexican people">Mexican peoples</a>, and was an early settler of what became <a href="/wiki/Mesa,_Arizona" title="Mesa, Arizona">Mesa, Arizona</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFHartley1993" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/William_G._Hartley" title="William G. Hartley">Hartley, William G.</a> (1 December 1993). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=My_Best_for_the_Kingdom&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="My Best for the Kingdom (page does not exist)">My Best for the Kingdom</a>: History and Autobiography of John Lowe Butler, a Mormon Frontiersman</i>. Salt Lake City: <a href="/w/index.php?title=Aspen_Books&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Aspen Books (page does not exist)">Aspen Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1562362127" title="Special:BookSources/1562362127"><bdi>1562362127</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=My+Best+for+the+Kingdom%3A+History+and+Autobiography+of+John+Lowe+Butler%2C+a+Mormon+Frontiersman&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.pub=Aspen+Books&amp;rft.date=1993-12-01&amp;rft.isbn=1562362127&amp;rft.aulast=Hartley&amp;rft.aufirst=William+G.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=XXokDwAAQBAJ">[91]</a>
<ul><li>Account of <a href="/w/index.php?title=John_Lowe_Butler&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="John Lowe Butler (page does not exist)">John Lowe Butler</a>, an early convert from <a href="/wiki/Kentucky" title="Kentucky">Kentucky</a>; bodyguard to Joseph Smith, <a href="/wiki/Danite" title="Danite">Danite</a> in <a href="/wiki/1838_Mormon_War" title="1838 Mormon War">the Missouri conflict</a>, missionary to the <a href="/wiki/Sioux" title="Sioux">Sioux</a>, <a href="/wiki/Origin_of_Latter_Day_Saint_polygamy#1842_scandal_and_the_new_vocabulary" title="Origin of Latter Day Saint polygamy">Nauvoo polygamist</a> and <a href="/wiki/Nauvoo_Legion" title="Nauvoo Legion">Legionnaire</a>, <a href="/wiki/American_frontier#Mormons_and_Utah" title="American frontier">frontiersman</a> and <a href="/wiki/Bishop_(Latter_Day_Saints)" title="Bishop (Latter Day Saints)">bishop</a> of <a href="/wiki/Spanish_Fork,_Utah" title="Spanish Fork, Utah">Spanish Fork</a> during the <a href="/wiki/Mormon_Reformation" title="Mormon Reformation">Mormon Reformation</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Utah_War" title="Utah War">Utah War</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFHartleyAlder2007" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/William_G._Hartley" title="William G. Hartley">Hartley, William G.</a>; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Lorna_Call_Alder&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Lorna Call Alder (page does not exist)">Alder, Lorna Call</a> (2007). <a href="/w/index.php?title=H._Lane_Johnson&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="H. Lane Johnson (page does not exist)">Johnson, H. Lane</a> (ed.). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Anson_Bowen_Call:_Bishop_of_Colonia_Dubl%C3%A1n&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Anson Bowen Call: Bishop of Colonia Dublán (page does not exist)">Anson Bowen Call: Bishop of Colonia Dublán</a></i>. Provo, Utah: L.C. Alder. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1928845522" title="Special:BookSources/978-1928845522"><bdi>978-1928845522</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Anson+Bowen+Call%3A+Bishop+of+Colonia+Dubl%C3%A1n&amp;rft.place=Provo%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=L.C.+Alder&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.isbn=978-1928845522&amp;rft.aulast=Hartley&amp;rft.aufirst=William+G.&amp;rft.au=Alder%2C+Lorna+Call&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Biography of <a href="/w/index.php?title=Anson_Bowen_Call&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Anson Bowen Call (page does not exist)">Anson Bowen Call</a> (1863–1958); <a href="/wiki/Bishop_(Latter_Day_Saints)" title="Bishop (Latter Day Saints)">bishop</a> of <a href="/wiki/Colonia_Dubl%C3%A1n" title="Colonia Dublán">Colonia Dublán</a>, a <a href="/wiki/Mormon_colonies_in_Mexico" title="Mormon colonies in Mexico">Mormon colony in Chihuahua, Mexico</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFLorelei2016" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Lorelei_(author)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Lorelei (author) (page does not exist)">Lorelei</a> (16 March 2016). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=From_Mormon_To_Mermaid&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="From Mormon To Mermaid (page does not exist)">From Mormon To Mermaid</a>: One Woman's Voyage from Oppression to Freedom</i>. <a href="/w/index.php?title=DogEar_Publishing&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="DogEar Publishing (page does not exist)">DogEar Publishing</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1457542930" title="Special:BookSources/978-1457542930"><bdi>978-1457542930</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=From+Mormon+To+Mermaid%3A+One+Woman%27s+Voyage+from+Oppression+to+Freedom&amp;rft.pub=DogEar+Publishing&amp;rft.date=2016-03-16&amp;rft.isbn=978-1457542930&amp;rft.au=Lorelei&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span>
<ul><li>Personal story of a woman, raised LDS, who leaves the Church after discovering doctrinal problems.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPearson2006" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Carol_Lynn_Pearson" title="Carol Lynn Pearson">Pearson, Carol Lynn</a> (2006). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Goodbye,_I_Love_You&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Goodbye, I Love You (page does not exist)">Goodbye, I Love You</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Cedar_Fort,_Inc." title="Cedar Fort, Inc.">Cedar Fort</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1555179843" title="Special:BookSources/1555179843"><bdi>1555179843</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Goodbye%2C+I+Love+You&amp;rft.pub=Cedar+Fort&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.isbn=1555179843&amp;rft.aulast=Pearson&amp;rft.aufirst=Carol+Lynn&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=gKIhCgAAQBAJ">[92]</a>
<ul><li>A memoir of a LDS woman's marriage to a gay man who died of <a href="/wiki/AIDS" class="mw-redirect" title="AIDS">AIDS</a> in 1984.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFShipps2000" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Jan_Shipps" title="Jan Shipps">Shipps, Jan</a> (19 December 2000). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Sojourner_in_the_Promised_Land&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Sojourner in the Promised Land (page does not exist)">Sojourner in the Promised Land</a>: Forty Years Among the Mormons</i>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0252025903" title="Special:BookSources/0252025903"><bdi>0252025903</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Sojourner+in+the+Promised+Land%3A+Forty+Years+Among+the+Mormons&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=2000-12-19&amp;rft.isbn=0252025903&amp;rft.aulast=Shipps&amp;rft.aufirst=Jan&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=XDrlJJ1xCEkC">[93]</a>
<ul><li>An assemblage of writings about the Latter-day Saints by a preeminent non-Mormon interpreter of Mormonism; combination of a portrait of the evolution of contemporary Mormonism (from a provincial to a universal belief system), with an intellectual autobiography of her personal encounters.</li></ul></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBrooks2012" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Joanna_Brooks" title="Joanna Brooks">Brooks, Joanna</a> (2012). <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Book_of_Mormon_Girl&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Book of Mormon Girl (page does not exist)">The Book of Mormon Girl</a>: A Memoir of an American Faith</i>. <a href="/wiki/Simon_%26_Schuster" title="Simon &amp; Schuster">Simon &amp; Schuster</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1451699685" title="Special:BookSources/978-1451699685"><bdi>978-1451699685</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Book+of+Mormon+Girl%3A+A+Memoir+of+an+American+Faith&amp;rft.pub=Simon+%26+Schuster&amp;rft.date=2012&amp;rft.isbn=978-1451699685&amp;rft.aulast=Brooks&amp;rft.aufirst=Joanna&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABibliography+of+the+Latter+Day+Saint+movement" class="Z3988"></span> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=XGWYwDoG9gcC">[94]</a>
<ul><li>Memoir of growing up in a devoutly LDS home; growing older and coming to wrestle with some tenets of the Church (including its stance on women's rights and homosexuality).</li></ul></li></ul>
